<h1>Internet Update #7</h1>

<center>
<h3>THE GEORGE WASHINGTON UNIVERSITY LAW SCHOOL</h3>
<h3>JACOB BURNS LAW LIBRARY</h3>
<h3>INTERNET UPDATE #7</h3>
<h3>MARCH 1996</h3>
</center>

Welcome to the seventh issue of the <i>Internet Update</i>, a listing of new and noteworthy websites,
gopher sites, and listserv &amp; newsgroup information.
<p>

<h3>This issue includes the following websites:</h3>

<ol>
  <li>ABA Network</li>
  <li>ACLU Freedom Network#</li>
  <li>Alaska Legal Resource Center</li>
  <li>All Politics#</li>
  <li>Arkansas Judiciary</li>
  <li>California Judicial Branch</li>
  <li>Canadian Government Online#</li>
  <li>CCH, Incorporated's Tax Legislation Hot Link</li>
  <li>Cleveland-Marshall College of Law and the Law Library -- change of address</li>
  <li>Community Environmental Council (CEC) -- Publications</li>
  <li>CRS Abstracts</li>
  <li>CubaWeb</li>
  <li>Emory Law School -- new link: (1)  U.S. Court of Appeals for the First Circuit</li>
  <li>EPA -- new links: (1)  Partners for the Environment, (2)  Region 1, (3)  Region 6, and (4) 
40 CFR -- Environmental Protection</li>
  <li>Federal Transit Administration</li>
  <li>Florida Supreme Court</li>
  <li>Fulton County Law Library</li>
  <li>GPO Access -- new links: (1)  Comptroller General Decisions and (2)  Economic Report of
the President</li>
  <li>GPO Access Search Tips</li>
  <li>Immigration Central--ITA (Information Technology Associates)</li>
  <li>Information Network of Kansas</li>
  <li>Journal of Criminal Justice and Popular Culture</li>
  <li>Lawbook Exchange, Ltd. -- new online catalogue: (1)  Antiquarian Catalogue 17</li>
  <li>LegalServ (Legal Services Directory)</li>
  <li>Minnesota State Legislature</li>
  <li>Missouri Digital News</li>
  <li>National Archives and Records Administration (NARA) -- new links: (1)  NARA home page,
(2)  NARA National Audiovisual Information Locator (NAIL), and (3)  NARA Government
Information Locator Service (GILS)#</li>
  <li>New Jersey Online</li>
  <li>PBS Citizens '96 Page#</li>
  <li>"Politics by the Numbers"</li>
  <li>RealCom National Politics and Personalities#</li>
  <li>Robert Crown Law Library at Stanford Law School -- new link: (1)  Unpublished Decisions</li>
  <li>Seoul National University College of Law</li>
  <li>State of Iowa</li>
  <li>State of Maryland</li>
  <li>State of Pennsylvania</li>
  <li>State of Virginia</li>
  <li>State Taxation Information#</li>
  <li>Telecommunications Act of 1996#</li>
  <li>Thomson acquisition of West Publishing Co.</li>
  <li>U.S. House of Representatives -- new link: (1)  Committee on Economic &amp; Educational
Opportunities</li>
  <li>Washington Weekly Presidential Primaries Page#</li>
</ol>


<h3>This issue contains the following listservs:</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Communications Decency Act of 1996 (CDA96-L) Discussion Group</li>
  <li>Pollution Prevention Mailing List</li>
  <li>Washburn University School of Law -- new listservs available: (1)  CaliforniaAttorneys-L, (2) 
ColoradoAttorneys-L, (3)  ExpertWitness-L, (4)  FloridaAttorneys-L, (5)  IllinoisAttorneys-L,
(6)  IowaAttorneys-L, (7)  MissouriAttorneys-L, (8)  NebraskaAttorneys-L, (9) 
OklahomaAttorneys-L, (10)  TexasAttorneys-L, (11)  WashingtondcAttorneys-L</li>
</ol>



<center>
<h2> ~ W E B S I T E S ~ </h2>
</center>

<dl>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.abanet.org/">1.  ABA NETWORK</a>
   <br>
   http://www.abanet.org/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The American Bar Association offers access through the
WWW to information about the association and its activities, links to relevant sites,
meeting announcements, and information on continuing legal education resources. Users
can also browse the group's catalogue of books, periodicals, and videotapes."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   2.  ACLU FREEDOM NETWORK
   <br>
   <a href="http://www.aclu.org/textpg.html">(1)  text-only</a>
   <br>
   http://www.aclu.org/textpg.html
   <br>
   <a href="http://www.aclu.org/">(2)  graphical</a>
   <br>
   http://www.aclu.org/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The ACLU Freedom Network is available on the web.  It
contains sections on issues including church and state, criminal justice, cyber-liberties,
the death penalty, free speech, racial equality, voting rights, and women's rights, among
others.  One of the highlights of the site is its inclusion of full text of the ACLU v Reno
complaint, regarding the  indecency provisions of the telecommunications legislation."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.touchngo.com/lglcntr/lglcntr.htm">3.  ALASKA LEGAL RESOURCE CENTER</a>
   <br>
   http://www.touchngo.com/lglcntr/lglcntr.htm
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The Alaska Legal Resource Center has expanded its coverage
of Alaska and national legal resources on the WWW.  It has same-day coverage of state
supreme court and court of appeals decisions, Alaska statutes, and state administrative
code and US district court rules, including local bankruptcy rules."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://allpolitics.com/info/contents.shtml">4.  ALL POLITICS</a>
   <br>
   http://allpolitics.com/info/contents.shtml
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "All Politics, a collaborative effort of CNN and Time
Magazine, covers all aspects of the 1996 campaign and includes several multimedia
efforts which set this site apart from the rest.  Besides news and candidate information,
it includes an issues matrix and a  rate-o-matic' that compares your views to the
candidates'.  Campaignland provides multimedia ads from present and past campaigns. 
An  election monitor' offers the latest Time/CNN polls.  In Focus features full text Time
Magazine articles on issues, and Intelligence features political analysis from CNN."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.state.ar.us/supremecourt/">5.  ARKANSAS JUDICIARY</a>
   <br>
   http://www.state.ar.us/supremecourt/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The Arkansas Supreme Court Library is proud to announce
the completion of the Arkansas Judiciary Home Page.  Linked to the Arkansas State
Home Page, the Judiciary Home Page contains a world of information about the
Arkansas court system and the library that serves it.  Opinions of the appellate courts
are loaded each Monday and Wednesday within minutes of being released by the courts. 
The opinions are updated each week with headnotes and editorial changes."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.courtinfo.ca.gov">6.  CALIFORNIA JUDICIAL BRANCH</a>
   <br>
   http://www.courtinfo.ca.gov
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The California Judicial Branch Website is now available." 
This site includes links to the California courts, opinions of the California Supreme
Court and Courts of Appeal, publications, and information about the Judicial Council of
California and the Administrative Office of the Courts.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://canada.gc.ca/">7.  CANADIAN GOVERNMENT ONLINE</a>
   <br>
   http://canada.gc.ca/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The Canadian Government Online web site provides
information of all kinds about Canada and its institutions.  The real power of the site is
its exhaustive  to Canadian Federal Institutions, arranged alphabetically, from
Agriculture and Agri-Food Canada to Yukon Water Board.  The  is completely
searchable.  Both English and French sites are accessible from the home page."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.cch.com/">8.  CCH, INCORPORATED'S TAX LEGISLATION HOT LINK</a>
   <br>
   http://www.cch.com/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "CCH, Incorporated, a provider of tax and  law information,
software and services, has a website.  Internet users can access CCH's Tax Legislation
Hot Links there, finding updates that include potential actions on topics such as
provisions facilitating long-term savings, business and investment breaks, small business
incentives, family-oriented and senior citizen tax breaks, extender provisions, the
taxpayer bill of rights and earned income tax credit reform."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   9.  CLEVELAND-MARSHALL COLLEGE OF LAW &amp; LAW LIBRARY -- new addresses
   <br>
   <a href="http://www.law.csuohio.edu/">(1)  Law School</a>
   <br>
   http://www.law.csuohio.edu/
   <br> 
   <a href="http://www.law.csuohio.edu/lawlibrary/">(2)  Law Library</a>
   <br>
   http://www.law.csuohio.edu/lawlibrary/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The Cleveland-Marshall College of Law and the Law Library
have completed a reconfiguration of our Home Pages and subsequently we have changed
some URLs.  We apologize for any inconvenience."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.grc.org/cec/">10.  COMMUNITY ENVIRONMENTAL COUNCIL (CEC) -- PUBLICATIONS</a>
   <br>
   http://www.grc.org/cec/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The CEC was founded in 1970 in Santa Barbara, CA, in
the wake of the disastrous Santa Barbara oil spill.  The CEC sought to address the
practical considerations of environmental and natural resource management, and has 
evolved into an  internationally recognized nonprofit research, policy development, and
education organization.'  The CEC is now using the Internet as a means of
disseminating its publications free of charge."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.clark.net/pub/pennyhill/pennyhill.html">11.  CRS ABSTRACTS</a>
   <br>
   http://www.clark.net/pub/pennyhill/pennyhill.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "Abstracts of Congressional Research Service (CRS) reports,
studies, fact sheets, Issue Briefs, and other documents are available at the Pennyhill
site.  Although this is a commercial service, access to the abstracts are free.  The service
provides same-day shipment of documents.  Librarians and others can, of course, obtain
the full documents from a Member of Congress without charge."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.cubaweb.cu/">12.  CUBAWEB</a>
   <br> 
   http://www.cubaweb.cu/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The national office of the Technological Information
Promotion Systems of Cuba offers access through the World Wide Web to  CubaWeb,' a
resource for news, investment, trade and travel information, cultural arts, and diplomatic
information on the Cuban government."  Links are in Spanish and English.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   13.  EMORY LAW SCHOOL -- new link
   <br>
   <a href="http://www.law.emory.edu/1circuit">(1)  U.S. COURT OF APPEALS FOR THE FIRST CIRCUIT CASES</a>
   <br>
   http://www.law.emory.edu/1circuit
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "In cooperation with the U.S. Court of Appeals for the First
Circuit, Information Technology Systems (ITS), is pleased to announce the immediate
availability of that court's cases in full text and keyword searchable.  Currently Emory
offers First Circuit cases from November 1995 to the present."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   14.  EPA -- new links
   <br>
   <a href="http://www.epa.gov/partners/">(1)  PARTNERS FOR THE ENVIRONMENT</a>
   <br>
   http://www.epa.gov/partners/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "Partners for the Environment presents an array of programs
that represent cooperative partnerships between businesses and other stakeholders and
the EPA.  These voluntary programs mark a change in direction for EPA's national
strategy by including, along with traditional approaches toward environmental protection,
voluntary commitments as a way to achieve real environmental results in a timely and
cost-effective way.'"</i>
</dd>
<br>
<dt>
   <a href="http://www.epa.gov/region01/">(2)  REGION 1</a>
   <br>
   http://www.epa.gov/region01/
   <br>
   <a href="http://www.epa.gov/earth1r6/">(3)  REGION 6</a>
   <br>
   http://www.epa.gov/earth1r6/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "Two more regions of the U.S. EPA have released home pages
-- Region 1, which includes Maine, New Hampshire, Vermont, Massachusetts,
Connecticut, and Rhode Island; and Region 6, which covers Arkansas, Louisiana, New
Mexico, Oklahoma, and Texas.  The Region 1 homepage currently offers access to
information on programs and special initiatives underway in the New England area, and
is planning to present more information, such as data sets and software tools, in the
future.  The Region 6 homepage presently focuses on their Water Quality Protection
Division and regional geographic information systems,  also provides links to other
servers that maintain information relating to Native Americans and the various states in
the region."</i>
</dd>
<br>
<dt>
   <a href="http://www.epa.gov/epacfr40/">(4) CFR -- ENVIRONMENTAL PROTECTION</a>
   <br>
   http://www.epa.gov/epacfr40/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The release of the 1995 issue of Title 40 of the CFR is a
pilot project of the EPA.  This project is designed to provide expanded access to
environmental  prior to the release of an official electronic version of the entire CFR by
the GPO.  The files used to create the information released under this pilot were provided
by the Office of Federal Register and represent the data used to print the July 1, 1995
edition of 40 CFR."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.fta.dot.gov/">15.  FEDERAL TRANSIT ADMINISTRATION</a>
   <br>
   http://www.fta.dot.gov/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "Federal Transit Administration offers access through the
WWW to information on transit panning and policy, and to current research and
technology developments within the industry.  Users can gain access to the National
Transit Database, which contains data on more than 600 transit agencies in the
country."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.rcfp.org">16.  FIRST AMENDMENT HANDBOOK</a>
   <br>
   http://www.rcfp.org
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The Reporters Committee for Freedom of the Press offers
access through the WWW to  The First Amendment Handbook,' a biweekly newsletter
on issues related to a free press.  The service also contains information on the Freedom
of Information Act and links to other journalism-related websites."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://justice.courts.state.fl.us/courts/supct/">17.  FLORIDA SUPREME COURT</a>
   <br>
   http://justice.courts.state.fl.us/courts/supct/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The Florida Supreme Court is pleased to announce that its
web page is now up and running.  The Page features biographies of the Justices,
portraits and anecdotes about past Justices from the Portrait Gallery, tons of useful legal
research and public information links, Court documents and recent opinions,
architectural notes about the Courthouse, and lots more."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.mindspring.com/~fclawlib/">18.  FULTON COUNTY LAW LIBRARY (ATLANTA, GA)</a>
   <br>
   http://www.mindspring.com/~fclawlib/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>This site contains information about the Georgia Court system, list of legal resources
links, an annotated list the local law libraries.  A "Frequently Asked Questions" section
is under construction.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.access.gpo.gov/su_docs">19.  GPO ACCESS</a> -- new links
   <br>
   (1)  GAO COMPTROLLER GENERAL DECISIONS
   <br>
   (2) ECONOMIC REPORT OF THE PRESIDENT
   <br>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>Click on the link, "Select Search and retrieve Full Text Online Via GPO Access From Over 50 Databases."  Scroll down to the list of documents.  Click on the desired database and enter search terms in the designated box.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.ll.georgetown.edu/wtaylor/gposrch.html">20.  GPO ACCESS SEARCH TIPS</a>
   <br>
   http://www.ll.georgetown.edu/wtaylor/gposrch.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "I have created a web page with searching tips for users of
GPO Access.  This is written for people who need a shorter, more handy reference than
the comprehensive GPO pages.  It assumes you are already familiar with the basics of
full-text searching, including Boolean operators."  Note that the address has to lower case
L's (for "law library") after the "www," and not the number eleven.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.wave.net/upg/immigration/index.html">21.  IMMIGRATION CENTRAL--ITA</a>
   <br>
   http://www.wave.net/upg/immigration/index.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "Immigration Central--ITA is a new website created by
Information Technology Associates, producers of the Immigration Assistant program for
immigration professionals.  ITA has a  gateway to an extensive menu of U.S.
immigration resources, including government and private sites offering information on
federal law, immigration regulations, books and other helpful immigration advice.' 
Resources include the INS, U.S. State Dept., Siskind &amp; Susser's immigration
newsletter, foreign embassies and others."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.ink.org/">22.  INFORMATION NETWORK OF KANSAS</a>
   <br>
   http://www.ink.org/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "State of Kansas offers access through the to the Information
Network of Kansas.'  The site is divided into sections related to business, education, local
and government, and professional associations.  Users can the full text of bills introduced
during the current legislative session, or browse library catalogues."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.scj.albany.edu:90/jcjpc/">23.  JOURNAL OF CRIMINAL JUSTICE AND POPULAR CULTURE (JCJPC)</a>
   <br>
   http://www.scj.albany.edu:90/jcjpc/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The State University of New York at Albany offers access
through the World Wide Web to the Journal of Criminal Justice and Popular Culture.  It
features reviews and essays on issues related to crime and its depiction in the
entertainment industry and other forms of popular culture."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   24.  LAWBOOK EXCHANGE, LTD. -- new online catalogue
   <br>
   <a href="http://www.abaa-booknet.com/usa/lbe/">(1)  ANTIQUARIAN CATALOGUE</a>
   <br>
   http://www.abaa-booknet.com/usa/lbe/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "Antiquarian Catalogue 17 contains nearly one-thousand
items in all fields of law and legal history.  The selection includes scholarly and
out-of-print books, mainly from the 20th century."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.leg.state.mn.us">25.  MINNESOTA STATE LEGISLATURE</a>
   <br>
   http://www.leg.state.mn.us
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "Last month the Minnesota State Legislature unveiled their
home page, a project of the Minnesota Legislative Reference Library on behalf of the
Minnesota House, Senate, and joint legislative offices.  The website offers access to the
full-text the Minnesota session laws for 1994 and 1995 (summaries for 1993)."</i>
</dd>

<p>


<dt>
   <a href="http://www.mdn.org/">26.  MISSOURI DIGITAL NEWS</a>
   <br>
   http://www.mdn.org/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "University of Missouri at Columbia access through the
WWW to  Missouri Digital News,' an electronic news-and-information service on state
government.  Users can retrieve information on the General Assembly, including pending
bills, Senate and House rosters and committee memberships, budget recommendations,
and voting records."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
