and job listings."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.state.pa.us/">34.  STATE OF PENNSYLVANIA</a>
   <br> 
   http://www.state.pa.us/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "State of Pennsylvania offers access through the WWW to
public information related to the state, including colleges and universities, economic
development plans, history, state technology initiatives, and a visitor's guide to tourism
and recreation."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.state.va.us/">35.  STATE OF VIRGINIA</a>
   <br>
   http://www.state.va.us/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "State of Virginia offers access through the WWW to state
agencies and related home pages, including the Virginia Assembly.  Users can browse
the online visitor's guide, which features information on historic sites, museums, and
parks."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/stahl/statinfo.htm">36.  STATE TAXATION INFORMATION</a>
   <br>
   http://ourworld.compuserve.com/homepages/stahl/statinfo.htm
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "Information on state taxation for each state is available. 
Addresses and phone numbers are provided for each state's revenue department. 
Pointers to the revenue department or general state home page are provided."  For some
states, tax forms can be downloaded."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   38.  TELECOMMUNICATIONS ACT OF 1996
   <br>
   (1)  THOMAS SITES
   <br>
   <a href="http://thomas.loc.gov/home/hot-titl.html">(a)  ACT IN SECTIONS</a>
   <br>
   http://thomas.loc.gov/home/hot-titl.html
   <br>
   <a href="ftp://ftp.loc.gov/pub/thomas/c104/s652.enr.txt">(b)  ACT IN ITS ENTIRETY</a>
   <br>
   ftp://ftp.loc.gov/pub/thomas/c104/s652.enr.txt
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The telecom bill has passed and been signed into law.  Full
text of the Telecommunications Law is available via the Internet."</i>
</dd>
<br>
<dt>
   <a href="http://www.commlaw.com/">(2)  PEPPER &amp; CORAZZINI, LLP</a>
   <br>
   http://www.commlaw.com/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "Pepper &amp; Corazzini specializes in communications,
telecommunications, Internet and online services law."  This site has a link that provides
a summary of the Telecom Act as well as links to related websites.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.thomson-thomson.com/">39.  THOMSOM &amp; THOMSON</a>
   <br>
   http://www.thomson-thomson.com/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "Thomson&amp; Thomson, a worldwide trademark and copyright
research company, offers searching and watching services of Internet domain names
registered with Network Solutions, Inc.  The company says clients will find the search

helpful for determining if the names they plan to use as their Internet site addresses
already are taken, or to see if a registered domain name conflicts with a client's existing
or planned trademark."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www1.nando.net/newsroom/ntn/biz/022696/biz4_25505.html">40.  THOMSON ACQUISITION OF WEST PUBLISHING CO.</a>
   <br>
   http://www1.nando.net/newsroom/ntn/biz/022696/biz4_25505.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the headline: "Thomson to Buy West Publishing Company for $3.425 Billion."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   41.  U.S. HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES -- new link
   <br>
   <a href="http://www.house.gov/eeo/">(1)  COMMITTEE ON ECONOMIC AND EDUCATIONAL OPPORTUNITIES</a>
   <br>
   http://www.house.gov/eeo/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "U.S. House of Representatives offers WWW access to
current information from its Committee on Economic and Educational Opportunities. 
Users can study student-aid issues, find out about the impact of the Balanced Budget
Act of 1995 on student-loan savings, and retrieve the text of proposed committee
legislation.  A listing of committee members and their biographies is also available."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://dolphin.gulf.net/Primaries.html">42.  WASHINGTON WEEKLY PRESIDENTIAL PRIMARIES PAGE</a>
   <br>
   http://dolphin.gulf.net/Primaries.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The Washington Weekly (an Internet newspaper) offers a
Presidential Primaries Page that is organized by candidate within each party.  For most
candidates there is biographical information, voting record, list of accomplishments or
stands on key issues, and a connection to the candidate's home page when available. 
This is a non-graphical but well organized page that provides the user with quick access
to voting records, speeches and press releases, and Web pages of the candidates."</i>
</dd>


</dl>


<center>
<h2>~ L I S T S E R V S ~</h2>
</center>


<dl>

<dt>
   <b>1.  COMMUNICATIONS DECENCY ACT OF 1996 DISCUSSION GROUP</b>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "CDA96-L is open to the networking community.  Its primary role is to
serve as a means of communication among people who are concerned about the implications of the
United States of America's Communication Decency Act of 1996 (signed into law by President
Clinton on February 8, 1996.  Its secondary role is to serve as a discussion forum for similar
legislation or regulation that may be in the formative or final stages in any other country, or at any
local jurisdiction that would restrict, limit or inhibit use of Internet resources based on ' decency,' 
'morality,' 'offensiveness,' or based on the age of someone using, operating, or accessing an Internet
resource."  To subscribe:</i>

<p>

<i>send to:</i> listproc@willamette.edu<br>
<i>with the message:</i> sub cda96-l &lt;your name&gt;

</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <b>2.  POLLUTION PREVENTION MAILING LIST</b>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The P2TECH mailing list invites all those involved in providing technical
assistance to industries on pollution prevention matters to share information and assist one another in
these efforts.  The P2TECH mailing list was implemented by the National Round table of State
Pollution Prevention Programs with support from the EPA's Pollution Prevention Information
Exchange System (PIES), the National Institute of Standards and Technology's (NIST)
Manufacturing Extension Partnership TECNET Program, Battelle Pacific Northwest Lab, and the
Great Lake Information Network (GLIN)."  To subscribe:</i>

<p>

<i>send to:</i> GLIN-majordomo@great-lakes.net<br>
<i>with the message:</i> subscribe P2TECH

</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <b>3.  WASHBURN UNIVERSITY SCHOOL OF LAW -- new listservs available</b>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>All of the listed listservs are unrestricted designed to facilitate communication between the target group
(attorneys or expert witnesses).  Note that a distinguishing feature of this service is that Washburn will
use the listserv to create a comprehensive email directory of attorneys (or expert witnesses, if you join
that particular listserv) and turned into a public email directory on WashLaw web, so if you do not
want to be listed in the public email directory, do not join this listserv!  To subscribe:</i>

<p>

<i>send to:</i> listserv@assocdir.wuacc.edu<br>
<i>with the message:</i> subscribe name of the listserv (check the listing at the beginning of this Internet
Update) &lt;your name&gt; &lt;your specialty, not to exceed 4 words!&gt;  (E.g.) subscribe
texasattorneys-l john doe criminal defense

</dd>
</dl>


<hr>

<i>Internet Update</i> is compiled by Leslie A. Lee, Reference Librarian at the Jacob Burns Law
Library, and is issued monthly as a service to the George Washington University Law School
community.

