<p>

<dt>21.  UNIVERSITY OF COLORADO-BOULDER GOVERNMENT PUBLICATIONS LIBRARY -- INTERNATIONAL ORGANIZATION INFORMATION ON THE INTERNET<br>
   <a href=http://www.colorado.edu/libraries/govpubs/>(1)  Main site</a>
   <br>
   http://www.colorado.edu/libraries/govpubs/<br>
   <a href=http://www.colorado.edu/libraries/govpubs/internat.htm>(2)  International Organizations site</a>
   <br>
   http://www.colorado.edu/libraries/govpubs/internat.htm
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The University of Colorado-Boulder Government Publications Library site is similar to the Federal Government Information on the Internet web page, with one major exception.  It also covers foreign agency statistics and government information very thoroughly.  Under 'International Documents' there are links to various international agencies such as the Asian Development Bank, EU, IMF, World Bank, UN and several of its organizations, and the International Atomic Energy Agency, among others."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=gopher://silo.adp.wisc.edu>22.  UNIVERSITY  OF WISCONSIN -- WOMEN'S STUDIES BIBLIOGRAPHIES</a>
   <br>
   gopher://silo.adp.wisc.edu	select "Campus Libraries Information - U.W. Madison," / "U.W. Madison Libraries Centers U-Z" / "Women's Studies Librarian's Office" / "Wisconsin Bibliographies in Women's Studies"
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The Women's Studies Librarian's Office of the University of Wisconsin System has recently made two new annotated bibliographies available via gopher.  Information Technology and Women's Lives, by Linda Shult.  The bibliography is available as one file, or as individual chapters, and is completely searchable.  Also offered is Mentoring Women in Higher Education: An Annotated Bibliography, by Phyllis Holman Weisbard. "</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://lawlib.wuacc.edu/washlaw/washlaw.html>23.  WASHBURN UNIVERSITY SCHOOL OF LAW -- new CHAT service</a>
   <br>
   http://lawlib.wuacc.edu/washlaw/washlaw.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "Washburn University School of Law is pleased to announce a new (free) online Web based CHAT service (live discussions on Internet) covering law related topics.  Topics include: lawyers, law professors, law librarians, law students, family law, tek-talk."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://www.feminist.org/other/wh_menu.html>24.  WOMEN'S HISTORY MONTH</a>
   <br>
   http://www.feminist.org/other/wh_menu.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "In honor of Women's History Month, the Feminist Majority Online's Women's Web World has created a 'Women's History World' page.  A fact of the day, book of the day, and link of the day are provided, as are calendar dates and events.  A 'Teach Women's History' page offers various teaching tools including a full text browsable and searchable online version of 'The Feminist Chronicles: 1953-1993'  by Toni Carabillo, Judith Meuli, and June Bundy Csida."</i>
</dd>

</dl>
	    
<center>
<h2>~ L I S T S E R V S ~</h2>
</center>

<dl>

<dt>
   <b>1.  ASSESSING ENVIRONMENTAL IMPACTS OF AGRICULTURE DISCUSSION GROUP</b>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "A new discussion group has been created to facilitate communication among 'multi-disciplinary researchers and practitioners working to develop environmental impact assessment systems and tools, or involved with the application of environmental impact assessment methods.'  The list, Ag-Impact, will be unmoderated and will cover all aspects of environmental impact assessment tools and methodologies.  To subscribe:</i>
   <p>
   <i>Send email to: </i>listproc@mtn.org<br>
   <i>With this message: </i>subscribe Ag-Impact <your name>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <b>2.  COURT-WEB-L</b>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "Announcing COURT-WEB-L: an email list dedicated to the discussion of problems, policies, and solutions for state and federal courts in maintaining web services.  This forum is available for the discussion of various issues relating to court maintained Internet services.  Discussion may include the technical problems and solutions encountered by court web administrators. This is also an appropriate forum for the discussion of policy issues that court web administrators must consider in making judicial information available on the Internet."  To subscribe:</i>
   <p>
   <i>Send email to: </i>listproc@citabra.uark.edu<br>
   <i>With this message: </i>subscribe court-web-l <your name>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <b>3.  CYBERSPACE-LAW</b>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "Cyberspace-Law is a distribution list for those interested in learning principles of law as they are applied to the Internet.  Topics include copyright and trademark law, free speech, libel, and privacy."  To subscribe:</i>
   <p>
   <i>Send email to: </i>listproc-request@counsel.com<br>
   <i>With this message: </i>SUBSCRIBE CYBERSPACE-LAW <your name>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <b>4.  INTERNATIONAL RELATIONS LIST</b>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The Theory of International Relations List is a moderated, manually distributed list for the scholarly discussion of ideas and issues directly related to International Relations (IR) theory and its research, as well as communicating with others involved or interested in IR theory and its research."  To subscribe:</i>
   <p>
   <i>Send email to: </i>IRTHEORY@UNIMELB.EDU.AU<br>
   <i>With this message: </i>SUBSCRIBE IRTHEORY <first name, last name>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <b>5.  LAW-TAG MAILING LIST</b>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "Announcing a new mailing list for those interested in development or writing of hypertext legal materials or legal instructional materials." To subscribe:</i>
   <p>
   <i>Send email to: </i>listserv@stcl.edu<br>
   <i>With this message: </i>subscribe law-tag
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <b>6.  LEXIS COUNSEL CONNECT'S NEWSLETTER, ÎTHE SQUIB'</b>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "Counsel Connect launched its free electronic newsletter, The Squib.  The Squib includes announcements and info on upcoming online seminars and events, hot legal documents and cases, new discussion forums, clients seeking to retain lawyers, legal websites (with reviews and weekly picks), and lots more." To subscribe:</i>
   <p>
   <i>Send email to: </i>listproc-request@counsel.com<br>
   <i>With this message: </i>subscribe the-squib <your name>
</dd>

</dl>
	 
	 
<hr>

<i>Internet Update</i> is compiled by Leslie A. Lee, Reference Librarian at the Jacob Burns Law
Library, and is issued monthly as a service to the George Washington University Law School
community.

