<dl>
<dt>
   <b>10.  LIFTON'S LABOR LAW LETTER (LLLL-L)</b>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "Lifton's Labor Law Letter is an open, moderated newsletter which will be
circulated twice monthly.  The topic is labor law and collective bargaining negotiation for the public
sector, especially schools and colleges.  The moderator, Fred Lifton, has conducted more than 700
collective bargaining negotiations in his career.  While school administrators, school board members,
and school-related unions will have particular interest in this newsletter, anyone is welcome to
participate."   To subscribe:</i>

<p>

<i>Send e-mail to:</i> Listproc@schoolaw.com<br>
<i>With message: </i>subscribe LLLL-L &lt;your e-mail address&gt;

</dd>
</dl>



<dl>
<dt>
   <b>11.  SUPREME COURT DECISIONS</b>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>Cornell's Legal Information Institute's (LII) Supreme Court Bulletin electronic newsletter provides
subscribers with quick, free access to syllabi of decisions handed down by the United States Supreme
Court.  Subscribers can expect to receive these summaries within a few hours after the decision was
rendered.  Also, if you want to receive the full-text of the decision, simply sed the message: </i>get
US&lt;casenumber&gt; (<i>e.g.,</i> get US96-1234)<i> to the same listserv address, and the opinion will be sent
to your e-mail address shortly.</i>  <i>To subscribe:</i>

<p>

<i>Send e-mail to:</i> listserv@listserv.law.cornell.edu<br>
<i>With message: </i>subscribe liibulletin &lt;your first name, your last name&gt;

</dd>
</dl>

