<h1>Internet Update 15</h1>

<center>
<h3>THE GEORGE WASHINGTON UNIVERSITY LAW SCHOOL</h3>
<h3>JACOB BURNS LAW LIBRARY</h3>
<h3>INTERNET UPDATE #15</h3>
<h3>NOVEMBER 1996</h3>
</center>

Welcome to the fifteenth issue of the <i>Internet Update</i>, a listing of new and noteworthy websites,
gopher sites, and listserv &amp; newsgroup information.
<p>

<h3>This issue includes the following websites:</h3>


<ol>
  <li>Atlantic Monthly Poetry Pages#</li>
  <li>Biography.com#</li>
  <li>Center for International Legal Studies Online</li>
  <li>Central European Environmental Data Request Facility (CEDAR)$</li>
  <li>Commission for Environmental Cooperation (CEC)$</li>
  <li>Commission on Presidential Debates#</li>
  <li>Contemporary Conflicts in Africa#</li>
  <li>"Culture, Society and Advanced Information Technology" Report#</li>
  <li>DOD Information Analysis Center (IAC) Newsletter#</li>
  <li>Department of Interior's Natural Resources Library$</li>
  <li>Election Notes--Klipsan Press</li>
  <li>Elsevier Science 'Contents Direct' and Tables of Contents#</li>
  <li>EnviroText$</li>
  <li>Food Quality Protection Act of 1996$</li>
  <li>Free On-Line Dictionary of Computing</li>
  <li>Hansard Debates Online:  (1)  House of Commons and (2) House of Lords#</li>
  <li>Journal of Internet Banking and Commerce</li>
  <li>Law Journal Xtra!#</li>
  <li>McKenna & Cuneo, L.L.P.</li>
  <li>Mercury Mail--Customized News By Email#</li>
  <li>National Agricultural Safety Database Resource Directory#</li>
  <li>National Center for Environmental Research and Quality Assurance (NCERQA)</li>
  <li>National Library for the Environment#</li>
  <li>One World Magazine#</li>
  <li>Panos Institute$</li>
  <li>Prickett, Jones, Elliott, Kristol, and Schnee -- new law firm homepage</li>
  <li>Roads to Refuge--Witness online documentary series</li>
  <li>Teaching Critical Evaluation Skills for WWW Resources</li>
  <li>Ultimate News Links Page#</li>
  <li>UNEP IE OzonAction Programme</li>
  <li>U.N. Food and Agriculture Organization -- new publications: (1) Commodity Market Review,
1995-96, (2) Food Outlook, and (3) Food Crops and Shortages</li>
  <li>U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees#</li>
  <li>U.N. Peace-keeping Bibliography#</li>
  <li>U.S. Code of Federal Regulations#</li>
  <li>U.S. Commission on Libraries &amp; Information Science</li>
  <li>U.S. Department of Justice's Bureau of Justice Statistics</li>
  <li>U.S. EPA Home Page -- redesigned$</li>
  <li>U.S. EPA's Test Method Index$</li>
