<dt>
   <a href="http://www.TheLawOffice.com/Intl_Law/CILS">3.  CENTER FOR INTERNATIONAL LEGAL STUDIES</a>
   <br>
   http://www.TheLawOffice.com/Intl_Law/CILS
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the homepage: "The Center for International Legal Studies is a non-profit
research, training, and law publications institute, established and operating under
Austrian law and with its international headquarters in Salzburg, Austria. The Center
has operated since 1976 in Salzburg. It has a close cooperation with the Faculty of Law
of the University of Salzburg, the Faculty of Law of the University of Amsterdam, The
Netherlands, the Faculty of Law of the University of Durham, England, and the
Faculty of Law of the Catholic University of Leuven, Belgium, the Austro-American
Institute in Vienna, and numerous other universities and educational organizations in
Europe and the United States. The Center's essential purpose is the promotion of the
dissemination of information among members of the international legal community, this
being achieved through the Center's various research and law publication projects and the
administration of post-graduate and professional training programs. More than 1,200
lawyers worldwide have been designated as Fellows of the Center for International Legal
Studies. "</i>
</dd>

