</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement:  "EnviroText is an online library consisting primarily of environment, safety, and health requirements.  EnviroText began to provide easy access and reliable information for the regulated community to comply with environmental requirements.  The service was developed through a cooperative effort among the following:  the EPA, DOE, DOI, DOJ, DOD, U.S. Army Corps of Engineers Construction and Engineering Research Laboratory, and the University of Illinois.  EnviroText contains datasets covering Federal, State, Indian Tribal, and Agency-specific information.  These datasets include the following:  the entire U.S. Code; most of the C.F.R. and the Federal Register, which is updated daily; Presidential Executive Orders from 1945 to the present; most Indian Tribal Codes; a complete set of Indian Tribal Agreements and Treatises; and a set of all International Agreements and Treaties."</i>
</dd>

