<dt>
   <a href="http://www.epa.gov/opppsps1/fqpa/index.html">14.  FOOD QUALITY PROTECTION ACT OF 1996 (FQPA)</a>
   <br>
   http://www.epa.gov/opppsps1/fqpa/index.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement:  "The EPA Office of Pesticide Programs is making the full text of the FQPA available from its website.  On August 3, 1996, the President signed the FQPA.  This law amends the two major pesticide laws:  the Federal Insecticide, Fungicide, and Rodenticide Act (FIFRA), and the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act (FFDCA).  This site contains information about the law, how EPA plans to implement the law, and opportunities for public involvement.  Included on this site are registration eligibility decisions, science issues raised by the Act, and emergency exemptions.  Also available are Federal Register notices pertaining to FQPA, Food Safety Advisory Committee (FSAC) information, and readers' guides to effects of the act on current legislation."</i>
</dd>

