<dt>
   31.  U.N. FOOD AND AGRICULTURE ORGANIZATION--NEW PUBLICATIONS:
   <br>
   <a href="http://www.fao.org/waicent/faoinfo/economic/esc/escp/cmrai.htm">(1) COMMODITY MARKET REVIEW, 1995-96</a>
   <br> 
   http://www.fao.org/waicent/faoinfo/economic/esc/escp/cmrai.htm
   <br>
   <a href="http://www.fao.org/waicent/faoinfo/economic/giews/english/fo/fotoc.htm">(2) FOOD OUTLOOK</a>
   <br>
   http://www.fao.org/waicent/faoinfo/economic/giews/english/fo/fotoc.htm
   <br>
   <a href="http://www.fao.org/waicent/faoinfo/economic/giews/english/fs/fstoc.htm">(3) FOOD CROPS AND SHORTAGES</a>
   <br>   
   http://www.fao.org/waicent/faoinfo/economic/giews/english/fs/fstoc.htm<br>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "The Economic and Social Department of the UN Food and
Agriculture Organization (FAO) has made three international food-related publications
available.  'Commodity Market Review, 1995-96' is a new title, replacing 'Commodity
Review and Outlook.'  It presents general developments in the world food economy. 
'Food Outlook' is a bimonthly publication that discusses aspects of world food
production, imports, and exports, and is highlighted by detailed selected country and
region tables on those variables.  'World Food Shortages' is a bimonthly publication that
concentrates on unfavorable crop prospects, food supply shortfalls, and local surpluses by
country.  Together, the three publications provide an excellent overview of the world food
situation."</i>
</dd>

