<body>

<h1>Internet Update #1</h1>

<center>
<h3>THE GEORGE WASHINGTON UNIVERSITY LAW SCHOOL</h3>
<h3>JACOB BURNS LAW LIBRARY</h3>
<h3>INTERNET UPDATE #1</h3>
<h3>MAY 1995</h3>
</center>

Welcome to the first issue of the <i>Internet Update</i>, a listing of new and noteworthy websites,
gopher sites, and listserv &amp; newsgroup information.
<p>

<h3>This issue contains the following websites:</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Canadian Open Government Project</li>
  <li>Fisher College of Business -- The MBA Page</li>
  <li>Gilbert and Sullivan Archive</li>
  <li>InterNet Bankruptcy Library</li>
  <li>United States Institute of Peace</li>
  <li>Walt Whitman's Diaries</li>
  <li>Wilson, Sonsini, Goodrich & Rosati</li>
</ol>

<center>
<h2> ~ W E B S I T E S ~ </h2>
</center>

<dl>

<dt>
   <a href=http://info.ic.gc.ca/opengov>1.  CANADIAN OPEN GOVERNMENT PROJECT</a>
   <br>
   http://info.ic.gc.ca/opengov
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>The Canadian Open Government Project has established a website providing access to Canadian documents, cases, and agency materials.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://www.cob.ohio-state.edu/dept/fin/mba.htm>2.  FISHER COLLEGE OF BUSINESS -- THE MBA PAGE</a>
   <br>
   http://www.cob.ohio-state.edu/dept/fin/mba.htm
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>The Fisher College of Business at Ohio State has created The MBA Page for accessing business resources.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://diamond.idbsu.edu/gas/GaS.html>3.  GILBERT AND SULLIVAN ARCHIVE</a>
   <br>
   http://diamond.idbsu.edu/gas/GaS.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>Music buffs might be interested in the Gilbert and Sullivan Archive, which includes librettos, song scores, and a database of opera performance schedules worldwide.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://bankrupt.com>4.  INTERNET BANKRUPTCY LIBRARY</a>
   <br>
   http://bankrupt.com
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>The InterNet Bankruptcy Library was developed by Bankruptcy Creditors Service in Princton, NJ.  It offers information on companies reorganizing in Canada and the United States, and recently has added data on distressed securities.  It even offers access to foreign statutes.  Looking for information on the Russian Securities Market? It's here!</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://witloof.sjsu.edu/peace/conflict.html>5.  UNITED STATES INSTITUTE OF PEACE</a>
   <br>
   http://witloof.sjsu.edu/peace/conflict.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>The United States Institute of Peace has unveiled its web page, featuring information regarding conflict resolution and negotiation theory.  It can link users to journals and news clippings, mailing lists, and newsgroups.  It has numerous resources on conflicts in South Africa and Northern Ireland--for example, if you are looking for the Joint Declaration of Peace and various support documents exchanged between the Irish and British governments, they are here.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://lcweb2.loc.gov/wwhome.html>6.  WALT WHITMAN'S DIARIES</a>
   <br>
   http://lcweb2.loc.gov/wwhome.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>Literature and history fans might want to look at digitized images of pages from the recently recovered diaries of Walt Whitman.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://www.wsgr.com/>7.  WILSON, SONSINI, GOODRICH & ROSATI</a>
   <br>
   http://www.wsgr.com/
   <br>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>Wilson, Sonsini, Goodrich & Rosati, a Palo Alto firm specializing in technology and life sciences, publishes internal newsletter on IP, life sciences, and media technology which it makes available at its website.  It also provides access to briefs and decisions in major cases.</i>
</dd>

</dl>


<hr>

<i>Internet Update</i> is compiled by Leslie A. Lee, Reference Librarian at the Jacob Burns Law
Library, and is issued monthly as a service to the George Washington University Law School
community.

