<body>

<h1>Internet Update #2</h1>

<center>
<h3>THE GEORGE WASHINGTON UNIVERSITY LAW SCHOOL</h3>
<h3>JACOB BURNS LAW LIBRARY</h3>
<h3>INTERNET UPDATE #2</h3>
<h3>OCTOBER 1995</h3>
</center>

Welcome to the second issue of the <i>Internet Update</i>, a listing of new and noteworthy websites,
gopher sites, and listserv &amp; newsgroup information.
<p>

<h3>This issue contains the following websites:</h3>

<ol>
  <li>Americans With Disabilities Act Document Center</li>
  <li>Currents: International Trade Law Journal</li>
  <li>Edlaw Homepage</li>
  <li>Electronic Privacy Information Center (EPIC)</li>
  <li>First Amendment Cyber-Tribune</li>
  <li>Fourth World Conference On Women, Beijing 1995</li>
  <li>Intellectual Property and the National Information Infrastructure Report</li>
  <li>Ladas & Parry Newsletters & Special Information Bulletins</li>
  <li>Law Employment Center</li>
  <li>National Law Journal and Law Journal Extra! Law Library</li>
  <li>Natural Resources Defense Council Online</li>
  <li>QRD (Lesbians, Gays, Bisexuals, Transgendered Persons Website)
  <li>Scott Rubin's Public Utility Home Page</li>
  <li>State-Specific Resources:  (1)  Alaska Administrative Code, (2)  HyperContract (Massachusetts), (3)  Georgia Online Network</li>
  <li>University of Sheffield's Virtual Law Library</li>
  <li>U.S. Court of Appeals For the Second Circuit</li>
</ol>


<h3>This issue contains the following listservs:</h3>

<ol>
  <li>CCGroup (Constitutional Law Listserv)</li>
  <li>Contents Alert Economics</li>
  <li>Envirolaw</li>
  <li>GAO Daybook</li>
</ol>

<center>
<h2> ~ W E B S I T E S ~ </h2>
</center>

<dl>

<dt>
   <a href=http://janweb.icdi.wvu.edu/kinder/>1.  AMERICANS WITH DISABILITIES ACT DOCUMENT CENTER</a>
   <br>
   http://janweb.icdi.wvu.edu/kinder/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>Prepared by the great lakes disability and business technical
       assistance center, the ADA Document Center contains copies of
       the ADA statutes, regulations, and technical sheets that have
       been reviewed by either the Equal Employment Opportunity Center
       or the Department of Justice.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://starbase.neosoft.com/~currents/default.html>2.  CURRENTS: INTERNATIONAL TRADE LAW JOURNAL</a>
   <br>
   http://starbase.neosoft.com/~currents/default.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>Currents is a student-edited, practice-oriented international
       trade law journal published at South Texas College of Law, and
       is one of the two law journals in the United States that
       focuses exclusively on international trade.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://www.access.digex.net/~edlawinc/>3.  EDLAW HOMEPAGE</a>
   <br>
   http://www.access.digex.net/~edlawinc/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>In addition to the full texts of federal statutes and
       regulations governing provision of special education at
       elementary and secondary levels, this site contains analysis
       and comment on judicial decisions and federal policy on
       education law.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://epic.org/>4.  ELECTRONIC PRIVACY INFORMATION CENTER (EPIC)</a>
   <br>
   http://epic.org/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>This web site is dedicated to examining emerging privacy and
       civil liberties issues related to the development of the
       Internet. Epic provides current legislative proposals,
       analysis and statements, and related sources.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://w3.trib.com/FACT/>5.  FIRST AMENDMENT CYBER-TRIBUNE</a>
   <br>
   http://w3.trib.com/FACT/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>Operated by editor and columnist at the Casper (Wyoming) Star-
       Tribune, this relatively new page contains many links
       including lists of books that were challenged or banned in
       1994-1995, lists of organizations that are active in
       protecting first amendment liberties, first amendment web
       sites, summaries of Supreme Court decisions dealing with
       religious freedom, First Amendment quotes, and more...</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://www.undp.org/fwcw/daw1.htm>6.  FOURTH WORLD CONFERENCE ON WOMEN, BEIJING 1995</a>
   <br>
   http://www.undp.org/fwcw/daw1.htm
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>This is the Official United Nations WWW page of the Fourth
       World Conference on Women (FWCW) set up by the FWCW Secretariat
       with the technical support of the United Nations Development
       Programme (UNDP).  This Web site contains links to official
       documents, press releases, statements by governments,
       statements by the UN and Inter-governmental organizations,
       statements by non-governmental organizations, and a photo
       gallery.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://www.uspto.gov/web/ipnii/>7.  INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY & THE NATIONAL INFORMATION INFRASTRUCTURE REPORT</a>
   <br>
    http://www.uspto.gov/web/ipnii/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>Secretary of Commerce Ronald H. Brown, Chairman of the White
       House Information Infrastructure Task Force (IITF), has
       released a report on Intellectual Property & the National
       Information Infrastructure.  The Report, written by the IITF
       Working Group on Intellectual Property Rights and Trademarks
       Bruce A. Lehman, explains how intellectual property law
       applies to Cyberspace and makes legislative recommendations to
       Congress to prepare the law for the digital age.  </i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://www.ladas.com/ladasnews.html>8.  LADAS & PARRY NEWSLETTERS & SPECIAL INFORMATION BULLETINS</a>
   <br>
   http://www.ladas.com/ladasnews.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>This newsletter contains intellectual property matters from
       around the world.  In addition, there is a form to subscribe to
       the newsletter via conventional mail.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://www.lawjobs.com>9.  LAW EMPLOYMENT CENTER</a>
   <br>
   http://www.lawjobs.com
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>This free home page for law students, lawyers, and other legal
       job hunters is maintained by the publishers of the New York and
       National Law Journals and Law Journal Extra!.  It contains up-
       to-date, searchable employment listings.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://library.ljextra.com>10.  NATIONAL LAW JOURNAL AND LAW JOURNAL EXTRA! LAW LIBRARY</a>
   <br>
   http://library.ljextra.com
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From their announcement:  "The Law Library is designed to provide instant and easy access to thousands of research resources on the Internet.  Users can tap into information about The latest products and services for library professionals, browse a weekly update of new and noteworthy articles and books, explore the Law Library's Archive of publications, search the Publishers Catalog, read the most important mailing lists for lawlibrarians and other legal professionals (including the popular "Law-Lib," "Lawlibref," and "Int-law" listservs) and access other legal libraries and research sites on the World Wide Web."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://www.nrdc.org/nrdc>11.  NATURAL RESOURCES DEFENSE COUNCIL ONLINE</a>
   <br>
   http://www.nrdc.org/nrdc
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>NRDC Online is an environmental service from the Natural
       Resources Defense Council.  The site's primary materials
       include "State of Nature," a bulletin which focuses on
       environmental legislation; action guidelines; and findings on
       environmental subjects.  Other resources include descriptions
       of the federal budget process, statistics on public lands
       management, and "auto-mailers" for retrieving a variety of
       organizational ASCII publications.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://www.qrd.org/QRD/>12.  QRD (Lesbians, Gays, Bisexuals, and Transgendered Persons Website)</a>
   <br>
   http://www.qrd.org/QRD/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>This Internet resource includes national and international
       legal information concerning lesbians, gays, bisexuals,
       and transgendered persons.  Some of the links include
       information including case law, news, electronic mailing
       lists, directories, organizations, etc.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href=http://home.ptd.net/~sjrubin/pubutil.htm>13.  SCOTT RUBIN'S PUBLIC UTILITY HOME PAGE</a>
   <br>
   http://home.ptd.net/~sjrubin/pubutil.htm
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>This web site contains a summary of Internet resources,
       including links to electric utility information, natural gas
       utility information, telecommunications information, water
       utility information, environmental information, federal
       government information, state government information, federal
       & State government information, U.S. Census information,
       expert witness information, and more...</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   14.  STATE-SPECIFIC RESOURCES
   <br>
   <a href=http://www.touchngo.com/lglcntr/akstats/aac.htm>(1)  ALASKA ADMINISTRATIVE CODE</a>
   <br>
   http://www.touchngo.com/lglcntr/akstats/aac.htm
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>Contains the full text of current alaska regulations via
       keyword searching.</i>
</dd>
<br>
<dt>
    <a href=http://www1.usa1.com/~pcohen/aw.html>(2)  HYPERCONTRACT</a>
    <br>
    http://www1.usa1.com/~pcohen/aw.html
</dt>
<dd>
    <i>HyperContract is a hypertext book on disk for Massachusetts
       legal professionals and law students.  HyperContract covers
       contract law, uniform commercial code, remedies, evidence,
       consumer protection, civil protection, and more.</i>
</dd>
<br>
<dt>
    <a href=http://www.doas.state.ga.us>(3)  GEORGIA ONLINE NETWORK</a>
    <br>
    http://www.doas.state.ga.us
</dt>
<dd>
  <i>Maintained by the State of Georgia, Department
       of Administrative Services, this resource includes many links
       to other state web/Gopher sites.</i>
</dd>
</dl> 
 

<dl>
<dt>
   <a href=http://www.shef.ac.uk/uni/academic/I-M/law/library/virt.html>16.  UNIVERSITY OF SHEFFIELD'S VIRTUAL LAW LIBRARY</a>
   <br>
   http://www.shef.ac.uk/uni/academic/I-M/law/library/virt.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>Although this new virtual library concentrates mainly on
       English law, it contains many useful links to all fields of law
       and aspects of legal research.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
15.  U.S. COURT OF APPEALS FOR THE SECOND CIRCUIT
   <a href=http://www.law.pace.edu/legal/us-legal/judiciary/second-circuit.html>http://www.law.pace.edu/legal/us-legal.judiciary/second-circuit.html</a>
   <br>
   <a href=http://www.tourolaw.edu/2ndcircuit/>http://www.tourolaw.edu/2ndcircuit/</a>
   <br>
   http://www.law.pace.edu/second-circuit/second-circuit.html
   <br>
   http://www/tourolaw.edu/abouttlc/2ndcircuit/main.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>The Touro Law Center, with the Pace University School of Law,
       is now making Second circuit Court of Appeals opinions
       available via the WWW.  Currently, September and October 1995
       cases are available.</i>
</dd>

</dl>



<center>
<h2>~ L I S T S E R V S ~</h2>
</center>

<dl>

<dt>
   <b>1.  CCGROUP (constitutional law listserv)</b>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement: "This new group is for the discussion of
       all matters constitutional.  It is envisaged that, at least
       initially, the group will discuss matters arising from the
       South African Constitutional experience and the comparative
       and international issues that arise thanks to s.35(1) of the
       SA constitution..."  To subscribe:</i>
   <p>
   <i>Send email to: </i>majordomo@wwwserver.law.wits.ac.za<br>
   <i>With this message: </i>subscribe ccgroup
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <b>2.  CONTENTS ALERT ECONOMICS</b>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>Contents Alert Economics is a free E-mail service that sends
       subscribers the latest tables of contents of 33 economics
       journals from north-holland on a weekly basis.  To subscribe:</i>
   <p>
   <i>Send email to: </i>econbase-e@elsevier.nl<br>
   <i>With this message: </i>subscribe casecon-c
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <b>3.  ENVIROLAW</b>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>Envirolaw is an electronic discussion list for environmental
       and natural resource law students throughout the world.  To
       subscribe:</i>
   <p>
   <i>Send email to: </i>mailserv@oregon.uoregon.edu<br>
   <i>With this message: </i>subscribe envirolaw
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <b>4.  GAO DAYBOOK</b>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>The U.S. General Accounting Office now maintains a mailing
       list service for a daily electronic posting of the daily
       listing of released GAO reports and testimony.  To subscribe:</i>
   <p>
   <i>Send email to: </i>majordomo@www.gao.gov<br>
   <i>With this message: </i>subscribe daybook
</dd>

</dl>
      

<hr>

<i>Internet Update</i> is compiled by Leslie A. Lee, Reference Librarian at the Jacob Burns Law
Library, and is issued monthly as a service to the George Washington University Law School
community.

