<title>Internet Update #4</title>

<meta name="Author" content="GWULAW">
<meta name="CreatedBy" content="WP Internet Publisher 6.1">

<center>
<h3>THE GEORGE WASHINGTON UNIVERSITY LAW SCHOOL</h3>
<h3>JACOB BURNS LAW LIBRARY</h3>
<h3>INTERNET UPDATE #4</h3>
<h3>DECEMBER 1995</h3>
</center>

Welcome to the fourth issue of the <i>Internet Update</i>, a listing of new and noteworthy websites,
gopher sites, and listserv &amp; newsgroup information.
<p>

<h3>This issue includes the following websites:</h3>


<ol>
  <li>Administration on Aging</li>
  <li>Earth Negotiations Bulletin -- ENB</li>
  <li>Environmental Industry</li>
  <li>European Union Internet Resources</li>
  <li>European Union Bibliography</li>
  <li>EPA Region5</li>
  <li>GAO Online#</li>
  <li>Government Contractor Resource Center</li>
  <li>Harvard's JFK School of Government</li>
  <li>NAFTA Commission For Environmental Cooperation</li>
  <li>National Center For Research Resources (NCRR)</li>
  <li>PoliticsNow</li>
  <li>Project Vote Smart#</li>
  <li>RCRA Permit Policy Compendium</li>
  <li>Standard Industrial Classification (SIC) Codes</li>
  <li>U.S. News Online#</li>
</ol>

<h3>This issue contains the following listservs:</h3>

<ol>
  <li>DeathPenalty List</li>
  <li>GOVPUB -- New Discussion List</li>
</ol>
<p>

<center>
<h2> ~ W E B S I T E S ~ </h2>
</center>

<dl>
<dt>
   <a href="http://www.aoa.dhhs.gov/aoa.html">1.  ADMINISTRATION ON AGING</a>
   <br>
   http://www.aoa.dhhs.gov/aoa.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement:  "The Administration on Aging, U.S. Department of
Health and Human Services has a Web page.  It contains information about AOA
and its programs, information about resources for practitioners, statistical
information on the aging, and information for consumers (older persons and their
families) including how to obtain services and electronic booklets on aging related
issues.  It also includes a link to AOA's National Aging Information Center and
extensive links to other aging related Web resources."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.iisd.ca/linkages/">2.  EARTH NEGOTIATIONS BULLETIN</a>
   <br>
   http://www.iisd.ca/linkages/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement:  "The Earth Negotiations Bulletin is a Daily record of
environment and development negotiations at the United Nations.  Publication of
the bulletin began in 1992  during the Fourth Preparatory Conference meeting for
the United Nations Conference on Environment and Development (UNCED),
continued during the Rio summit, and subsequently was assumed by the
International Institute For Sustainable Development.  Both the daily bulletins
issued during the course of Negotiations and the summary issues prepared at  close
of the conference or meeting are available at this website as either ASCII or PDF
files."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.enviroindustry.com/">3.  ENVIRONMENTAL INDUSTRY</a>
   <br>
   http://www.enviroindustry.com/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement:  "Published by Home Page Associates, an independent
Internet marketing concern, the Environmental Industry Web Site is intended
primarily to facilitate business-to-business communication.  The website includes a
hot linked list of companies and organizations within the environmental industry,
both alphabetically and by type of activity.  Also available are calendars of
relevant upcoming events, business opportunities, a 'featured article of the month'
(this month's is on ISO 14000), and a substantial list of Internet resources for the
environmental industry."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.lib.berkeley.edu/GSSI/eu.html">4.  EUROPEAN UNION INTERNET RESOURCES</a>
   <br>
   http://www.lib.berkeley.edu/GSSI/eu.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>Contains links to Europa, the European Community Web Server, the European
Parliament, and CORDIS (providing access to information on EC-sponsored
scientific and technical research and development), as well as links to many EU
documents, including the 1996 Intergovernmental Conference, Copyright of
Programs in EC, the Summary of the Fourth Framework Programme, the Treaty on
European Union, the Treaty Establishing the European Community, and more.</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.lib.berkeley.edu/GSSI/eugde.html">5.  EUROPEAN UNION BIBLIOGRAPHY</a>
   <br>
   http://www.lib.berkeley.edu/GSSI/eugde.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement:  "The University of California, Berkeley has received EU
publications since 1952 and has been an official depository since 1964.  This guide
is intended to assist the user in locating information on the activities and policies
of the EU from its publications."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.epa.gov/Region5/home.html">6.  EPA REGION 5</a>
   <br>
   http://www.epa.gov/Region5/home.html
</dt>
   <i>From the announcement:  "The EPA's Region 5, encompassing Minnesota, Illinois,
Wisconsin, Michigan, Indiana, and Ohio, has just established a homepage.  The
Region 5 website provides topical information on 'protecting our air,' 'protecting
our land,' 'protecting our water,' and 'protecting human health.'  Press releases
from the region are also provided, as well as general information on how to
process a Freedom of Information Act (FOIA) request through Region 5, the
region's mission statement, and a list of publications.  A section called 'special
issues,' which is under construction, focuses on regional projects and initiatives
and currently provides data on the Brownfields Initiative and pollution
prevention."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.gao.gov">7.  GAO ONLINE</a>
   <br>
   http://www.gao.gov
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement:  "The U.S. General Accounting Office (GAO), the
congressional watchdog agency, now has a web page providing information on how
to search and retrieve the full text of GAO Reports, subscribe to a mailing list, and
access to other GAO Information.  For instructions on accessing GAO information
via email send mail to info@www.gao.gov."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.govcon.com/">8.  GOVERNMENT CONTRACTOR RESOURCE CENTER</a>
   <br>
   http://www.govcon.com/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement:  "This website dedicated to government contracting,
provides a wealth of resources for those involved in the procurement process. 
Many of the resources at the site are available to non-registered users; a short,
free registration, however, is required for access to more substantial resources
such as the Commerce Business Daily.  The offerings are provided in three
categories:  Current Business Opportunities, which includes access to the
Commerce Business Daily, teaming opportunities, mergers and acquisitions, and
employment postings; the Information Center, with pointers to federal agencies'
homepages, access to the Federal Acquisition Regulations (FAR) (also FIRMR and
DLAR), Cost Accounting Standards, lists of contracting officials, the U.S. Budget,
a guide to codes and acronyms, and other resources; and the Interactive Yellow
Pages, providing a directory of individuals and companies with expertise in
government contracting.  The website also maintains a 'What's New' section, a
means for contacting the webmasters via a form, and access to a searchable 8(a)
database.  Registered users of the website also receive a number of free email
services such as updates and newsletters."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://ksgwww.harvard.edu/~ksgpress/ksgnews.htm">9.  HARVARD'S JFK SCHOOL OF GOVERNMENT</a>
   <br>
   http://ksgwww.harvard.edu/~ksgpress/ksgnews.htm
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement:  "Harvard's John F. Kennedy School of Government
offers access to the best national and international resources for reporters at the
News Office's home page.  In addition to faculty sources, events, research and
publications, the news page links to the online Political Information Network
(OPIN) a well-developed set of links to most major sources of government and
political information available on the Internet [Click on Political/Govt
Information.]."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.cec.org/english/index.html">10.  NAFTA COMMISSION FOR ENVIRONMENTAL COOPERATION</a>
   <br>
   http://www.cec.org/english/index.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement:  "The Commission For Environmental Cooperation
(CEC) was established to ensure that protection of the environment remains a key
element in the implementation of the North American Free Trade Agreement
(NAFTA).  The CEC's Internet offerings currently include the full-text of the North
American Agreement on Environmental Cooperation; guidelines for citizen
submissions; the full-text of ECO REGION, the CEC newsletter; access to CEC
databases; and information on CEC procurement.  The site is under construction
but apparently intends to provide access to CEC publications and the CEC
Resource Center in the Future.  Under CEC Databases option, users will find the
'Summary of Environmental Law in North America,' a topical presentation of the
legal and regulatory framework for each signatory that includes provisions, laws,
policies, and issues, with appendices for legal instruments, acronyms, and a
bibliography."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.ncrr.nih.gov">11.  NATIONAL CENTER FOR RESEARCH RESOURCES (NCRR)</a>
   <br>
   http://www.ncrr.nih.gov
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement:  "The Web page of the National Center For Research
Resources (NCRR), a project of the National Institutes of Health, provides
information about their programs and how to access their research resources.  It
also includes several on-line directories to readily identify the array of biomedical
investigators across the country.  In addition, it provides links to the homepages of
many NCRR supported resources, which in turn, lead to other sources of valuable
information relevant to the biomedical research community."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.politicsnow.com/">12.  POLITICS-NOW</a>
   <br> 
   http://www.politicsnow.com/
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the website:  "PoliticsNow combines the two best political websites - ElectionLine and PoliticsUSA - to create the place for you to come to find out what is happening in politics and to make your voice heard online."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.vote-smart.org/campaign_96/presidential/pres96.html">13.  PROJECT VOTE SMART</a>
   <br>
   http://www.vote-smart.org/campaign_96/presidential/pres96.html
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement:  "Candidate information is provided for four Democrat,
four Libertarian, and thirteen Republican candidates.  Candidate information
includes bibliographies, contact information, and website information (when the
candidate has a website)."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.epa.gov/OSWRCRA/hazwaste/permit">14.  RCRA PERMIT POLICY COMPENDIUM</a>
   <br>
   http://www.epa.gov/OSWRCRA/hazwaste/permit
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement:  "The RCRA Permit Policy Compendium represents a
'13-volume set of reference docments for RCRA hazardous waste permitting
policies and procedures.'  The compendium gathers permitting policies and
procedures, a user's guide, a key Word Index, reference memoranda, letters, Office
of Solid Waste and Emergency Response (OSWER) Directives, and other
documents. Arrangement is chronological within subject categories.  The material
in the electronic compendium is current as of 1991.  The version available via the
Internet is for informational purposes only; official, signed copies of the
compendium are available through EPA regional libraries and state hazardous
waste program offices.  Information on the Permit Improvement Team and the
Public Participation and Permitting Proposed Rule is also available along with the
Compendium."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.gsionline.com/guide/APP_E.htm">15.  STANDARD INDUSTRIAL CLASSIFICATION (SIC) CODES</a>
   <br>
   http://www.gsionline.com/guide/APP_E.htm
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement:  "A list of four digit Standard Industrial Classification
(SIC) Codes is available via Global Securities Information's homepage.  The list is
presented both alphabetically by industry class and numerically by four-digit code. 
This is an ASCII text file, however, and is not searchable; finding the SIC code
desired requires scrolling through the list."</i>
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <a href="http://www.usnews.com">16.  U.S. NEWS ONLINE</a>
   <br>
   http://www.usnews.com
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement:  "U.S. News Online offers their weekly news magazine, as
well as daily news updates, photo essays, sound bites, and special features. 
Sections include:  NewsWatch, Washington Connection, Town Hall, News You Can
Use, College Fair and the Current Issue.  Special features include Election '96,
with election stories, photos, background information, and links to candidates'
websites.  People Power offers citizens a complete reference for finding their
congressional representatives, researching their financing histories, biographical
information, and ratings by special interest groups.  The interactive game Mind
Junket offers winners the chance to see Clinton morph into Newt Gingrich.  The
Clock Page lets visitors keep track of the National Debt, World Population, and
more."</i>
</dd>

</dl>


<center>
<h2> ~ L I S T S E R V S ~ </h2>
</center>

<dl>
<dt>
   <b>1.  DEATHPENALTY LIST</b
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement:  "This list is of interest to academics, professionals and students in the
following or related areas:  Administration of criminal justice, Criminal law, Constitutional law,
Bill of Rights jurisprudence, Legal practice, Law teaching, Criminal policy, Criminology,
Sociology, Penology, Politics, and Morality.  This list will offer a forum for scholarly and
professional discussion of issues related to the administration of capital punishment.  The
specific focus will be upon the administration of capital punishment in the US and on
developments in the US Supreme Court's Eighth Amendment jurisprudence.  This list will
welcome discussion of broader ethical and moral issues associated with capital punishment as
well as discussion of current cases, decisions and problems."  To subscribe:</i>

<p>

<i>send to:</i>  listserv@assocdir.wuacc.edu<br>
<i>with the message:</i>  subscribe deathpenalty &lt;your name, position, and institution&gt;
</dd>

<p>

<dt>
   <b>2.  GOV-PUB -- NEW DISCUSSION LIST</b>
</dt>
<dd>
   <i>From the announcement:  "This list provides a forum for government agency staff who are
responsible for the dissemination of government information online to exchange ideas and
information related to their efforts.  Both the technical and policy issues of government
information on the Internet are expected to be addressed; the list, however, is not intended to be
a vehicle for political discussion.  To subscribe:</i>

<p>

<i>send to:</i>  listserv@VM1.nodak.edu<br>
<i>with the message:  </i>subscribe govpub &lt;your name&gt;<p>
</dd>

</dl>


<hr>

<i>Internet Update</i> is compiled by Leslie A. Lee, Reference Librarian at the Jacob Burns Law
Library, and is issued monthly as a service to the George Washington University Law School
community.

