<html>
<head>
<title>Welcome</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<font face="HELVETICA,ARIAL" size=-1>


<h3>Welcome</h3>

The Dean Dinwoodey Center for Intellectual Property Studies and Freedom of Expression
sponsors frequent programs on policy matters that bring together leading academics, professors,
and jurists from all over the world.  The Center supports overseas studies by students at the
George Washington University Law School, particularly focusing on the Max Planck Institute
in Munich and Opportunities in Asia.  The Center sponsors a monograph series, the George
Washington Intellectual Property Studies.<p>

The Dinwoodey Center is named in honor of Dean Dinwoodey (J.D. '29), one of the founders
of the Bureau of National Affairs.  It is funded in substantial part by BNA in his memory.  The
Director of the Center, Professor Harold C. Wegner, also serves as Director of the Intellectual
Property Program of the George Washington University Law School.<p>

Other administrators of the Center are:<p>

     Jack Harlan Friedenthal, Dean<br>
     Roger Trangsrud, Associate Dean<br>
     Professor Jerome A. Barron, Lyle T. Alverson Professor of Law<br>
     Professor Thomas D. Morgan, Oppenheim Professor of Antitrust and Trade Regulation Law<br>



</font>
<p>
<img src="http://128.164.161.15/yline.gif" WIDTH=357 HEIGHT=13>
<p>
<A HREF="http://www.gwu.edu/"><img src="http://128.164.161.15/gwu-logo.gif" WIDTH=50 HEIGHT=50 border=0></A>
<A HREF="http://www.law.gwu.edu/"><img src="http://128.164.161.15/woodicon.gif" WIDTH=50 HEIGHT=50 border=0></A>
</body>
