   GW Law School SIPLA IP Lecture:  Federal Circuit Appeals
  </title>
 </head>
 <body bgcolor="#fff7d6" text="#00295a">
  <hr>
  <h1>
   <center>
    GW Law School 
   </center>
   <center>
    SIPLA
   </center>
   <center>
    IP Lecture: 
   </center> 
   <center>
    Federal Circuit Appeals
   </center>
  </h1>
  <hr>
  <p>
   Welcome to the
   <a 
    href="http://www.gwu.edu">
    GW
   </a>
   <a
    href="http://www.law.gwu.edu">
    Law School
   </a>
   SIPLA IP Lecture:  Federal Circuit Appeals Home Page!
  </p>
  <hr>
  <p>
   The GW Law School SIPLA invites you to attend the following IP Lecture:
  </p>
  <dl>
   <dt>
    <h3>
     Topic:
    </h3>
   </dt>
   <dd>
    <p>
     <h5>
      Federal Circuit Appeals
     </h5>
    </p>
   </dd>
   <dt>
    <h3>
     Speaker:
    </h3>
   </dt>
   <dd>
    <dl>
     <dt>
      <h5>
       Mr. Don Dunner
      </h5>
     </dt>
     <dd>
      <h5>
       Partner, Finnegan Henderson Farabow Garrett & Dunner
      </h5>
     </dd>
    </dl>
   </dd>
   <dt>
    <h3>
     Time:
    </h3>
   </dt>
   <dd>
    <h5>
     Wednesday, November 15, 1995 at 8:00 PM
    </h5>
   </dd>
   <dt>
    <h3>
     Location:
    </h3>
   </dt>
   <dd>
    <h5>
     The GW Law School Lerner Hall, Moot Court Room
    </h5>
   </dd>
   <dt>
    <h3>
     A Reception will follow in The GW Law School Stockton Hall, Faculty 
     Lounge.
    </h3>
   </dt>
  </dl>
