<html>
<head>
<title>
Keuka College: Special Education
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff text=000000 link=0000ff
alink=ff0000 vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+3><b>Special Education</b></font><br>
<font size=+2>at Keuka College</font><p>
<font size=+1>

<b>Major Briefs</b><br>
The special education program prepares teachers for "included," resource or self-contained classrooms at the pre-kindergarten, elementary and secondary school levels. The program addresses all areas of disability including:  students who are mentally disabled, learning disabled, emotional/behaviorally disabled, physically disabled and multiply disabled.
<p>
<b>Career Options</b><br>
In addition to special education teachers, graduates of Keuka's program are elementary and secondary education teachers, administrators and higher education faculty members and professionals. 
<p>
<b>Alumni Update</b><br>
More than 100 graduates are special education teachers!
<p>
<a href="./edcrs.html"><b>Course Descriptions</a>
<p>
<a href="./admifi.html">Admissions Information</a></B>
<hr><font size=+2>
<img src="greendot.gif"><a href="./dved.html">Return to the Education Division page</a><br>
<img src="greendot.gif"><a href="./index.html">Return to the Keuka College home page</a><br>
</font>
</body>
