</DOCHDR>
<html>
<head>
<title>
Keuka College: Elementary Education
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff text=000000 link=0000ff
alink=ff0000 vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+3><b>Elementary Education</b></font><br>
<font size=+2>at Keuka College</font><p>
<font size=+1>
<b>Major Briefs</b><br>
The elementary education certification program is based on three areas of study. The liberal arts core requirements of the College give the future teacher the broad base of knowledge necessary for elementary education teaching. The required liberal arts concentration provides in-depth study in one particular academic content field. The education requirements provide the necessary background knowledge in theory, history, psychology and foreign languages.
<p>
<b>Career Options</b><br>
In addition to elementary school teachers, graduates of Keuka's program are secondary and special education teachers, administrators and higher education faculty members and professionals. 
<p>
<b>Alumni Update</b><br>
Nearly 400 graduates are elementary education teachers!
<p>
