<title>
Keuka College: Mathematics
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff link=0000ff alink=ff0000 vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+3><b>Mathematics</b></font> <br>
<font size=+2>at Keuka College</font><p>
<font size=+1>
<b>Major Briefs</b><br>
This program covers analysis, algebra, geometry, statistics, service courses for majors in other divisions and courses for non-mathematics and non-science majors. 

<p>

<b>
Career Options</b><br>
A major in mathematics prepares the student for graduate study, for a career in secondary education teaching and for business careers.

<p>
<b>
<a href="bccrdr.html">Course Descriptions</a></b><p>

<b><a href="./admifi.html">Admissions Information</a></b></font>
<hr><font size=+2>
<img src="greendot.gif"><a href="./dvnsm.html">Return to the Division of Natural Science, Mathematics and Physical Education page</a><br>
<img src="greendot.gif"><a href="./index.html">Return to the Keuka College home page</a><br>
</font>
