<title>
Keuka College: Extracurricular Opportunities
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff Link=0000ff alink=ff0000 Vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+2>
Occupational Therapy <br></font>
<font size=+3>Extracurricular Opportunities</font>
<p><font size=+1>
<b>Organizations</b><br>
Professional student organizations are affiliated with the Occupational Therapy Division. Membership is optional and open to all interested students. The activities of these groups often reinforce classroom learning experiences while bringing together students with common career goals. 
<ul>
<li> OTTERS (Occupational Therapy Towards Excellence in Rahabilitation Services)
</ul>
The honorary societies at Keuka College recognize academic excellence and achievement as well as potential for success in specific career fields. Their activities are often instrumental in promoting student interest in particular fields of study. Each society maintains specific criteria for membership. 
<ul>
<li>  Pi Theta Epsilon 
</ul><b>
Student Activities</b><br>
Members of the OTTERS Club learned the value of community service last semester.  In October, they sponsored a car wash and donated the proceeds to the Yates County ARC.
<p>
In November 1996, Keuka students majoring in occupational therapy will attend the New York State Occupational Therapy conference in Rochester, NY.  Students will see the latest in technology, adaptive equipment and gain insight into their profession.


