<title>
Keuka College: Career Opportunities
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff Link=0000ff alink=ff0000 Vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+3>
Occupational Therapy <br></font>
<font size=+2>at Keuka College</font>
<p><font size=+1>
<b>Career Opportunities</b><br>
Currently, there is a national shortage of occupational therapists. 100 percent of Keuka's graduates are employed immediately upon completion of their degree requirements. Many work in school systems with children with learning disabilities or developmental disabilities. Rehabilitation of people of all ages with orthopedic or neurological deficits continues to present opportunities in hospitals, rehabilitation centers, nursing homes and home care. Many are working in the community with people who were previously institutionalized with psychiatric conditions or birth defects but now live in group homes or other community settings. Private practice is also emerging as an employment opportunity often with emphasis on hand therapy. 

<hr></font><font size=+2>
