<head>
<title>
Keuka College: Occupational Therapy Admissions
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff Link=0000ff alink=ff0000 Vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+2>
Occupational Therapy <br></font>
<font size=+3>Admissions</font>
<p><font size=+1>
Students accepted into Keuka College with the intended major of occupational therapy begin the occupational therapy course instruction when they meet the following requirements:
<ol>
<li>  An overall grade point average of at least 2.8

<li>  completion of all prerequisite and required support courses with no grade less than C-
</ol>
Students transferring into Keuka College must be accepted through the Admissions office and also meet the above occupational therapy requirements before they are accepted into the program. Intended transfer students must contact the Admissions office (1-800-33-KEUKA) regarding course transfer credit and availability for transfer students each year. 
<p>
Upon acceptance into the major students will be assigned an occupational therapy faculty member as their advisor. This advisor will guide students through the registration process each semester and in locating their clinical internships. 
<p>
<a href="admifi.html">Further Admissions Information</a>

