<html>
<head>
<title>
Admissions and Financial Aid
</title>
<body background="greenwhi.gif" bgcolor="ffffff" text=000000 link=0000ff vlink=006000>

<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+3>Keuka College<br>
Admissions & Financial Aid</font>
<p>
<font size=+1>
Keuka College welcomes applications from men and women who have a capacity for academic achievement and are responsive to the opportunities available to them. Admission is offered without regard to race, creed or national origin, and Keuka students represent diversified interests, goals and socioeconomic backgrounds. Applicants to the College are selected and evaluated individually on the basis of several factors. An application form, a secondary school transcript and results of the Scholastic Assessment Test (SAT I) of the College Board or of American College Testing's ACT Assessment are the basic credentials required for an admission decision. The academic record is the most important, and the challenge and appropriateness of the candidate's secondary school program are also considered.<p>
Application and Information
All applicants must submit the completed application and designated transcript and test scores. Students applying for admission by transfer from another college must present an official transcript of their academic record from the college or colleges previously attended. A transcript from the student's secondary school may also be requested prior to acceptance.<p>
Inquiries regarding academic programs, student aid or admission to Keuka College should be directed to:<p>
<address>
Dean of Admissions and Financial Aid<br>
Keuka College<br>
Keuka Park, NY 14478<br>
Telephone:  (315) 536-5254<br>
(800) 33-KEUKA (toll free)<br>
</font>
</address>
