<head>
<title>
Keuka College: Natural Sciences, Mathematics and Physical Education Division Briefs
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff Link=0000ff alink=ff0000 Vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+2>
Natural Sciences, Mathematics,<br> and Physical Education<br></font>
<font size=+3>
Division Briefs</font>
<p>
<li>The Division of Natural Science, Mathematics and Physical Education includes the disciplines of biology, chemistry, mathematics, medical technology, physical education and physics. The Division offers majors leading to the bachelor of arts degree in biochemistry, biology, biology 7-12, mathematics and mathematics 7-12. The bachelor of science degree is given in medical technology and clinical science.
<br>
<li>Students are individually assisted in the design of programs in pre-medical and other pre-professional areas. Keuka is affiliated with Clarkson University for a three-two program with a degree in mathematics from Keuka and engineering from Clarkson. Physics courses are offered as support courses for other science programs.
<br>
<li>The physical education academic curriculum expands the student's holistic knowledge of physical activities. Courses are selected each year according to the needs and interests of the majority of students. 
<br>
<li>60-65% of graduates go into advanced degree programs. 
<br>
<li>367 graduates shape our future as professors and peace corp volunteers, researchers and scientists, professors and business executives.

<hr></font><font size=+2>
<img src="greendot.gif"><a href="./dvnsm.html">Return to the Natural Sciences, Mathematics and Physical Education Division page</a><br>
<img src="greendot.gif"><a href="./index.html">Return to the Keuka College home page</a></font>
</body>
