<head>
<title>
Keuka College: Clinical Science
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff link=0000ff alink=ff0000 vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+3><b>Clinical Science</b></font> <br>
<font size=+2>at Keuka College</font><p>
<font size=+1>
<b>Major Briefs</b><br>
Keuka College and the New York Chiropractic College offer a program leading to a Bachelor of Science degree from Keuka College  and a Doctor of Chiropractic degree from New York Chiropractic College. The Clinical Science program provides entry into the New York Chiropractic College and grants the bachelor of science degree from Keuka College based on three years of satisfactory course completion at Keuka and transfer of first year clinical-type courses from the chiropractic college.
As students of the only New York State registered and approved joint degree program, Keukonians are assured a quality education. 
The joint degree program combines the student's fourth year of undergraduate study with the first year of graduate study. Students accelerate completion of a doctor of chiropractic degree by one year, shaving time and tuition from their expenses.
Successful completion of all preferred seating requirements guarantees students admission to New York Chiropractic College.
A second option for obtaining a Keuka degree is available if a student decides not to move into the chiropractic college.

<p>

<b>
Career Options</b><br>
A career in chiropractic can lead to opportunities in primary health care, sports medicine, rehabilitation and nutrition management. Chiropractic College graduates enjoy several career options:  starting their own practice; joining a practice; becoming a member of a multidisciplinary clinic or an HMO; becoming a teacher; or entering the research field. 

<p>
<b>
<a href="bccrdr.html">Course Descriptions</a></b><p>

<b><a href="./admifi.html">Admissions Information</a></b></font>
