<head>
<title>
Keuka College: Education Division Briefs
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff Link=0000ff alink=ff0000 Vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+2>
Education<br></font>
<font size=+3>
Division Briefs</font>
<p>
<li>Keuka's education programs educate profesional, knowledgeable and skilled classroom teachers for various grade levels and specialties. We offer a bachelor of science degree and provisional certification in elementary education and in special education. Students seeking provisional certification in secondary education complete both the requirements for a bachelor of arts degree in a discipline (biology, English, mathematics or social studies) and specific requirements in education. 
<li>
The education programs encompass the entire four-year college experience. Education courses on the methods of teaching specific areas build on College liberal arts core courses or major courses. All methods courses involve some experiential learning. In addition, all education students take one or more Field Periods in the major (elementary, secondary, special educaion). Our student teaching semester involves regular supervision and conferences with a member of the Keuka faculty. Students are encouraged to participate in professional activities on and off campus.
Keuka's Education Division is accredited by the New York State Department of Education. 
<li>
50-70% of graduates each year are hired for first-year employment positions. 
<li>
Nearly 1,200 graduates shape our future as professors and teachers, principals and administrators.
<hr></font><font size=+2>
<img src="greendot.gif"><a href="./dved.html">Return to the Education Division page</a><br>
<img src="greendot.gif"><a href="./index.html">Return to the Keuka College home page</a></font>
</body>
</html>
