<head>
<title>
Keuka College: Experiential Learning Opportunities
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff Link=0000ff alink=ff0000 Vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+2>
Education <br></font>
<font size=+3>
Experiential Learning Opportunities</font>
<p>
<center><b>From Student To Teacher in Eight Days</center></b>
<p>
Debra Rusinko, a graduate of the Class of 1995, breezed through her first day of teaching just eight days after graduating from Keuka. Thanks to the knowledge she gained through her Field Periods and special education classes, fresh-out-of-college Rusinko successfully taught in the Resource Room at Horseheads Elementary School without a hitch. 
<p>
"It was a great day," Rusinko said. "I worked with 19 fourth-, fifth- and sixth-graders on math and reading." 
<p>
Rusinko knew what to expect because of the solid background of work experiences she gained at Keuka. Through Keuka's Field Periods, Rusinko worked in three different classrooms while she was still a student. 
<p>
"My Field Periods were beneficial because I had a variety of placements. I learned a lot from observing teachers. I also knew how to help the children in the Resource Room because of techniques I had remembered from special education class discussions," Rusinko said.

<hr></font><font size=+2>
