<title>
Keuka College: Extracurricular Opportunities
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff Link=0000ff alink=ff0000 Vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+2>
Education<br></font>
<font size=+3>
Extracurricular Opportunities</font>
<p><font size=+1>
<b>Organizations</b><br>
Professional student organizations are affiliated with the Education Division. Membership is optional and open to all interested students. The activities of these groups often reinforce classroom learning experiences while bringing together students with common career goals. 
<ul>
<li>Education Club
<li>Council for Exceptional Children
</ul>
<b>Honorary Societies</b><br>
The honorary societies at Keuka College recognize academic excellence and achievement as well as potential for success in specific career fields. Their activities are often instrumental in promoting student interest in particular fields of study. Each society maintains specific criteria for membership. 
<ul>
<li>Frances H. Smith Education Honor Society
</ul>
<b>Recent Activities</b><br><ul>
<li>Members of the Education Club brought Joe Clark, the subject of the film "Lean on Me" to campus. Captivating more than 300 Keukonians and community members, the visionary and realist noted for turning around a crime-ridden, drug-infested inner city New Jersey high school spoke on education, discipline and the future. 
<li>
These club members and members of the Council for Exceptional Children participated in and organized a variety of holiday festivities for local children including a carnival-style Halloween party and Halloween dance.
</ul><hr></font><font size=+2>
