<title>
Keuka College: Secondary Education
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff text=000000 link=0000ff
alink=ff0000 vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+3><b>Secondary Education</b></font><br>
<font size=+2>at Keuka College</font><p>
<font size=+1>
<p>
<b>Major Briefs</b><br>
The secondary education program centers on the student's choice of discipline and emphasizes the teaching of that academic area in junior and senior high school. Graduates are eligible for provisional certification to teach in that discipline for grades 7-12.
<p>
<b>Career Options</b><br>
In addition to secondary school teachers, graduates of Keuka's program are elementary and special education teachers, administrators and higher education faculty members and professionals.
<p>
<b>Alumni Update</B><br>
More than 300 graduates are secondary education teachers!
<p>
