<head>
<title>
Experiential Education
</title>
<body background="greenwhi.gif" bgcolor="ffffff" text=000000 link=0000ff vlink=006500>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+3>Experiential Education<br>
At Keuka College</font><p><font size=+1>
Keuka students describe their College as an environment where classrooms have no back rows; where doing is as much a part of their learning process as listening or reading; and where the world and the classroom are closely integrated.<p>
Field Period, established in 1942, is central to Keuka's instructional climate. Every year, each student must complete a self-directed, self-initiated 3-credit hour learning experience. During the 4-5 week annual placements, students transform classroom theory into practical experience. They immerse themselves in new cultures and gain a realistic understanding of the real world as they test career choices and build a resume of experience.<p>
<hr></font>
<font size=+2>
<img src="greendot.gif">
<a href="./index.html"> Return to the Keuka College home page</a><p>
</font>
</body>
