<head>
<title>
Keuka College: Food, Hotel, and Resort Management
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff link=0000ff alink=ff0000 vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+3><b>Food, Hotel, and Resort Management</b></font> <br>
<font size=+2>at Keuka College</font><p>
<font size=+1>
<b>Major Briefs</b><br>
The food, hotel and resort management major develops leadership and management skills in the areas of hotel and restaurant operations, tourism planning and development, convention and conference planning and food and beverage management in a wide variety of environments. The program uses the Keuka Field Period and co-ops to provide a progression of off-campus experiential learning placement in the hospitality industry. Each student is given the opportunity to experience various fields of interest and develop the applied skills necessary for success in those fields. 
Between Field Periods and co-ops, you will have more than 1,000 hours of work experience before you graduate!
<p>

<b>
Career Options</b><br>
In addition to resort managers, graduates of Keuka's program can look forward to successful careers in hotel or motel management, food and beverage management, meeting and convention planning, resort management, or employment with cruise lines, casinos, spas, health clubs, country clubs and theme parks. 

<p> 
<b>
<a href="fhrcrdr.html">Course Descriptions</a></b><p>

<b><a href="./admifi.html">Admissions Information</a></b></font>
