<title>
Keuka College: Buisness and Management Faculty
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff Link=0000ff alink=ff0000 Vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+2>
Buisness & Management<br></font>
<font size=+3>
Faculty Profiles</font>
<p><font size=+2>
Associate Professors</font>
<p>
<b>Sharon R. Breitling </b><br>
Associate Professor of Management Information Systems (1983); B.A., Daemen College; M.A., Fordham University. Sharon will return to Keuka's classrooms this fall after a year-long sabbatical to Japan. She and her husband, William (listed below), taught U.S. military personnel on an Asian military base. 
<p>
<b>William Breitling</b><br>
Associate Professor of Management (1989); B.S., Fordham University; M.S., Boston College;  M.B.A., Rochester Institute of Technology. Bill serves on the College's faculty liaison committee and was instrumental in the development of a program that provides and markets a Keuka College Class Wine every year. 
<p>
<b>Joseph McCarthy</b><br>
Associate Professor of Management (1989); B.S., University of South Carolina; M.B.A., St. John Fisher College. Joe chairs the College's budget advisory committee and also assists in implementing transfer articulation agreements with area community colleges. He serves as the Division chair.McCarthy Financial Services is his own consulting company concentrating in nonprofit auditing, tax preparation and planning and financial planning. 
<p>
<b>David Romm</b><br>
Associate Professor of Management (1991); B.S., Princeton University; M.P.S., Cornell University. David teaches at Cornell University every summer. He trains business executives in services management. David and Scott Hamula (listed below) were instrumental in obtaining 2 grants totaling more than $12,000 from Direct Marketing Day. The New York City organization is dedicated to educating people in all phases of direct marketing.    
<p>
</font><p>
<font size=+2>Assistant Professors</font><p>
<b>Scott R. Hamula</b><br>
 Assistant Professor of Marketing (1994); B.A., SUNY Buffalo; M.B.A., University of Chicago. Scott comes to the classroom from the world of radio. His enthusiasm for broadcast not only adds to the educational experience, but also the extracurricular experience. He is the advisor for the campus radio club. 
<p>
<b>Craig Hovey</b><br>
Assistant Professor of Accounting and Economics (1994); B.A., Nazareth College of Rochester, B.S., SUNY Empire State College; M.S.W., SUNY Albany; C.P.A., C.M.A. Craig combines his passion for teaching with his writing talent. A chapter he wrote will enhance a new economics textbook. He also authored the workbook accompanying the text. 
<p>
<b>Gary M. Smith</b><br>
Assistant Professor of Food, Hotel and Resort Management (1994); B.S., Roberts Wesleyan College; M.B.A., SUNY Buffalo. Gary and David Romm (listed above) are faculty representatives for the College's strategic planning committee.  Gary brings to the classroom professional experiences gained from owning and operating Endless Adventures, an enterprise specializing in white water rafting, kayaking and outdoor adventures. 
