<html>
<head>
<title>
Keuka College: Social Work
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff link=0000ff alink=ff0000 vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+3><b>Social Work</b></font> <br>
<font size=+2>at Keuka College</font><p>
<font size=+1>
<b>Major Briefs</b><br>
The Keuka College BSW program is accredited by the Council on Social Work Education. Social work, as a helping profession, is concerned with how people address interpersonal and social problems and how they obtain the resources needed to live with dignity. The social worker is committed to making society more responsive to people's needs. Social work is a professional program of preparation for generalist social work practice. Keuka College offers a bachelor of science degree and combines an interdisciplinary liberal arts educational base with professional training and experience. Emphasis is placed on concepts, professional values and techniques in entry level generalist social work practice. 
<p>
Majors are expected to demonstrate competence in the cognitive and affective skills demanded for ethnic, sensitive, effective and generalist practice. Proficiency in Spanish or another modern language, computer science and economics is encouraged. Possession of a valid driver's license is recommended.
<p>
In addition, social work students receive ongoing feedback regarding their performance in meeting the knowledge, skills and value expectations of the profession. Finally, all social work students must be accepted into the major, complete the practicum readiness-assessment evaluation  and complete all necessary prerequisites for the major prior to enrollment in the Senior Practicum.

<p>

<b>
Career Options</b><br>
Career opportunities include direct service to individuals, families, small groups, organizations and community systems. Graduates of this program work in a variety of settings-youth agencies, family and child welfare services, correctional social services, developmental disabilities field, housing and urban development field, school social work, employment field, geriatric programs, hospitals, community action groups, crisis centers, mental health services, halfway houses and alcohol and drug treatment facilities. The program also provides preparation for graduate studies.

<p>
<b>
<a href="./soccrdr.html">Course Descriptions</a></b><p>

<b><a href="./admifi.html">Admissions Information</a></b></font>
