<title>
Latest News
</title>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" text=000000 link=0000ff vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+1> Keuka College </font>
<br>
<b><font size=+3> Latest News</font></b><br><p>
<br>

<hr>
<font size=+2><a href="./news/121096.html">Presidential Search Committee Appointed</a></font><p>
The Board of Trustees appointed a committee to conduct a search and recommend to the Board
of Trustees a candidate for the presidency of Keuka College. Members of the committee
represent alumni, faculty, students and Trustees. . .<p>
<font size=+2>
<hr>

<a href="./news/112696.html">Strong Appointed Interim President; Others Assume New Responsibilities</a>
</font><p>
The Keuka College Board of Trustees has appointed Frank P. Strong, Jr., Board of Trustees chair, as the College's interim president, effective January 1, 1997. Keuka President Arthur F. Kirk Jr. announced his resignation from the College last month, to assume the presidency of St. Leo College outside of Tampa, Fla.  Strong served as Keuka's acting president from February to August 1995 while Kirk completed a six-month sabbatical. . .  
<p><hr>
<font size=+2>
<a href="./news/kirk.html">Keuka College President Resigns Post</a>
</font><p>
Keuka College President Arthur F. Kirk Jr. has resigned as president of Keuka College to accept the presidency of Saint Leo College outside of Tampa, Fla., effective January 1, 1997. In November, the Keuka College Board of Trustees will retain a search firm to help in the selection of a new president for Keuka College. . .

