<html>
<head>
<title>
Keuka College: Business and Management Division Briefs
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff Link=0000ff alink=ff0000 Vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+2>
Business and Management<br></font>
<font size=+3>
Division Briefs</font>
<p>

<li>The Division of Business and Management prepares its students for success in a wide range of business environments or graduate school. Each major in the program provides a solid foundation in management, computer systems, accounting, human resources, financial analysis, marketing and strategic planning. Our aim is to provide students with marketable skills that make their transition into the "real world" as efficient and successful as possible. Field Periods add particular value to the Business and Management graduate by integrating four hands-on work experiences into their educational development. Students put into practice what they have learned in the classroom while they create a network of useful contacts. 

<li>For students considering advanced degrees, Keuka College is developing special relationships with graduate schools. An agreement already in place with Clarkson University allows graduates from the Management program to earn a Clarkson M.B.A. with just one year of additional study. Similar relationships with other schools are in process. 

<li>More than 10 percent of Keuka's student body are enrolled in the Division of Business of Management. 

<li>574 graduates shape our future as accountants, resort managers, caterers, human resource managers and marketing professionals.  

<hr></font><font size=+2>
<img src="greendot.gif"><a href="./dvbuma.html">Return to the Business and Management Division page</a><br>
<img src="greendot.gif"><a href="./index.html">Return to the Keuka College home page</a></font>
</body>
</html>
