<title>
Keuka College: Spanish and Area Studies Courses
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff link=0000ff alinf=ff0000 vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+3>
Spanish and Area Studies</font><br>
<font size=+2>Course Descriptions</font><p><hr size=8>
<font size=+2>French</font><hr>
FRE 101 Introduction to French<br>
French through the four basic skills: understanding, speaking, writing, and reading. Emphasis on usage. (Offered every fall semester) 	(3)
<hr>
FRE 102 Continuing Introductory French<br>
Prerequisite: FRE 101 or two years of high school French, or equivalent with consent of instructor. Continuing development of four skills: understanding, speaking, writing and reading. Emphasis on usage. (Offered every spring semester)				(3)
<hr>
FRE 103 Conversation<br>
Prerequisite: FRE 102 or two or three years of high school French, or equivalent, with consent of instructor. Intermediate level course emphasizing systematic development in French conversation; study of structure as needed. (Offered as needed)						(3)
<hr>
FRE 104 Topics and Issues in a French Speaking World<br>
Prerequisite: FRE 102 or two to three years of high school French, or equivalent, with consent of instructor. Intermediate level course emphasizing development of writing, reading and conversation, through exploration of social, cultural and political issues in the French-speaking world; study of grammatical structure as necessary. (Offered as needed)			(3)
<hr>
FRE 295 Introductory Topics in French<br>
Prerequisites: to be determined by the Division of Humanities and Fine Arts. An introductory study of a specific topic within French. Intended for freshmen and sophomores, or for students with little or no background in French. The student may repeat the course, but not the topic. (Offered as needed)			(1-3)
<hr>
FRE 399 Independent Study<br>
Prerequisite: consent of instructor. (Offered every semester)				(1-3)
<hr size=8>
<font size=+2>Spanish</font><hr>
SPA 101 Introduction to Spanish<br>
An introductory course with emphasis on conversational skills. Basic structures, pronunciation, vocabulary and use of audio materials. (Offered every fall semester)	(3);
<hr>
SPA 102 Continuing Introduction to Spanish<br>
Prerequisites: SPA 101 or one-to-two years of high school Spanish with consent of instructor.   Development of skills in understanding, speaking, reading and writing. Culturally oriented readings and use of audio materials. (Offered every spring semester)			 	(3);
<hr>
SPA 103 Spanish for Communication<br>
Prerequisites: SPA 102 or two years of high school Spanish. Further development of basic concepts and systematic cultivation of conversational skills. Practice of grammatical structures as necessary.  (Offered every even fall semester)				(3);
<hr>
SPA 104 Conversation and Composition<br>
Prerequisites: SPA 103 or three years of high school Spanish. Refinement of language skills, oral and written discussions, development of vocabulary. (Offered every odd spring semester);
(3);
<hr>
SPA 108 Spanish for the Professions<br>
Prerequisites: SPA 103 or three years of high school Spanish. Situational conversational vocabulary and written forms of communication oriented to achieving communicative proficiency in professional life. Alternatively focused to meet needs of business, health and social work professions. Emphasis on development of intercultural sensitivity. (Offered as needed)	 					(3);
<hr>
SPA 201 Latin American Short Story<br>
Prerequisite: SPA 103. Survey in Spanish of major Latin American short story writers such as Borges, Rulfo, Garcia Marquez and Quiroga, emphasizing contemporary contributions. (Offered as needed)			(3);
<hr>
SPA 202 Selected Topics in Hispanic Literature<br>
Prerequisite: SPA 104. Topics in Peninsular or Latin American literature, including theatre, poetry, novel and short story. This course can be taken more than once for credit if the topic is different. (Offered as needed)		(3);
<hr>
SPA 211 Culture and Civilization of Latin America<br>
Prerequisites: SPA 103 or three years of high school Spanish. A survey of the arts, history and diverse regions of Latin America from pre-Columbian times to the present. (Offered every odd fall semester)			(3);
<hr>
SPA 212 Culture and Civilization of Spain<br>
Prerequisites: SPA 103 or three years of high school Spanish. A survey of the arts, history and diverse regions of Spain from the Middle Ages to the present. (Offered every even spring semester)						(3);
<hr>
SPA 295 Introductory Topics in Spanish<br>
Prerequisites: to be determined by the Division of Humanities and Fine Arts. An introductory study of a specific topic within Spanish. Intended for freshmen and sophomores, or for students with little or no background in Spanish. The student may repeat the course, but not the topic. (Offered as needed)			(1-3);
<hr>
SPA 399 Independent Study<br>
Prerequisite: consent of instructor. (Offered every semester)				(1-3);
<hr>
