<title>
Keuka College: Experiential Learning Opportunities
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff Link=0000ff alink=ff0000 Vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+2>
Basic and Applied Social Sciences  <br></font>
<font size=+3>
Experiential Learning Opportunities</font>
<p><font size=+2><hr><center>
 </center></font>
As a group field period, students traveled to Costa Rica where they participated in a variety of hands-on experiences. They helped with the construction of a "hogar de paso," a "home for those passing through in the Methodist Church of Ciudad Quesada. The home would provide outpatient hospital services for Costa Ricans and Nicaraguans who could not afford lodging. Students had the opportunity to learn more about the lives and work of common Costa Ricans, as well as the role of the church and it service in that community.

<hr></font><font size=+2>
