<head>
<title>
Keuka College: Accounting
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff link=0000ff alink=ff0000 vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+3><b>Accounting</b></font> <br>
<font size=+2>at Keuka College</font><p>
<font size=+1>
<b>Major Briefs</b><br>
The accounting major provides a career-oriented educational opportunity with a firm foundation in the liberal arts and a current body of knowledge in business and economics. The major offers the necessary preparation for a wide range of business and accounting environments or for admission into graduate school. The program is registered with the Division of Professional Education of the New York State Department of Education, and graduates meet the requirements for admission to the CPA and CMA exams.
Accounting, a concentration in the Division since before 1988,  was approved by the Department of Education as a major in 1994. The first students enrolled in the Fall 1995. Certifications are available as certified public accountants, certified management accountants, certified internal auditors and certified financial analysts. 
Keuka has 20 accounting majors. 
<p>

<b>
Career Options</b><br>
In addition to corporate accounting, graduates of Keuka's program can look forward to 
successful careers as financial accountants, cost accountants, internal or external auditors or tax accountants.
<p>
<b>
<a href="accrdr.html">Course Descriptions</a></b><p>

