<title>
Keuka At a Glance
</title>
<body background="greenwhi.gif" bgcolor="ffffff" text=000000 link=0000ff vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+3>Keuka College<br>
At a Glance</font><p>


<font size=+1>
Founded in 1890, this four year, private college has doubled enrollment 
during the last 10 years.
On the shore of Keuka Lake, the 173-acre campus is in Penn Yan, N.Y.,  
recently ranked as one
of the top 100 best small towns in America!
<BR>
Keuka College is known for its intensely personal campus atmosphere, 
excellent and accessible
faculty members, affordability and leadership opportunities. It is 
renowned for <a href="./exped.html">Field Period</a>.
Challenging, life-defining opportunities, Field Periods allow Keukonians 
to learn while doing and
transform classroom theory into practical experience. The self-directed, 
3 credit hour Field
Periods are required each year and give the professional edge to Keuka 
graduates.<BR><BR>
