<head>
<title>
Keuka College: Organizational Communication
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff link=0000ff alink=ff0000 vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+3><b>Organizational <br>Communication</b></font> <br>
<font size=+2>at Keuka College</font><p>
<font size=+1>
<b>Major Briefs</b><br>
Keuka College's organizational communication major provides a career-oriented educational opportunity. Grounded in the liberal arts, the program offers a strong background in the cultural, historical and aesthetic dimensions of English language and literature. The program emphasizes theory and practice in communication and business. Students majoring in organizational communication develop teamwork and leadership skills, an understanding of the English language as a way of communicating and comprehension of current business and marketing principles. 
<p>
The program's emphasis on experiential learning and the required senior practicum give graduates the head start they need for success in a highly-competitive job market.
<p>
Keuka offers organizational communication as a major or minor program.   


<p>


<b>
Career Options</b><br>
The major prepares students for employment in a wide range of communication positions in the corporate and nonprofit sectors and for admission to graduate programs. 

<p>
<b>
<a href="occrdr.html">Course Descriptions</a></b><p>

<b><a href="./admifi.html">Admissions Information</a></b></font>
