<head>
<title>
Keuka College: Humanities and Fine Arts Division Briefs
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff Link=0000ff alink=ff0000 Vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+2>
Humanities and Fine Arts<br></font>
<font size=+3>
Division Briefs</font><p>
The humanities: English, modern languages, organizational communication, philosophy and religion, explore those enduring values of our heritage that have sustained and enriched human life in times of crises and doubt, prosperity and peace. Firmly rooted in human experience, the humanities examine, define and relate that experience to the contemporary age. Humanities involve the individual in the varied experiences of life. Course work in the humanities encourages students to express their individual ideas and personalities and to determine how they may succeed creatively in their chosen careers. 
<p>
The fine arts: art, dance, music and theater, emphasize the role of creativity in our lives. Course work in art, music, dance and theater gives students the opportunity to explore the varied ways in which individuals express themselves artistically. Courses offer historical and theoretical perspectives, as well as practice in artistic techniques and training in particular disciplines, giving students an appreciation of aesthetics. 
<p>
The Division of Humanities and Fine Arts offers a major in English with options for concentrations in writing/communication and creative writing and in organizational communication, as well as minor programs in art, creative writing, English, organizational communication and Spanish. Students also may receive certification to teach English in grades 7-12 by completing the requirements for teacher certification. 
<hr></font><font size=+2>
<img src="greendot.gif"><a href="./dvhumfa.html">Return to the Humanities and Fine Arts Division page</a><br>
<img src="greendot.gif"><a href="./index.html">Return to the Keuka College home page</a></font>
</body>
</html>
