<title>
Keuka College: Extracurricular Opportunities
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff Link=0000ff alink=ff0000 Vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+2>
Nursing <br></font>
<font size=+3>Extracurricular Opportunities</font>
<p>
<b>Organizations</b><br>
Professional student organizations are affiliated with the Nursing Division. Membership is optional and open to all interested students. The activities of these groups often reinforce classroom learning experiences while bringing together students with common career goals. 

<ul><li>  Nursing students can elect to become involved with the Keuka College Student Nurses Association. This organization offers students opportunities to develop professional social skills for advancing the concept of nursing in the community. 
</ul>
<b>Recent Activities</b><br>
Senior nursing students consulted for deputies in the Yates County Sheriff's Office this past year. The students provided individualized information on nutrition, exercise, fitness strategies and stress management. 
<p>
Members of Keuka's Student Nurses Association showed their community spirit and educated parade spectators by entering a hand-decorated float depicting a variety of nursing roles in Penn Yan's Buckwheat Harvest Festival Parade. 
<p>
These same students sponsor annual health fairs in the Penn Yan and surrounding areas in order to advance general concepts of wellness and health practices for residents in the area.  The series incorporates general messages of wellness and health teaching. 
<p>
Interests in international health care led two Keukonians abroad for Field Periods. In-depth studies uncovered the role of the Austrian nurse and Austria's health care system and nursing theories learned from a well-known nursing theorist in Japan. 


