<title>
Keuka College: Extracurricular Opportunities
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff Link=0000ff alink=ff0000 Vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+2>
Humanities and Fine Arts<br></font>
<font size=+3>
Extracurricular Opportunities</font>
<p>
Students who want exposure in journalism, creative writing, graphics and photography can gain valuable entry level skills in the following organizations. 
<ul>
<li> Keukonian (student-run, student-produced newspaper)
<li>  Kiondaga (student-run, student produced yearbook)
<li>  Red Jacket (literary magazine published by English majors)
</ul>
The honorary societies at Keuka College recognize academic excellence and achievement as well as potential for success in specific career fields. Their activities are often instrumental in promoting student interest in particular fields of study. Each society maintains specific criteria for membership.
<ul>
<li>  Alpha Mu Gamma (foreign language)
<li>  Sigma Tau Delta (senior English majors)
</ul>
Many opportunities for performing are available through various fine arts programs. The following organizations offer opportunities to participate in concerts and musical productions, dance performances, choreography, acting, directing, staging and lighting. Membership is generally determined by auditions. 
<ul>
<li>  Keuka College Dance Classes
<li>  Private voice lessons
<li>  Private piano lessons
</ul>
Students practice conversational Spanish weekly during "La Mesa," an informal Spanish language table led by Michaela Cosgrove, assistant professor of Spanish. 

