<html>
<head>
<title>
Keuka College: Criminal Justice/Criminology
</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=ffffff link=0000ff alink=ff0000 vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+3><b>Criminal Justice/
 Criminology</b></font> <br>
<font size=+2>at Keuka College</font><p>
<font size=+1>
<b>Major Briefs</b><br>
This program combines a nucleus of criminology/criminal justice knowledge with the enlightenment of the liberal arts.  It aspires to use knowledge from the social sciences to improve our quality and security of life.
<p>
Students are prepared for work in areas related to criminal justice, and provided with a strong background in social issues and a sensitive understanding of human problems.  
<p>
The major includes criminology (the study of crime and criminal behavior) as well as criminal justice (the system that deals with criminals), in addition to options in criminalistics (forensic science),  Relevant courses in sociology, psychology, political science/law, and statistics are also required.  To compliment theoretical components, there is an extensive experiential component consisting of two criminology/criminal justice Field Periods and a one-semester internship in the senior year.

<p>

<b>
Career Options</b><br>
Graduates may seek entry into a variety of related fields including probation, juvenile services, law enforcement, corrections, para-legal activities, community action groups, private security, and research.

<p>
