<html>
<head>
<title>
Latest News
</title>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" text=000000 link=0000ff vlink=006000>
<img align=right src="coltop2.gif">
<font size=+1> Keuka College </font>
<br>
<b><font size=+3> Latest News</font></b><br><p>
<br>
<p><hr>
<font size=+2>
Keuka College President Resigns Post
</font><p>
Keuka College President Arthur F. Kirk Jr. has resigned as president of Keuka College to accept the presidency of Saint Leo College outside of Tampa, Fla., effective January 1, 1997. In November, the Keuka College Board of Trustees will retain a search firm to help in the selection of a new president for Keuka College. 
<p>
Kirk leaves at a time when Keuka College is experiencing record growth, Chairman of the Board Frank P. Strong, Jr. said. Keuka's student body has more than doubled in the last 10 years. Students bring with them superior academic talents, boasting SAT scores above the national average. The College's endowment has skyrocketed, increasing eleven-fold. Millions of dollars of campus-wide renovations have rejuvenated the College's physical plant, modernizing facilities, providing handicapped accessibility and restoring Keuka's campus. For the first time in nearly 20 years, all of the College's facilities are in use for their intended purposes.
<p>
This growth, prosperity and stability follow on the heels of successful execution of the IDEAL 2000, the College's strategic plan. 
<p>
Keuka's success is due, in part, to the multi-year strategic plan, the IDEAL 2000, Strong said. The College has a plan and works that plan effectively. The Board of Trustees expects that the IDEAL 2000 will catapult the College well into the 21st century, establishing Keuka as a model in academic excellence and experiential learning. But the College's success is also due in large measure to the leadership and vision of Arthur Kirk. His insight, guidance and strategic planning abilities have guided Keuka for more than a decade. The College is fortunate that his wisdom and vision, his legacy, has permeated every aspect of the College.
<p>
It has been an honor and a privilege to lead Keuka College, Kirk said. Keuka continues to educate more students and educate them better, preparing them for a life of service to their communities, their professions and themselves. 
<p>
Accepting the presidency of St. Leo's College was one of the most difficult decisions I have made in my professional career. It was possible only because I am confident that Keukonians are united by the College's mission and vision and guided by a strong strategic plan that produces remarkable accomplishments year in and year out.
<p>
The IDEAL 2000 was implemented in the Spring 1994. Guided by a vision of the ideal Keuka for the 21st century, the strategic plan focuses on dynamic key result areas and is a process of continuous improvement. The plan is systematically renewed biannually and extends what is and has been the best of Keuka, allowing the College to realize its true potential. 
<p>
The IDEAL 2000 builds on the College's core strengths and charts a new course for Keuka, Marilyn Baader, a member of the Class of 1963 and Board of Trustees vice chair, said. It establishes this College as one of a handful of colleges in America with a comprehensive program to demonstrate the value of its educational experience, using the results to improve student learning. Keuka's integrated use of experience as a teacher and the synergistic interweaving of academic and student life programs into a seamless educational experience create a national model for educating students for a lifetime of learning.
<hr>
<br>
