<h1><a href="http://www.tut.fi/ttkk.koti/index_en.html"><img src="http://www.tut.fi/ttkk.koti/pics/pal28ken.gif" alt="TUT" align="middle"></h1></a>

<!---------------------------------------------------------------------->
<a href="alku"></a>

<img src="http://www.tut.fi/images/ttkk300.gif" lowsrc="http://www.tut.fi/image
s/ttkk_int.gif ALT="TTKK kampus" ALIGN="left" WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=150 HSPACE=20 VS
PACE=20>
<br>


<h1><a href="http://www.uta.fi/cgi-bin/hervanta-zoom?217,172">Tampere University of Technology</h1></a>   is located in <a href="#hervanta">Hervanta</a>, approximately 7 km from downtown <a href="#city">Tampere</a>, the third-largest city in <a href="#finland">Finland</a>. 

<p>
<hr>







<!---------------------------------------------------------------------->

<a name="city"></a><p>
<h2>TAMPERE</h2>
<a href="http://www.uta.fi/cgi-bin/yleiskartta-loc?379,249,TTKK">The map of Tampere</a>
<p>

<a href="http://www.tampere.fi/english.htm">Overview of the city</a>
<p>

Founded in the year 1779 on the banks of the Tammerkoski rapids, about 170 km up north from
Helsinki, the city of Tampere is today a vigorous center of the greater economic area of Tampere
region with a total population of 400 000. Tampere combines material and intellectual resources
with impressive natural beauty in a most dynamic way. Tampere is the third-largest city in  and the largest inland city in Scandinavia, with its population of 170 000. Tampere is the major
industrial, marketing, and communication center for all of South-Central Finland and also a clean
and vibrant cultural center, located between two large lakes, Lake Pyh&auml;j&auml;rvi and Lake N&auml;sij&auml;rvi. <p>

<p>

The city's festival year begins with the Tampere film festival, which brings the world's best short
films to the silver screen. There are many cinemas in town which present a variety of films all
through the year. Tampere has two theatres, Tampereen Teatteri and Ty&ouml;v&auml;enteatteri where plays
and musicals are staged throughout the year. Tampere Jazz Happening and Tampere Illuminations
are held every autumn. In the summertime there is an open-air theatre at a beautifull site at the
Pyynikki-hill. <p>

<p>

In S&auml;rk&auml;nniemi recreation area you can find an amusement park, dolphinarium, aquarium,
planetarium, small children's zoo and Sara Hild&eacute;n art museum.<p>

There are excellent indoor and outdoor sports-facilities in Tampere and surrounding areas.<p>

<p>

<p>

<h3>Travel information</h3>
<p>

If flying to Helsinki on Finnair, you are eligible to get the connecting flight to Tampere free of
charge if you have requested this before your ticket has been written. This is not available on
charter or discount flights.<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

From Helsinki to Tampere you can connect by plane, train or bus. The bus is the most convenient,
since there are direct buses (e.g.the bus company called "Paunu") from Helsinki airport to
Tampere almost every hour. The ride takes less than 3 hours.<p>

<a href="http://www.tut.fi/ttkk.koti/aikataulut.html">Timetables</a><p>

You can also take the Finnair bus from the airport directly to the railway station in Helsinki and
then the train to Tampere. Trains run nearly every hour during the daytime. If arriving in Finland
by boat, direct train service is available from both Helsinki and Turku (In Swedisth &Aring;BO !!). The
cost is less than FIM 100 one-way. The ride takes about two hours from both cities.<p>

<p>
<a href="#alku"><img src="http://www.adm.tut.fi/images/back1.gif"></a>
<hr>


<!---------------------------------------------------------------------->

<a name="hervanta"></a><p>

<a href="http://www.uta.fi/cgi-bin/hervanta-location?209,171,TTKK"><h2>HERVANTA</h2></a>
<p>

<a name="TUT"></a><p>

Hervanta is a small community with vibrant activities. There is a free time activity centre, church,
swimming hall, tennis, badminton and squash courts. Just outside the centre there is a fabulous
nature waiting for joggers, skiers and bikers who enjoy fresh air and outdoor sports.  <p>

Hervanta provides all needed services: shops, post-office, banks, pharmacy, health care centre,
liquer store, restaurants, cinema etc.<p>

<i><p>

How to get to TUT in Hervanta</i><p>

<p>

In Tampere, city 
<a href="gopher://butler.cc.tut.fi:70/11/Valitut%20palat/Valitut%20aikata
ulut%20%28bussit%206%2C20%2C23%2C30%29">buses</a>  no. 23 and 30 run every 15 minutes from Keskustori, Central Square, to Hervanta suburb. The bus fare is FIM 9 and takes about 20 minutes. By taxi the trip from the city
centre costs about FIM 80 and takes about 10 minutes.<p>

<p>
<a href="#alku"><img src="http://www.adm.tut.fi/images/back1.gif"></a>
<hr>

<a name="finland"></a>
<h2>Finland</a></h2>

<!---------------------------------------------------------------------->
<a href="http://www.tpo.fi/gif/finland.gif"> The map of  Finland</a>. <br>
<a href="http://www.vn.fi/vn/um/">Virtual Finland </a><p>


Finland is the fifth largest country in Europe in terms of area. Of the total land area 70 % is
covered by forests. Finland is also famous for its 188 000 lakes and the 30 000 islands dotting its
coastline of 1 100 kilometres. The population is about 5 million. After Iceland and Norway,
Finland is the most sparsely populated country in Europe with 16 inhabitants perkm2.<p>

<p>

Finland has a mild continental climate and it is more favored than most countries at similar
latitudes because of the warming influence of the Gulf Stream. Winters in Tampere are rather
cold, with some snow. Summers are usually relatively warm. In fall and spring there is occasional
rain. Average temperature in Tampere in winter is about -5C and in summer about +15C. <p>

<p>

The short but spectacular spring and autumn seasons help to counterbalance the effect of the
winter. During the summer it never gets completely dark, and in the north sthe sun does not set at
all for some time. During the darkest weeks of winter there are six hours of full day-light. <p>

<p>

Since the weather is very cold in winter you should bring supplies of warm clothing such as coats,
hats, sweaters, warm socks, long underwear, etc. You will also need at least onepair of sturdy,
comfortable and warm boots or walking shoes as well as casual shoes. There are good
opportunities for winter sports so if you ice-skate, play ice hockey of ski cross-country, you may
wish to bring your equipment along.<p>

<p>

<a href="#alku"><img src="http://www.adm.tut.fi/images/back1.gif"></a>
<hr>
