<HTML>
<title>The fields of engineering and architecture in TUT</title> 
<center>
<A HREF="/ttkk.koti/index_en.html"> <img src="/ttkk.koti/pics/pal28ken.gif" alt="Tampere University of Technology" border=0></a>
</center>
<H1>TUT in general</H1>
<P>
<B>TUT offers enterprises a wide diversity of research, product-development and consulting 
services.</B><P><B>
</B>The University  is responsible for scientific research, education in engineering and architecture 
based on this research, and the taining of researchers in the fields of engineering and architecture.<P>
Tampere University of Technology has grown rapidly  since it was founded in 1965. The student body 
numbers ca. 7000. In addition to basic-degree students, there are 800 postgraduate students at the 
University.  To date a total of over 5300 engineers and architects have qualified here. The University 
has over 900 staff members. <P>
Students may choose between 10 distinct degree programs, which are:<P>
  - Architecture<P>
  - Automation<P>
  - Civil Engineering<P>
  - Information Technology <P>
  - Electrical Engineering<P>
  - Environmental Engineering<P>
  - Fiber, Textile, and Clothing Science<P>
  - Industrial Management and Engineering<P>
  - Materials  Engineering<P>
  - Mechanical Engineering<P>
<A HREF = "http://www.tut.fi/ttkk.koti/units.html">Departments and Institutions  in TUT</A> <P>
English has already been  introduced as the language of tuition in Signal Processing, Materials 
Engineering, and Biomedical Engineering and is due to be introduced in Architecture, Environmental 
Engineering, and Mechanical Engineering. In addition to agreements inside the Nordic Countries, 
there are also cooperation and axhange agreements with ca. 30 foreign univerisities.<P>
<P>
<H3>Close Involment with Industrial and Commercial 
World</H3>
Right from the outset the University has emphasized the value of  good  relations with industrial and  
commercial life.  The Universitys<B> </B> expertise and equipment have been utilized by 
enterprises, e.g. in their product development. The University has also provided access for enterprises 
to national and international research cooperation.<P>
The Universitys institutes are active in e.g. many research programs financed by the EU, such as 
COST, ESPRIT, RACE, EUREKA, and COMET II.<P>
<H3>Center of Knowledge and Skill</H3>
Technology results are often the fruit of combining results from many disciplines. The University is 
able to link up expertise in different areas of engineering in a flexible manner. Tampere Tecnology 
Centre, Hermia , with its various enterprises, together with the Tampere laboratories of the Technical 
Research Center of Finland (VTT), are both neighbors and partners of the University. <P>
<P>
<P>
<P><B>
</B><P>
<P>
