<!-- toinen sarake, johon tulee varsinainen leipateksti, leveytta ei ole asetettu -->
<TD VALIGN=TOP>
<!-- sisennysta varten tarvitaan DefinitionList -->
<DL>
<!-- uusi kappale aloitetaan P-DT yhdistelmalla -->
<P><DT>
<!-- Otsikoiden fontiksi arial/helvetica, koska se nayttaa paremmalta -->
<!-- Huomaa myos englanninkielelle tyypillinen otsikoiden capitalisointi -->
<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H1>General Information</H1></FONT>
<!-- sisennys tapahtuu DD-tagilla -->
<DD>
<UL type=disk>
<LI><A HREF="overview.htm">Information about Tampere University of         Technology</A>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="health.htm">Medical care and Insurance</A>
<LI><A HREF="accomodation.htm">Accomodation</A>
</UL>
<P>
<!-- Ylempi viittaa Katin yleista koulusta sivulle -->
<LI><A HREF="herwood.htm">Vicinity of TUT, Hervanta</A>
<LI><A HREF="tampere.htm">City of Tampere</A>
<LI><A HREF="finland.htm">Finland</A>
</UL></P>
Approximately 200 international students attend Tampere University of
Technology. International Office staff members help these students
with their initial adjustment to the University, assist them throughout
their entire stay by  answering questions and giving advice about personal
concerns, social and cultural differences  and finances. International Office
works  closely with faculty, staff and campus organizations  to ensure that
international students and  scholars have the greatest opportunity to
achieve their academic and personal goals.
<P>
Prior to coming to campus, international students receive the "Guide for
Foreign Students". Among the subjects covered in the guide are housing,
health, insurance, expenses, immigration regulations and transportation.
All course descriptions in English are published in "ECTS Information
Packages"which are available at the International Office  or  they can be
found in the Internet World Wide Web.
<P>
An orientation course will be held prior to the beginning of studies at
theend of  August. The program is designed to help students and scholars
become involved in the  campus and life in Finland.           
<P>
Students are encouraged to visit the International Office to obtain program
specific information and to meet with the International Office staff.
The International Office is open Monday through Friday from 9:00 am to 15:00
pm. An international student advisor and  a study abroad advisor are available
on a walk-in basis every day.        
<P>
</DL>
<!-- sopivaan valiin voi iskea sinisen viivan erottamaan asioita toisistaan -->
<IMG WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=14 SRC="images/BlueLine.gif" ALT="- - -"><BR>
