<!-- toinen sarake, johon tulee varsinainen leipateksti, leveytta ei ole asetettu -->
<TD VALIGN=TOP>
<!-- sisennysta varten tarvitaan DefinitionList -->
<DL>
<!-- uusi kappale aloitetaan P-DT yhdistelmalla -->
<P><DT>
<!-- Otsikoiden fontiksi arial/helvetica, koska se nayttaa paremmalta -->
<!-- Huomaa myos englanninkielelle tyypillinen otsikoiden capitalisointi -->
<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica">
<h1>Course guide</h1>
</FONT>

Most of the courses are taught in Finnish but they are mainly based on literature written in
English. If the course is not taught in English, foreign students are encouraged to study the
subject concerned, for instance from books written in English. Examinations can also be arranged
individually, preferably in English.<p>

<b>All the credit units are given in the ECTS credit system.</b> (1
credit unit at TUT corresponds to 1,5 ECTS credits)<p>
	    
	  <ul type=disk>
	    <li><A HREF="mech96.html">Department of Mechanical Engineering</A>
	      <font size=-1><br>
		<A HREF="mech96.html#mecha">Engineering Mechanics</A>,
		<A HREF="mech96.html#desi">Machine Design</A>,
		<A HREF="mech96.html#produ">Production Engineering</A>...<p>
	      </font>
	    <li><A HREF="inf96.html">Department of Information Technology</A>
	      <font size=-1><br>
		<A HREF="inf96.html#mathematics">Mathematics</A>, 
		<A HREF="inf96.html#signal">Signal Processing</a>, 
		<A HREF="inf96.html#software">Software</a>, 
		<A HREF="inf96.html#telecommunications">Telecommunications</a>...<p>
	      </font>
	    <li><A HREF="ele96.html">Department of Electrical Engineering</A>
	      <font size=-1><br>
		<A HREF="ele96.html#biomedical">Biomedical Engineering</A>, 
		<A HREF="ele96.html#physics">Physics</A>, 
