<!-- Otsikoiden fontiksi arial/helvetica, koska se nayttaa paremmalta -->
<!-- Huomaa myos englanninkielelle tyypillinen otsikoiden capitalisointi -->

<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H1>Overview of the University</H1></FONT>
<!-- sisennys tapahtuu DD-tagilla -->
<DD>
Tampere University of Technology provides highest level education in technical science
and architecture,   engages in research and  product development and furthers technical
and scientific development in Finland.
<P>
In addition, TUT serves public institutions as well as industry  by means of shared
projects, commissioned research and  diploma projects.
<P>
TUT was founded in 1965.  The student body numbers  ca. 7000. The University has
about 1000 staff members.
<P>
TUT offers programs covering a wide spectrum of technological knowledge and
skills.
<P>
English has already been  introduced as the language of  tuition in Signal Processing,
Materials Engineering and  Biomedical Engineering and is due to be introduced in
Architecture,  Environmental Engineering and  Mechanical Engineering.  <P>
Right from the outset the University has emphasized the value of good  relations with
industrial and  commercial life.
<P>
Tampere Technology Centre, Hermia, with its various enterprises is a neighbor of the
University.
<P>
For more information see <a href="http://www.tut.fi/ttkk.koti/index_en.html">TUT homepage</a>.

</DL>
<!-- sopivaan valiin voi iskea sinisen viivan erottamaan asioita toisistaan -->
