<TD VALIGN=TOP>
<!-- sisennysta varten tarvitaan DefinitionList -->
<DL>
<!-- uusi kappale aloitetaan P-DT yhdistelmalla -->
<P><DT>
<!-- Otsikoiden fontiksi arial/helvetica, koska se nayttaa paremmalta -->
<!-- Huomaa myos englanninkielelle tyypillinen otsikoiden capitalisointi -->
<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H1>Medical care and insurance</H1></FONT -->
<!-- sisennys tapahtuu DD-tagilla -->
<DD>
Students should bring an E-111 form with them for the local health care.
<P>
The Finnish Student Health Service (FSHS) [in Finnish : YTHS] provides medical care for students enrolled at the universities or at other institutions of higher education in 16 towns throughout Finland. A medical care fee is included in the Student Union membership fee which is FIM 464,-. After paying the fee, students are entitled to use the medical care services. FSHS sevices are either free of charge or reasonably priced.
<P>
If a student becomes acutely ill and needs immediate attention and the Student Health Service is not open, he/she can contact one of the local communal health centers to get an appointment. In Tampere it costs about FIM 50 per appointment.
<P>
The main principle of the EC agreement is that a citizen of any EC country will get same benefits of the social security system as the citizents of the EC country where he or she is studying or working (for example hospital services). Students must have an E-111 form with them from their own local Social Security Office in order to be covered by the scheme.
</DL>
<IMG WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=14 SRC="images/BlueLine.gif" ALT="- - -"><BR>
<A HREF="info.htm">
<IMG WIDTH=95 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BackButton.gif" ALT="<- Back" BORDER=0>
</A>
</TD>
