<A HREF="http://www.tut.fi/cgi-bin/cgiwrap/~kvweb/aglimpse"><IMG WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BtnSearch.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="Search"></A><BR>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN=TOP>
<!-- sisennysta varten tarvitaan DefinitionList -->
<DL>
<!-- uusi kappale aloitetaan P-DT yhdistelmalla -->
<P><DT>
<!-- Otsikoiden fontiksi arial/helvetica, koska se nayttaa paremmalta -->
<!-- Huomaa myos englanninkielelle tyypillinen otsikoiden capitalisointi -->
<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H1>Accomodation</H1></FONT -->
<!-- sisennys tapahtuu DD-tagilla -->
<DD>
Students' housing can be arranged by Tampere District Student Housing
Foundation (<A HREF="http://www.ton.tut.fi/toas/english/housing.htm">TOAS</A>, Tampereen
seudun opiskelija-asuntosäätiö). If you wish to live in student apartments,
it is important that you confirm the date of your arrival to the TOAS Housing
Office. You may of course arrange your own accomodation outside the student
housing system, if you wish.

<P>
You should plan to arrive on weekdays during the office hours of the TOAS
Housing Office (open Monday - Friday 9.00 - 15.00) in order to get a key to
your apartment. Please contact first the TOAS Housing office as soon as you
have arrived in Tampere and arrange your housing here. Our International
tutors will help you during the official arrival dates and the orientation
period if you have any problems.
<P>
The housing is usually arranged in student apartments near the University of
Technology in the buildings called "Mikontalo", "Wäinölä" and "Paavola".
<P>
Student apartments are composed of several two- or three-bedroom apartments
in which every student has one private room and shares a kitchen and a
bathroom. Laundry facilities are located in the basement of each building.
Students should bring their own towels, bed linen and kitchenware. All the
student apartments are equipped with basic furniture. The rents range from
800 - 1200 FIM for a single room to 1500 - 3500 FIM for a whole apartment.
<P>
The address of TOAS Student Housing Office is:
<P>
Housing Office<BR>
Atalpa Kehruukoulunkatu 5<BR>
33100 Tampere<BR>
FINLAND<BR>
Tel. INT+ 358-31-249 5560 / please, ask for Housing office Fax. INT+358-31-222 5409
<P>
Places to stay if arriving late in the day or at the weekend.
<P>
Name: <B>Hostel Uimahallin Maja</B>, in the centre of Tampere<BR>
Address: Pirkankatu 10-12, 33230 Tampere, Finland Telephone: 358 - (9)31 - 222 9460<BR>
Distance from railwaystation: 1,5 km<BR>
Estimated cost per night: FIM 150 (single room)<BR>
FIM 115 (double room per person)<BR>
FIM 90 (six persons' room)<BR>
Breakfast costs about FIM 20.
<P>
Name: <B>Hotel Hermica</B>, in Hervanta
<P>
Address: Insinöörinkatu 78, 33720 Tampere, Finland <BR>
Telephone: 358 - (9)31 - 365 1111 (Fax: 358 - (9)31 - 3171200)<BR>
Distance from railwaystation: 8 km<BR>
Distance from Tampere University of Technology: 500 m<BR>
Special price for foreign students of TUT at the end of August:<BR>
FIM 150 (single room) Breakfast is not included.<BR>
FIM 200 (double room) Breakfast is not included.<BR>
Special price for foreign students of TUT at the end of August:<BR>
FIM 170 (single room) With breakfast.<BR>
FIM 220 (double room) With breakfast.
<P>
Name: <B>Hotel Victoria</B>, in the centre of Tampere
<P>
Address: Itsenäisyydenkatu 1, 33100 Tampere, Finland<BR>
Distance from railwaystation: about 150 m<BR>
Estimated cost per night: FIM 340 (single room) during the week<BR>
FIM 380 (double room)<BR>
FIM 300 (single room) during weekend<BR>
FIM 340 (double room)<BR>
Breakfast, sauna and a morning swim included.
<P>
Name: <B>Hotel Artica</B>, directly across the railway station
<P>
Address: Hämeenkatu 1, 33100 Tampere, Finland<BR>
Estimated cost per night: FIM 450 (single room) during the week<BR>
FIM 480 (double room)<BR>
FIM 330 (single room) during weekend<BR>
FIM 390 (double room)<BR>
Breakfast, a morning swim and sauna included.
</DL>
