<TD VALIGN=TOP>
<!-- sisennysta varten tarvitaan DefinitionList -->
<DL>
<!-- uusi kappale aloitetaan P-DT yhdistelmalla -->
<P><DT>
<!-- Otsikoiden fontiksi arial/helvetica, koska se nayttaa paremmalta -->
<!-- Huomaa myos englanninkielelle tyypillinen otsikoiden capitalisointi -->
<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H1>The city of Tampere</H1></FONT>
</P>
<P><DT>
<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H2>Tampere in general</H2></FONT>
<DD>
<P>Tampere is the largest inland city in Scandinavia and the third largest city in Finland with a
population of 182000. With a population over 400000 in Tampere region it is a major economical
and industrial center in Finland, situated about 180km from the capital city Helsinki
to the northwest on an isthmus between two lakes. Tampere offers a wide variety of possibilities considering
the culture and entertainment, like several theatres, museums, good chances to take part in or
follow sports and a lively nightlife.
<P><DT><FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H2>Studying in Tampere</H2></FONT>
<DD><P>Tampere is a major educational center in Finland. With two
universities, the University of Tampere and Tampere University of
Technology, there is around 18000 university students in the city.This guarantees
that a whole lot of different kind of activities can be found within the
student community as well as outside of it. While the University of Tampere is scattered around the downtown
Tampere, the University of Technology is situated as a whole in the Hervanta suburban area,
about 7 km from the downtown. Besides the universities there are also many other educational
organizations in Tampere providing education of different levels.
<P><DT><FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H2>More information about Tampere</H2></FONT>
<DD>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.tampere.fi/">City of Tampere</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.uta.fi/region.html/">Tampere region</A>
</DL>
<!-- sopivaan valiin voi iskea sinisen viivan erottamaan asioita toisistaan -->
