<!-- sisennysta varten tarvitaan DefinitionList -->
<DL>
<!-- uusi kappale aloitetaan P-DT yhdistelmalla -->
<P><DT>
<!-- Otsikoiden fontiksi arial/helvetica, koska se nayttaa paremmalta -->
<!-- Huomaa myos englanninkielelle tyypillinen otsikoiden capitalisointi -->
<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H1>Finland</H1></FONT>
</P>
<P><DT>
<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H2>General about Finland</H2></FONT>
<DD>
<P>Finland became an independent republic in 1917 and is situated in
Northern Europe neighbouring to Sweden, Norway and Russia. Since 1995
Finland has been a member of the European Union but has stayed outside
of all military alliances.
<P>There are about 5 million inhabitants in Finland, biggest cities
being the capital city Helsinki, Espoo and Tampere. Most of the population
live in the southern part of the country. With a surface area on
338.000 sq. km. the population density is rather low even in the
southern part of the country. Finland has two official languages,
Finnish which is spoken by the majority and Swedish spoken by approximately
6% of people.
<P>The climate in Finland varies quite a lot between seasons, in the
winter the temperature varies from 5 to -30 degrees Celcius and during
the summer from 10 to 30 degrees Celcius while the mean annual temperature
being around 5 degrees Celsius in the SouthernFinland.
<IMG WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=14 SRC="images/BlueLine.gif" ALT="- - -"><BR>
<P><DT>
<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H2>Where to get more information</H2></FONT>
<DD><P><LI><A HREF="http://www.finland.fi/">The homepage of Finland</A>
This page contains quite comprehensive package of information
about Finland.
</DL>
<!-- sopivaan valiin voi iskea sinisen viivan erottamaan asioita toisistaan -->
