<TD VALIGN=TOP>
<!-- sisennysta varten tarvitaan DefinitionList -->
<DL>
<!-- uusi kappale aloitetaan P-DT yhdistelmalla -->
<P><DT>
<!-- Otsikoiden fontiksi arial/helvetica, koska se nayttaa paremmalta -->
<!-- Huomaa myos englanninkielelle tyypillinen otsikoiden capitalisointi -->

<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H1>Library</H1></FONT>
<!-- sisennys tapahtuu DD-tagilla -->
<DD>

The University Library offers library and information services as well as training in how to
research for information to the University community and others in the area close to Tampere
requiring technical information. The library's collections may be used on the premises or taken on
loan. To maintain the quality of its collections, new literature and materials are continuously being
added and connections with international organizations are developed. Interlibrary loans are
arranged with almost a hundred cooperating libraries. <p>

Tampere Technical Information Service (TATTI) assists enterprises with a variety of problems in
information management. TATTI offers information searches and current awareness services via
international systems. In addition, other services are offered, such as travelling information
specialist services and three-party searching.<p>

The Library at Tampere University of Technology has about 140 000 volumes, 1500  periodicals
and a variety of CD-ROM databases. Borrowing is free. The library has books, journals,
magazines and study desks. Catalogues and borrowing are partly computerized. Library catalog is
called TUTCAT and the research language is multilingual. <p>

Most of the institutes and laboratories have small-scale libraries of their own (or some collections
of professional literature: books and periodicals).<p>

An introduction to the library and borrowing is given during the orientation course in the
beginning of the fall term.<p>

</DL>

