<!-- sisennysta varten tarvitaan DefinitionList -->
<DL>
<!-- uusi kappale aloitetaan P-DT yhdistelmalla -->
<P><DT>
<!-- Otsikoiden fontiksi arial/helvetica, koska se nayttaa paremmalta -->
<!-- Huomaa myos englanninkielelle tyypillinen otsikoiden capitalisointi -->

<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H1>Computer Center</H1></FONT>

<!-- sisennys tapahtuu DD-tagilla -->
<DD>
It is the function of the Conputer Center to provide data processing services for teaching, studies,
and administration at the University. It is responsible of the procurement, maintance, and
supervision of the computer recourses and campus network intended for the general use of the
University and for advice on their use.<p>
<DT>
<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H2>Computers for the studens</H2></FONT>
<DD>
Students have good access to computers at the University. They can either work on the UNIX
server or on PCs. All the attending students have the right to get a user name and an e-mail
address to the computing center's UNIX server. Every department has one or two computer
classrooms for students use. The staff and international tutors will assist in using computer
facilities and in demonstrating how to run software packages.<p>
<DT>
<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H2>Computer Center's information secvice</H2></FONT>
<DD>
In the G-wing in S&auml;hk&ouml;talo (Electric Building), room SG108, open between 8:30-11:00 and
12:00-15:00.<p>

The e-mail address of the information service is neuvonta@cc.tut.fi<p>

You are welcome to come and have a chat about all the issues related to the use of the computing
center. There you can also get the user names for the computing center's computers.<p>

<DT>
<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H2>Students register database (oinfo)</H2></FONT>
<DD>

An inquiry version of the students register, entries for the exams and courses are just some of the
services offered by the computing center's database services.<p>
</DL>

