<DL>
<P><DT>

<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H1>DEPARTMENTS IN THE UNIVERSITY</H1></FONT>
<!-- Using a table makes it easier to construct -->
<dd>Tampere University of Technology provides highest level education in technical science
and architecture,   engages in research and  product development and furthers technical
and scientific development in Finland.

<P>In addition, TUT serves public institutions as well as industry  by means of shared
projects, commissioned research and  diploma projects.

<P>TUT offers three one-year International University Programs, whose language
of instruction is English. The programs are in the
following fields: <a href="laaketek.htm">Biomedical Engineering</a>,
<a href="signal.htm">Digital Signal Processing</a> and <a href="material.htm">Materials Science</a>.
English is due to be introduced in
Architecture,  Environmental Engineering and  Mechanical Engineering as the language of tuition.

<P>Usually the language of Instruction at TUT is Finnish, but individual studies for
non-Finnish-speaking exchange students are
arranged in English. A good oral and written command of English is
therefore necessary for all exchange students. TOEFL may
be used to certify English skills.

<P>TUT offers programs covering a wide spectrum of technological knowledge and skills.
<P>
<UL type=disc>
<li><a href="arkkari.htm">Department of Architecture</a>
<li><A HREF="kone.htm">Department of Mechanical Engineering</a>
<li><A HREF="sahko.htm">Department of Electrical Engineering</a>
<li><A HREF="raksa.htm">Department of Civil Engineering</a>
<li><A HREF="material.htm">Department of Materials Science</a>
<li><A HREF="tite.htm">Department of Information Technology</a>
<li><A HREF="autek.htm">Automation Department</a>
<li><A HREF="tuta.htm">Department of Industrial Engineering and Management</a>
<li><A HREF="ymppi.htm">Environment Department</a>
</ul>
<P>Other Units
<P>
<UL type=disc>
<li><A HREF="http://dmiwww.cs.tut.fi/DMI-index.html">Digital Media Institute</a>
<li><A HREF="http://www.tacnet.sci.fi/edutech/">Continuing Education (Edutech)</a>
<li>Language Center
<li>University Library
<li><A HREF="http://www.tut.fi/lake/">Computer Services</A> <I>(In Finnish)</I>
<li><A HREF="http://www.pori.tut.fi/">Pori University Unit</a>
<li><A HREF="http://alpha.cc.tut.fi/">Technical Computing Institute</a> <i>(In Finnish)</i>
</ul>
</DL>

