<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H1>Academic Calendar</H1></FONT>
<!-- sisennys tapahtuu DD-tagilla -->
<DD>

<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H2>Fall semester: September 2 - December 20, 1996</H2></FONT>
<ul type=disc>
<pre>
<li><A HREF="orientation.htm">Orientation</a>:         August 28 - 30, 1996      for foreign students
<li>Registration:        August 21 -25, 1996
<li>Classes begin        September 2, 1996
<li>I Period:            September 2 - October 18, 1996
<li>II Period:           October 21 - December 5, 1996
<li>Examination period:  December 9 - 20, 1996
<li>Vacation period:     December 23, 1996 - January 3, 1997
</pre>
</ul>

<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H2>Spring semester: January 7 - May 16, 1997</H2></FONT>
<ul type=disc>
<pre>
<li><A HREF="orientation.htm">Orientation</a>:         Individual orientation
<li>Registration:        January 2 - 9, 1997 (6th of January is a holiday!)
<li>Classes begin:       January 7, 1997
<li>III Period:          January 7 - February 21, 1997
<li>Vacation period:     February 24 - February 28, 1997
<li>IV Period:           March 3 - April 25, 1997
<li>Examination period:  May 5 - 16, 1997
<li>Vacation period:     March 27 - April 2, 1997
<li>Summer vacation:     June - August 1997
</pre>
</ul>
<p>
The University does provide some instruction during the summer months and the departments are open for examinations, private studies and research work.
<p>

