<DL>
<!-- uusi kappale aloitetaan P-DT yhdistelmalla -->
<P><DT>
<!-- Otsikoiden fontiksi arial/helvetica, koska se nayttaa paremmalta -->
<!-- Huomaa myos englanninkielelle tyypillinen otsikoiden capitalisointi -->

<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica"><H1>Registration</H1></FONT>

<!-- sisennys tapahtuu DD-tagilla -->
<DD>

All exchange students, should be registered at a university in their home
country and the courses taken at Tampere University of Technology should be part of their main
degree. Two years of university studies are required for all exchange students before attending
TUT. Every student studying at TUT must register every academic year. Depending on his / her
academic status, every student has to register either as an exchange student, a degree student, a
postgraduate student, or a non-degree student.<p>

Students should register at the Student Office (or at the International Office) at the end of August
or the beginning of September for the whole year or the fall term and at the beginning of January
for the spring term.<p>

In order to register, students have to fill in a registration form and pay a membership fee of ca.
FIM 500 to the Student Union.<p>

</DL>

