<b>24330 Design of Machine Structures			4,5 ETCS credits</b><p>

<p>

Assoc. prof. Erno Keskinen<p>

Lectures 35 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Static and dynamic dimensioning of load bearing structures, plate and beam
designs. Utilizing the product model in strength calculations and manufacturing. Joints of frame
structures and booms. Foundations of machines. Light structures. Examples of booms in mobile
machinery, process industry and manufacturing systems.<p>

COURSE REQUIREMENTS: Accepted design exercises and subsequent written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Lecture notes, topical articles.<p>

NOTE: Suitable for post-graduate studies. Preliminary requirements: Passed course 24230
Advanced CAD. Recommended to be taken simultaneously with 23590 Finite Element Method in
Structural Mechanics and 27411 Manufacturing Technology I.<p>

