<b>73132 Numerical methods for Differential Equations</b>	<b>4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Assoc. prof. Seppo Pohjolainen<p>

Lectures 42 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term(s).	syksy/kev&auml;t/molemmat<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: The numerical aslution of elliptic, parabolic and hyperbolic partial differential
eqations by finite element and finite difference methods and semidiscretisation, and the use of
software packages.<p>

REQUESTS: Course work and /or written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: Sewell: The Numerical Solution of Ordinary and Partial Differential Equations,
Academic, 1988.<p>

NOTE: Lectured every second year. Will be lectured in 1996-1997.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>73133 Distributed Parameter Systems 		4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

Assoc. prof. Seppo Pohjolainen <p>

Lectures 42 h. Lab. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: The control of linear systems described by partial diferential equations and delay
equations, based on function space generalisations of the state space and transfer function theory
of control engineering. Intended for sudents with basic knowledge of control theory and an
onterest in mathematics. The course includes computer-based labs with simulations of diffusion,
vibration, etc.<p>

REQUESTS: Course work or written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: Balakrishnan: Applied functional Analysis, Springer 1976. Curtain &amp; Pritchard:
Functional Analysis in Modern Applied Mathematics, Academic 1977.<p>

NOTE: Lectured every second year. Will be lectured in 1996-1997.<p>

<p>

<p>

