<h2>Courses Offered by the Signal Processing Laboratory</h2>

<p>

<p>

<b>80100 Microprocessors				4.5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Senior Assist. Sami Kiiskil&auml;	fall term l/e	spring term l/e<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h.	-/-	-/-	2/2 	2/2<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Basic knowledge of microprocessors and systems based on tehm. Basics of
microprocessor based systems programming. Microprocessors, memories, peripherals, auxiliary
logic.<p>

REQUESTS: Weekly exercises and final exam.<p>

LITERATURE: Lecture notes.<p>

NOTE: Obligatory course for all students of information technology. Can't be one of the
advanced courses on digital technology or computer science.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>80105 Microcontroller Systems			4.5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Senior Assist. Sami Kiiskil&auml;	fall term l/e	spring term l/e<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h.	-/-	-/-	2/2 	2/2<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Specification, design and implementation of microcontrollr based systems. Basics
of printed circuit board design. Different controllers, usage of emulators, required pheripheral
components.<p>

REQUESTS: Project exercise and final exam.<p>

LITERATURE: To be announced.<p>

PREQUISITIES: 74001, 80100, 80113<p>

NOTE: Obligatory course for basic module of signal processing.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>80113  Basic Digital Design			6.0 ECTS credits </b><p>

<p>

Assoc. Prof. Jouni Isoaho	fall term l/e	spring term l/e<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h.	2/2	2/2	-/-	 -/-<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Design of simple logic systems. Logic families, logic, combinatory and sequence
circuits. Algorithmic design methods. Specification, design and implementation of a digital device.
Basics of VHDL design.<p>

REQUESTS: Weekly exercises and final exam.<p>

LITERATURE: To be announced.<p>

PREQUISITIES: 74001, 80100<p>

NOTE: Replaces old course 80110 Digital systems desing.<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>80114  Digital ASIC Design			6.0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Assoc. Prof. Jouni Isoaho	fall term l/e	spring term l/e<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h.	-/-	-/-	2/2 	2/2<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Design of complex digital and ASIC design. Methods of data and control systems
design. Specification, design and implementation of a digital ASIC circuit. VHDL and logic
synthesis. Circuit technologies and testability. Management and economic aspects of a ASIC
project.<p>

REQUESTS: Project exercise and final exam.<p>

LITERATURE: To be announced.<p>

PREQUISITIES: 80113, 83000<p>

