<p>

<p>

<b>80120  Computer Architectures			4.5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Jukka Saarinen	fall term l/e	spring term l/e<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h.	-/-	 -/-	 2/2	2/2<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Architecture of computers and computer systems. Design principles of central
processing units. Simulation on RISC architecture. Design of data processing and control units at
register level using different implementation methods. Operating principles of memories and
memory systems.<p>

REQUESTS: Exam, calculation excercises, project exercise and presentation.<p>

LITERATURE: John L. Hennessy &amp; David A. Patterson: Computer Architecture, A Quantitative
Approach, Morgan Kauffman Publishers Inc. 1990. Possible other literature is announced later.<p>

PREQUISITIES: 80113<p>

NOTE: There is limited amount of students allowed on this course. The selection is made at the
beginning of the course.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>80126 VLSI for Signal Processing			9.0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Assoc. Prof. Olli Vainio	fall lec/exe spring lec/exe<p>

Lectures 42 h. Exercises 42 h.	3/3	3/3	-/3	-/3<p>

Laboratory work 42 h<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Principles of CMOS VLSI design, digital arithmetic, micro-architecture of
computational elements, filter implementations, microprogrammed signal processing structures,
core processors for DSP, analog interfaces, system design methods.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Final exam and exercise projects.<p>

TEXT: Weste &amp; Eshraghian, Principles of CMOS VLSI Design: A Systems Perspective,
Addison-Wesley, 1993. Additional reading announced during the course.<p>

NOTES: Basic knowledge about MOS design, and 80505/6 Digital Signal Processing are
required. 80114 Digital ASIC Design is also recommended as prerequisites.<p>

<p>

