<b>80554 Advanced Digital Filtering	 		3,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

Assoc.Prof. Tapio Saram&auml;ki	fall term l/e	spring term l/e<p>

Lectures 28h. Exercises 14h	-/-	 -/-	4/2	-/-<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Efficient design and implementation of finite-impulse response filters, infinite-impulse response filters, decimators, and interpolators as well as filter banks. Other
applications of multirate filtering are also considered.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Project work and final examination.<p>

TEXT: Lecture Notes, Handbook for Digital Signal Processing, edited by S. K. Kaiser and J. F.
Kaiser, John Wiley and Sons, 1993, E. C. Ifeachor and B. W. Jervis: "Digital Signal Processing -
A Practical Approach", Addison-Wesley 1993.<p>

NOTES: Lectures in Finnish or English. 80505/6 as prerequisite.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>80555 System Level DSP Algorithms	 	3,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

