Lectures 28h. Exercises 14h	-/-	 -/-	-/-	4/2<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: System-level design of DSP algorithms for various applications. Optimizations of
the algorithms for both VLSI- and signal processor implementations are considered.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Project work and final examination.<p>

TEXT: Lecture Notes.<p>

NOTES: Lectures in Finnish or English. 801554 or 80552 as prerequisite.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>80562 Nonlinear Signal Processing 		4.5 ECTS credits</b><p>

Dr. Tech. Pauli Kuosmanen	fall term l/e	spring term l/e<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28h.	2/2	2/2	-/- 	-/-<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Nonlinear signal processing algorithms. Median and other magnitude order based
filters.Morphological, homomorphic and polynomial filters. Adaptive nonlinear filters.<p>

REQUESTS: Active participation on lectures and exercises and approved final exam.<p>

LITERATURE: Nonlinear Digital Filters, Principles and Applications, I. Pitas and A.N.
Venetsanopoulos, Kluwer Academic Publishers, 1990.<p>

PREQUISITIES: 80502.<p>

NOTE: Can be used as licenciate course. <p>

<p>

<b>80563 Advanced Methods in Nonlinear Signal Processing</b>    <b>4.5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Dr. Tech. Pauli Kuosmanen	fall lec/exe spring lec/exe <p>

Lectures 42h, exercises 14h	-/- 	-/-	3/1	3/1<p>

 <p>

CONTENTS: Advanced methods in nonlinear signal and image processing will be discussed in the
course. The focus shall be on one of the following operator classes: order statistics,
morphological or polynomial operators.<p>

TEXT: I. Pitas and A. Venetsanopoulos, Nonlinear Digital Filters, Kluwer Academic Publishers,
1990, and recent journal articles.<p>

NOTES: Offered every other year, not offered in 1995 - 96. Prerequisite: 80562 Nonlinear Signal
Processing.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>80571 Digital Image Processing II			4.5 ECTS credits</b><p>

Senior Assist. Karen Egiazarian	fall lec/exe spring lec/exe<p>

Lectures 42. Exercises 14	 -/- 	-/-	 3/1	3/1<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Advanced topics in image processing will be presented in the course in the form of
lectures and/or seminars. Topics include image representation, image filtering and restoration,
image analysis and computer vision, image reconstruction from projections and image data
compression.<p>

TEXT: Anil K. Jain: Fundamentals of Digital Image Processing. Prentice-Hall, 1989.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Attendance of most of the lectures and exercise sessions, pass the final exam
and/or in-class presentation.<p>

PREQUISITIES: 80511 Digital Image Processing. <p>

NOTES: Offered every other year. Not offered in 1996 - 97. Extremely useful course for signal
processing majors.<p>

<p>

