<b>72115 Basic Semiconductor Technology		4,5 ECTS credits

</b><p>

PhD Jouko Lammasniemi<p>

Lectures 42 h, exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Basic properties of semiconductor materials (Si, GaAs). Binary, ternary and
quaternary compound semiconductors. Heterostructures. Manufacturing of the most important
types of semiconductor devices and integrated circuits. Diffusion, ion implantation, oxidation,
chemical vapor depositon (CVD), metallization, epitaxial growth nethods.  <p>

LITERATURE:J.W.Mayer &amp; S.S.Lau: Electronic Materials Science. MacMillan, NY 1990.<p>

PREREQUISITES: Course 72064 <p>

<p>

<p>

<b>72122 Semiconductor Physics I			3,0 ECTS credits

</b><p>

PhD Jouko Lammasniemi<p>

Lectures 42 h, exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Energy bands in semiconductors. Properties of homogenous semiconductors.
Generation and recombination. Boltzmann transport equation. Scattering and mobility.<p>

LITERATURE: S.S. Li: Semiconductor Physical Electronics. Plenum Press, New York,1993.
Chapters 1-8.<p>

PREREQUISITES: Course 72115 <p>

<p>

<p>

<b>72123 Semiconductor Physics II			3,0 ECTS credits

</b><p>

PhD Arto Salokatve<p>

Lectures 42 h, exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Optical and photoelectric properies of semiconductors. Meta/semiconductor
junction, thermionic emission. Current mechanisms in homo-and heterojunctions. Optical devices
(solar cells, detectors, LED's and lasers). Fast III-V semiconductor devices. <p>

LITERATURE: S.S. Li: Semiconductor Physical Electronics. Plenum Press, New York,1993.
Chapters 9-15.<p>

PREREQUISITES: Course 72122 <p>

<p>

<p>

<b>72135 Photonics				4,5 ECTS credits

</b><p>

PhD Arto Salokatve<p>

Lectures 42 h, exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Optical resonatiors, photon optics, laser amplifiers, semiconductor lasers and
detectors, fiber optical systems. <p>

LITERATURE: Saleh, Teich: Fundamentals of Photonics. Wiley, New York, 1991. Chapters 9,
11-17, 22.<p>

