<b>72448 Introduction to Optical Spectroscopy		4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Docent Rolf Hernberg<p>

Lectures 28h, Exercises 28h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Physical elements of optical atomic and molecular spectroscopy. Rotational,
vibrational, Raman, electronic and combined spectra of diatomic molecules. Optical electronic
spectra of atoms. Introduction to the spectra of polyatomic molecules. <p>

REQUIREMENTS: Written exams on problem sessions and the whole course. <p>

LITERATURE: C.N. Banwell, Fundamentals of Molecular Spectroscopy, McGraw-Hill, 1983.<p>

NOTE: Course given every second year. Given in the academic year 1995-96.<p>

<b>

72451 Methods of Optical Spectroscopy		3,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Doc. Rolf Hernberg<p>

Lectures 21h, Exercises 21h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Experimental methods of optical spectroscopy. Blackbody radiation. Spectral line
shape. Origin and processing of spectroscopic signals. Measuring optics. Spectroscopic
instruments and lasers.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Written exams on problem sessions and the whole course. <p>

LITERATURE: R. Hernberg: Optisen spektroskopian perusteet, TTKK Opintomoniste 172. (In
Finnish)<p>

NOTE: Course given every second year. Not given in the academic year 1995-96.<p>

