<b>74081   High Frequency Techniques			3,0 ECTS credits

</b><p>

Lecturer Olli-Pekka Lunden<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

OBJECTIVE: Give basic knowledge of high frequency techniques. Students will learn to
understand, analyze, and also in some cases design RF- and microwave circuits and entire radio
systems.<p>

CONTENTS: Waveguides, resonators, active high frequency devices, antennas, radiowave
propagation, applications.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Passed examination and exercises<p>

RECOMMENDED PREVIOUS KNOWLEDGE: Electronics basic module.<p>

LITERATURE: R&auml;is&auml;nen, Lehto: Radiotekniikka, Otatieto Oy, publication #885.<p>

FOR MORE INFORMATION CONTACT: Olli-Pekka Lunden (olli-pekka.lunden@nmp.
nokia.com, olunden@ee.tut.fi).<p>

