<p>

<b>74111 Integrated Analog Circuits 			6,0 ECTS credits

</b><p>

Lecturer Jarmo Tanskanen<p>

Lectures 28h (fall), Exercises 48h (fall) + 8h (spring)<p>

Takes place during buth fall and spring terms.<p>

<p>

AIMS: The Lectures and Exercises are meant to provide solid basic design skills, based on an
extensive use of P-SPICE or H-SPICE for MS-Windows and UNIX Platforms.<p>

CONTENTS: Precise Models for Standard Analog Integrated components: Resistors, Capacitors,
Inductors, Diodes, BJT, FET and MOSFET for BiCMOS technology. Circuit Modelling: DC-Sweep Analysis, Frequency and Noise Analysis, Transient and Spectral Analysis, Temperature
Dependence, Parametric, Monte-Carlo and Worst-Case Analysis. Mixed Mode Analysis;
Behavioural Modelling. Basic Designs: One Stage Circuits, Cascodes, Current Mirrors, Voltage
References, Differential  Amplifiers, Output Amplifiers, Current Conveyors, Transconductance
Amplifiers, Operational Amplifiers, Comparators. Design Analog Circuits for Mixed Analog-Digital Subsystems: Analog Switches, Sample/Hold and Track/Hold Memories. Main
Applications Design: Continuous-Time Filters, SC-Filters, Oscillators, Digital to Analog and
Analog to Digital Converters.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved course works/homeworks and written examination on the theory.<p>

REFERENCES:<p>

[1] Laker K., Sansen W.,  Analog Integrated Circuits and Systems, McGraw-Hill, 1994.<p>

[2] Gray P., Meyer R., Analog Integrated Circuits, John Wiley &amp; Sons, 1993, 3rd Ed.<p>

[3] Allen P., Holberg D., CMOS Analog Circuit Design, Holt, Rienart and Winston, 1987.<p>

[4] Geiger R., Allen P. and Strader N., VLSI Design Techniques, McGraw-Hill, 1990.<p>

[5] Alvarez A., BiCMOS Technology and Applications, Kluwer, 1989.<p>

[6] Tomazou C., Lidgey F., Haigh D., Analog IC Design, IEE, 1990.<p>

[7] Ismail M., Fiez T.,  Analog VLSI: Signal and Information Processing, McGraw-Hll, 1994.<p>

[8] Sakurai S., Ismail M., Low Voltage CMOS Operational Amplifiers, Kluwer, 1994.<p>

NOTES:	74001 Basic Circuits of Electronics<p>

		74031 and 74035 Electronics Laboratory<p>

		74042 Electronic Circuits and Devices<p>

		74052 App. of Semiconductor Components<p>

		74251 IC Technique<p>

		74501 Analog Technique<p>

		74521 Electronic Components and Circuits<p>

The course is an essential pre-requisite for the courses: <p>

		74081 High-Frequency Technique<p>

		74560 High-Speed Electronics<p>

		83700 Communication Circuits<p>

<p>

<b>74251 IC-Technique				7,5 ECTS credits

</b><p>

Jarmo Tanskanen<p>

Lectures 28h. Exercises 14h. <p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

AIMS: Get a student widely familiar with IC-circuit and layout techniques.<p>

CONTENTS: Fabrication techniques of Bipolar and CMOS circuits briefly. Modelling of the
circuits, estimation of performance characteristics, logic design and methods, testability design.
There is also quite large exercise with GDT or IC station software during spring term.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Exercises and final exam on theory<p>

LITERATURE: Weste, N.H.E., Eshraghian, K.: Principles of CMOS VLSI Design, A Systems
Perspective, 2ed, Addison-Wesley, 1993, R.L.Geiger, P.E.Allen, N.R.Strader: VLSI, Design
Techniques for Analog and Digital Circuits, McGraw-Hill, 1990. K.Laker, W.Sansen: Design of
Analog Integrated Circuits and Systems, McGraw-Hill,1994.<p>

NOTES: Pre-requisite 74042 and 80111.<p>

