<h2>Power Electronics</h2>

<p>

<b>78100 Introduction to Power Electronics</b>

<p>

Prof. Juhani K&auml;rn&auml; <p>

Lectures 28 h, exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Power semiconductor devices. Naturally commutating converters. A.C. regulators.
D.C. switching regulators. Static power inverters.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Final examination.<p>

LITERATURE: B.M. Bird, K.G. King, D.A.G. Pedder: An Introduction to Power Electronics.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>78110 Power Semiconductor Devices		4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Senior Ass. Jaakko Ollila <p>

Lectures 28 h, exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: SCR, GTO, PIN-diode,BJT, FET, IGBT, SIT, SITh, MCT. Device selection.
Losses and thermal design. Control and protection. Operation in switching converters. Passive
components, chokes and capacitors. Current, speed and angle measurement.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Exam from the contents of lectures and exercises. <p>

LITERATURE: Mohan, Undeland and Robbins, Power Electronics: Converters, Applications and
Design, John Wiley &amp; Sons, Second Edition, 1995.<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

