<a name="magnetism">
<h2>Electricity and Magnetism</h2>

 <p>

<b>79105 Electrical Materials			4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Lab. Eng. Lasse S&ouml;derlund<p>

Lectures 42 h, exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Resistive materials, magnetic materials, permanent magnets and dielectric materials.
Theory of semiconductors, solid state components.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Written exam of the lectures and literature. Literature remains to be
announced.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>79109  Network Analysis			4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Lecturer Risto Mikkonen<p>

Lectures 42 h, exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS:  General circuit analysis with graph theory. Fundamental methods of network
analysis. Sensitivity analysis. Numerical approach. Non-linear dc. circuits. Dynamic circuits. State
variables. Optimization algorithms.  <p>

REQUIREMENTS: Written exam of the lectures, approved case-exercise.<p>

LITERATURE: Istvan Vago, Graph theory, application to the calculation of electrical networks.
Elsevier 1985.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>79115  Electromagnetic System Modelling		4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Jarl-Thure Eriksson<p>

Lectures 28 h, exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Mathematical conditioning of magnetic circuits. Electromechanical coupling. Static
and dynamic equilibrium conditions. Analysis examples. Measuring and optimizing criteria of
electromagnetic devices. Temperature considerations.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Written exam of the lectures and literature.<p>

LITERATURE: H. Woodson, J. Melcher, Electromechanical dynamics, Part I. John Wiley &amp;
Sons.<p>

<p>

<b><p>

79122  Nonlinear and Chaotic Systems		4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Jarl-Thure Eriksson<p>

Lectures 28 h, exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Nonlinearity, nonlinear dynamic models, linearization. Chaos theory, strange
attractors, fractals. Information in physical systems. Complex systems. Identification of chaos.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Written exam of the lectures and literature. Literature remains to be
announced.<p>

<p>

<b>79127  Complex Systems			7,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Jarl-Thure Eriksson<p>

Lectures 30 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Modelling in physical science, complex theory. Information and its meaning in
complex systems. Economical, political and social systems. Guiding function of brain.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Attendance is required. Written exam of the lectures, approved case exercise.<p>

LITERATURE: A series of actual scientific articles.<p>

<p>

