<p>

<b>26291  Machine Automation, Special Assignment  	6.0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Reijo Tuokko<p>

Assoc. prof. Tapio Virvalo<p>

Takes place during both fall and spring terms<p>

<p>

OBJECTIVE: Learn to solve problems in the field of research and design.<p>

CONTENTS: A research or product development assignment from the professional subject area.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercise.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>26312  Introduction to Hydraulics and Automation   	4.5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Assoc. prof. Jari Rinkinen  and prof. Reijo Tuokko<p>

Lectures 35 h.  Exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term<p>

<p>

OBJECTIVE: Brief view of hydraulics, pneumatics and electrical automation in machine design
applications, necessary calculations and symbols.<p>

CONTENTS: The methods to produce and use hydraulic and pneumatic energy. The basics of
fluid dynamics. Automatic functions by means of mechanics, hydraulics and pneumatics.  Components in hydraulics and pneumatics and their symbols.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and an examination.<p>

REQUIRED READING: Copies of the lecture material.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>26321  Measurements in Hydraulics and Automation	4.5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Senior ass. Asko Ellman<p>

Lectures and seminars 28 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term<p>

<p>

OBJECTIVE: Understanding the principles of measuring and data acquisition. To know the
basics of different methods to measure and control hydraulic and pneumatic systems and automatic machines. Readiness to make measurements.<p>

CONTENTS: Principles of measuring and data acquisition. Accuracy. Calibration. Basics of
measuring pressure, force, torque, flow, position, velocity, acceleration and temperature. Measuring hydraulic noise and vibrations.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and an examination.<p>

REQUIRED READING: Copies of the lecture material.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>26332  Laboratory Course in Fluid Power		7.5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Assoc. prof Tapio Virvalo, senior ass. Esa M&auml;kinen<p>

Takes place during spring term<p>

<p>

OBJECTIVE: Give the skill to design and realize control and servo systems with hydraulic and
pneumatic actuators.<p>

CONTENTS: Control and servo system exercises with hydraulic and pneumatic actuators by
using PLC, microprocessor and PC.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and seminars.<p>

REQUIRED READING: To be informed during the course.<p>

<p>

<b><p>

26342  Seminar for Students doing Dr Thesis <p>

         in Hydraulics and Automation</b>		<b>3.0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Matti Vilenius, prof. Reijo Tuokko, assoc. prof. Jari Rinkinen and assoc. prof. Tapio
Virvalo<p>

Seminars 28 h.<p>

Takes place during both fall and spring terms<p>

<p>

