<p>

<b>26410  Systematic Project Engineering		3.0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Special Lecturers Antero H&auml;likk&auml; and Jorma Repo<p>

Lectures and teamwork exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term<p>

<p>

OBJECTIVE: Readiness to produce system model of a project.  Developing systematic way of
thinking and teamwork abilities.<p>

CONTENTS: Setting up and ecology of a project. Setting up and modelling the objective by
means of effect/charge ratio.  Resources, organising, know-how.  Factors, cultures and interest
groups of a project environment.  Process work and the method of a creative proceeding. 
Follow-up and inspection.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Participating in lectures and exercises and approved exercises.<p>

REQUIRED READING: Material submitted during lectures.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>26420  Robotics and Automatic Materials Handling 	4.5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Reijo Tuokko<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term<p>

<p>

OBJECTIVE: Understanding the principles of robotics. Basic skills of designing and selecting
components of automated materials handling systems and short-distance transfer.<p>

CONTENTS: Industrial robotics. Components used in automated materials handling systems.
Principles of designing and dimensioning systems.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and examination on the material.<p>

REQUIRED READING: Copies of lecture materialand literature stated at lectures.<p>

<p>

<b>26430  Mobile and Telerobotics             		4.5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Reijo Tuokko<p>

Lectures and seminars 28 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term<p>

<p>

OBJECTIVE: Acquaintance with structure, operation, design, control, programming and
applications of mobile robots, telemanipulators and other special robots.<p>

CONTENTS: Structure , components, subsystems and control of mobile robots and
telemanipulators. Autonomous and teleoperated robots. Model based telerobotics. Factory and
field applications.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and examination on the material.<p>

REQUIRED READING: Copies of lecture material and literature stated at lectures.<p>

<p>

<b>26440  Automatic Assembly			4.5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Reijo Tuokko	<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises and teamwork 28 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term<p>

<p>

OBJECTIVE: Readiness to design and realize automated assembly systems and machinery.
Understanding the design for manufacture.<p>

CONTENTS: Components, subsystems and principles of automated assembly systems. Designing
products for manufacture, assembly and recycling. Designing assembly systems for volume
production and flexible short-run production. Interfaces to other production. Automated
disassembly of products.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and examination on the material<p>

REQUIRED READING: Copies of lecture material and literature stated at lectures<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>26251  Systems Engineering in Machine and <p>

          Factory Automation			4.5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Reijo Tuokko	<p>

Lectures 14 h. Exercises and teamwork 56 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term<p>

<p>

OBJECTIVE: Readiness to design systematically multi-technical machinery and devices and
technology of automated systems. Practical experience of using systematic design and teamwork
methods.<p>

CONTENTS: Components and subsystems of machine and factory automation. Combining
components. Design of control systems. Systematic design of multi-technical automation systems.
Using systematic project work methods and procedures practically. Main idea of the course is
learning by doing. Lectures give readiness and guidance for this learning process. During the
course a demanding automation project is carried through as teamwork.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and teamwork and examination on the material.<p>

REQUIRED READING:  Copies of lecture material and literature stated at lectures.<p>

<p>

<b>26460  Robotics, Special Assignment		6.0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Reijo Tuokko<p>

Takes place during both fall and spring terms<p>

<p>

OBJECTIVE: Acquaint students with solving research and development problems of robotics<p>

CONTENTS: A limited research or development project dealing with robotics.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved report<p>

NOTE: Subject and proceeding are discussed with supervisor personally.<p>

<p>

<p>

