course. Approved exercises.<p>

LITERATURE: P. Kettunen, T.Tiainen: Metallioppi IV, TTKK, Lecture
material 117, 1987 (when applicable).<p>

<B>28210 Physical Metallurgy V  4,5 ECTS credits</B><p>

Prof. Pentti Kettunen<p>
Lectures 28 h, seminar Exercises 14 h. <p>
Given during spring term<p>

OBJECTIVE: A detailed insight in the mechanisms and processes
controlling the strength of metals. <p>

CONTENTS: Monotonic and cyclic strain hardening. Fatigue. Creep and
high temperature mechanical properties. Fracture physics. Modern
materials testing methods. <p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved written examination of the contents of the
course. <p>

LITERATURE: Copies of lecture material.<p>

<B>28231 Corrosion Phenomena  3,0 ECTS credits</B><p>

