Lectures 28 h. Exercises and seminars 14 h.<p>
Given during fall term<p>

OBJECTIVE: A detailed survey on diffusion mechanisms and processes
controlled by diffusion.<p>

CONTENTS: Diffusion of solute and interstitial atoms. Diffusion driven
by chemical gradient in binary or multicomponent alloys. Short circuit
and surface diffusion. Homogenization.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved written examination of contents of lectures and
exercises.<p>

