<a name="#institutes">
<h2>Description of the Institutes and Laboratories and Their
Activities in the Department of Environmental Engineering</h2>

<p>

<b>Thermal Engineering</b><p>

<p>

Our society requires energy in many forms. Energy must be produced
with ever increasing efficiency and environment friendliness. It must
also be used wisely and economically. It is precisely with energy
production and its efficient use that the institute of Thermal
Engineering is involved. From amongst the wide range of activities,
the principal emphasis rests on combustion processes, computer
calculation of fluid flow measurement, pumps and blowers, energy use
in buildings, air conditioning, and refrigeration engineering.<p>

<p>

One example of the Institute's multifarious research activities is the
joint developement with industry of a heavy-oil burner.<p>

The institute is well equipped to participate in research and
development work on energy production, emissions reduction, economical
operation and the development of new products and methods.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>Paper Converting</b><p>

<p>

The Institute of Paper Converting gives education in the fields of paper and paper converting
technologies. In paper converting technology is especially concentrated on packaging materials of
which flexible and liquid packaging products form the lion's share in paper and paper board
converting. Ever stricter legislation in different countries, and particularly in EU directives,
stipulates that packaging be recyclable. The Institute of Paper Converting is responding to this
equally technological and economic challenge by researching and developing environmentally friendly paper, paper board and plastic packaging solutions.<p>

<p>

Pilot lines at the Institute are helping in the development of manufacturing processes and different
webs for flexible and liquid packaging.<p>

<p>

<a name="study">
<h2>Study Options Available in These Departments</h2>

<b>Paper Converting</b><p>

<p>

- Paper technology<p>

- Paper converted products and packaging technology<p>

<p>

<b>Thermal Engineering</b><p>

<p>

- Fluid flow and heat transfer engineering<p>

- Thermal power engineering<p>

- Combustion engineering<p>

- Refrigeration machinery and heat pumps<p>

- Heating, ventilation, and water supply engineering<p>

<p>

<b>Environmental Engineering</b><p>

<p>

- Use and protection of water systems<p>

- Municipal and industrial water supply and sewerage<p>

- Waste treatment<p>

- Environmental protection<p>

<p>

<a name="degree">
<h2>Degree Program in Environmental Engineering</h2>

<p>

Since the beginning of 1970's water and sanitary engineering education
has been given within the Civil Engineering programme. A Master`s
programme in environmental engineering was started in 1991 and
includes water and environmental engineering, chemistry, thermal
engineering and safety engineering. The basic degree awarded by TUT
after completition of studies is the M.Sc. in Engineering.<p>

<p>

<b>Objectives and professional orientation</b><p>

<p>

Environmental issues have gained a lot of attention and the need for
managing them have widely been admitted. Thus it is essential to train
specialists to meet new challenges. Prevention and management are key
words in solving environmental problems. Environmental engineering is
needed to steer practices towards clean technologies, environmentally
sound products and management of natural resources. Environmental
specialists must be able to work in the context of economic, social
and ecological issues.<p>

<p>

The programme provides the competence for students to work for
consultants, contractors, public authorities, commercial and

industrial enterprises, incurance companies, national and
international organizations, and research and training institutes.<p>

<b>Participation of International Students</b><p>

<p>

The programme provides a limited number of courses in English for
MSc-studies. These courses are shown in the presentation part of the
information package. The teaching in English is in process and will in
future provide more opportunities for international students to study
in the programme.<p>

<p>

However, within the degree programme it is possible to have teaching
(no lectures) in different topics by agreement with the
professors. The study books in English will be selected. The professor
provides guidance on reading and gives written or oral
examination. BSc-degree or equivalent in Environmental Engineering or
related studies is a prereguirement. International student applicants
must prepare a proposal of a study plan based on this information
package and send it to TUT for review.<p>


<a name="thermal">
<h2>Thermal Engineering</h2>

<p>

<p>

<b>25100 Introduction to Thermal Engineering</b>		4.5  ECTS credits <p>

<p>

Prof. Reijo Karvinen<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Basics of thermodynamics, fluid dynamics, and heat transfer. Principles of machines
and devices used in energy production and utilization.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Written exam. <p>

LITERATURE: Copies of lecture material.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>25110 Thermodynamics</b>		 		4.5 ECTS credits<p>

<p>

Prof. Antero Aittom&auml;ki<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Second law and it's consequences. Power and refrigeration cycles. Thermodynamic
functions. Thermodynamic equilibrium. State equations. Availability (exergy). Combustion.
Modelling of processes. Third law.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Written exam and exercises.<p>

LITERATURE: For instance, Holman: Thermodynamics. 4 th ed. New York 1969. McGraw-Hill
Book Co.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>25200 Fluid Dynamics</b>				4.5 ECTS credits<p>

<p>

Prof. Reijo Karvinen<p>

Lectures 42 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Governing equations of fluid flow. Irrotational flow theory. Principles of laminar
and turbulent viscous fluid flow.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: Copies of lecture material.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>25210 Viscous Fluid Flow</b>                		4.5 ECTS credits<p>

<p>

Senior Ass. Hannu Ahlstedt<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Boundary layer theory. Analytical and numerical solution methods applied to jets,
wakes, mixing of jets and internal flows. Turbulence models. Gas-particle flow.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Written exam and approved exercises.<p>

LITERATURE: Copies of lecture material. Cebeci, T. and Bradshaw, P.: Momentum transfer in
boundary layers. Hemisphere Corporation, 1977.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>25220 Hydraulics Machines</b>			4.5 ECTS credits<p>

<p>

Prof. Reijo Karvinen<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Theory of hydraulic machinery. Design of dynamic pumps and Kaplan turbines.
Characteristics of pumps. Theory of fluid transients.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and exam.<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>25300 Introduction to Heat Transfer</b>		4.5 ECTS credits<p>

<p>

Assoc. Prof. Risto Raiko<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Basic knowledge in: Heat conduction. Convective heat and mass transfer. Heat
transfer change of phase. Heat exchangers. Radiation.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Copies of lecture material.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>25305 Heat Transfer</b>		         		4.5 ECTS credits<p>

<p>

Assoc. Prof. Timo Kalema<p>

Lectures 40 h. Exercises 40 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Heat transfer from fins, analytical and numerical methods for two-dimensional
conduction and transient conduction, spectral properties of radiation, radiation networks, phase
change in conduction heat transter.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercise and exam.<p>

LITERATURE: Incropera &amp; DeWitt; Fundamentals of Heat and Mass Transfer; Bayley, Owen,
Turner: Heat Transfer; copies of lecture material.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>25321 Convection Heat Transfer</b>	         		4.5 ECTS credits<p>

<p>

Prof. Reijo Karvinen<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Equations of convective heat and mass transfer. Laminar and turbulent internal and
external convection. Transient convection. Numerical modelling of turbulent fluid flow and heat
transfer. Turbulence models.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercise and a written exam.<p>

