<a name="water">
<h2>Water and Environmental Engineering</h2>

<p>

<p>

<b>59101 Fundamentals of Water and Waste Engineering</b>        	<b>4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Lecturer, Dr. (eng)  Jouko Peltokangas <p>

Lectures 42 h. Exercises 10 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

NOTE: To understand the role of water and waste engineeringin society.<p>

CONTENTS: Inroduction to water and waste engineering (hydrology,hydromechanics, water
supply, sewerage systems, waste management, environmental in pact assessment).<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and passed written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Peltokangas 1994: Vesi- ja ymp&auml;rist&ouml;nsuojelutekniikan perusteet. Copies of
lecture material.  Additional reading to be announced at lectures.<p>

<b>

59202 Hydrology</b>				<b>3,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Lecturer, M.Sc. Jaakko Muurim&auml;ki<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 10 h. Project exercises 10 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

NOTE: To understand the role of hydrological phenomena to watershed planning, hydraulic
structures and design of water supply and sewerage systems. <p>

CONTENTS: Advanced hydrology. Hydrological measurements and calculations, statistical and
systemanalytical methods. Flow regulation and watershed planning. Human impacts on hydrologic
cycle. Design and research methods.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and passed written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Mustonen 1986: Sovellettu hydrologia. Vesiyhdistys ry. (chapters 1-8, 11-14).
RIL 141: Yleinen vesitekniikka (chapters 1, 4). Copies of lecture material. Additional reading to
be announced at lectures.<p>

<p>

<b>

59212 Hydromechanics</b> 			<b>4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Lecturer, M.Sc Pentti Bergmann<p>

Lectures 42 h. Exercises 12 h.<p>

Project excercises 26 h.<p>

Takes place during both fall and spring terms.<p>

<p>

GOAL: To give theoretical and mathematical background for designing water supply andsewerage networks, pumping stations, open channels, etc.<p>

CONTENTS: Hydrostatics and hydrodynamics. Pipe and open channel flow. Physical and statistical modelling. Hydromechanical  structures and machines.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and passed written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: RIL 187-1990: Sovellettu hydromekaniikka, RIL 92-1973: Vesirakennus. Copies
of lecture material. Additional reading to be announced at lectures.<p>

<p>

<b>

59220 Water Supply and Sewerage Systems</b>                     	<b>4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Lecturers, M.Sc. Esko Haume and <p>

M.Sc. Timo Heinonen<p>

Lectures 56 h. Excursions 10 h.<p>

Project excercises 40 h.<p>

Takes place during both fall and spring terms.<p>

<p>

GOAL: Design and operation of municipal water supply and sewerage systems.<p>

CONTENTS:  Sanitary engineering as a part of infrastructural design. Utilization of groundwater
aquifers and surface water sources. Design, construction and renovation of water supply and
sewerage systems. Pumping. Flow measurement. Selection criteria for water and wastewater
treatment systems. Principles of treatment plant design. Operation and maintenance.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved project and case excercises. Passed written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Kaupunkiliiton julk. B63, 1979: Vesijohtojen ja viem&auml;reiden suunnittelu. Copies
of lecture material. Additional reading to be announced at lectures.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>59233 Physical and Chemical Unit Operations 	4,5 ECTS credits

      in Water Engineering</b>			<p>

<p>

Prof. Matti Viitasaari<p>

Senior Lec. Simo Isoaho<p>

Lectures 42 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: Design, operation, research and development of unit operations in water and wastewater
treatment.<p>

CONTENTS: Mechanical separation, filtration, flotation, pH-adjustment, gas transfer, aeration,
stripping, membrane techniques, ion exchange, electrochemical proceses.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and passed written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Peltokangas, Hein&auml;nen and Viitasaari: Vesihuoltotekniikan yksikk&ouml;operaatiot ja
yksikk&ouml;prosessit, osa I: Vedenhankinta, osa II: J&auml;tevesien puhdistus.  Additional reading to be announced at lectures.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>59236 Water and Wastewater Treatment	3,0 ECTS credits 

      Plant Design </b><p>

<p>

Prof. Matti Viitasaari<p>

Lectures 28 h. Project exercises 40 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

					<p>

GOAL: Water and wastewater treatment plant design and operation.<p>

CONTENTS: Selection and combination of unit operations. Process lay-out. Instrumentation and
automation. Operation and management. Economic and financial aspects.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercise and passed written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Additional reading to be announced at lectures.<p>

<p>

<b>59250 Applied Limnology</b>			<b>4,5 ECTS credits</b>	<p>

<p>

Lecturer, Dr. Tom Frisk<p>

Lectures 28 h.<p>

Exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

OBJECTIVE: The aim of the course is to give theoretical elements of limnology and to make the
student familiar with aquatic environmental assesment as well as other applications of limnology.<p>

CONTENTS: The main features of the physics, chemistry and biology of lakes and rivers. Water
quality models and their applications in water management and protection.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Literal exam and exercises.<p>

LITERATURE: Lecture material and literature stated at lectures.

<p>

<b>59301 Biochemistry 				3,0</b> <b>ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Assoc. Prof.  Jaakko Puhakka<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: Biochemical phenomena and methods.<p>

CONTENTS: Biochemical compounds. Enzyme kinetics. Biochemical pathways.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Passed written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Additional reading to be announced during lectures.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>59302 Microbiology</b>  			<b>	3,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Assoc. Prof.  Jaakko Puhakka<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: Microbial processes and their importance in biotechnical applications.<p>

CONTENTS: Versatility of microorganisms. Micribial ecology. Cell structure. Metabolism. 
Microbial growth. Methods in microbiology.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Passed written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Additional reading to be announced at lectures.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>59303 Environmental Analysis</b> 	<b>	3,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<b>	Supervised also in English

</b><p>

Lecturer, Dr. (eng) Jukka Rintala<p>

Lectures 14 h. Exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: To be familar with the main analytical methods in environmental engineering.<p>

CONTENTS: Sampling. Environmental analyses. Interpretation of results. Standards and guidelines.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Passed written examination and exercises<p>

LITERATURE: Additional reading to be announced at lectures.<p>

<p>

<b>59312 Laboratory Excercises in		3,0 ECTS credits

 	Environmental Biotechnology  

	Supervised also in English</b><p>

<p>

Assoc. Prof.  Jaakko Puhakka<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: Ability to laboratory work , use experimental methods and to instrumental analysis.<p>

CONTENTS: Microbiological methods. Practical experiments  and measurements.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>59315 Biotechnical Processes in		3,0 ECTS credits <br>

      Environmental Engineering</b><p>

<p>

Assoc. Prof.  Jaakko Puhakka<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: To be acquainted with biotechnical processes and equipment in water, waste water and
solid waste treatment and in bioremediation of contaminated environments.<p>

CONTENTS: Design and operation of biochemical processes and equipment and their applications in water, wastewater and solid waste treatment.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Passed written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Additional reading to be announced at lectures.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>59317 Environmental Biotechology Biodegradation and 	3,0 ECTS credits<br>

	Bioremediation of Environmental Contaminants    	</b><p>

<p>

Assoc. Prof . Jaakko Puhakka<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: Synthetic chemical contaminants, their biotransformations, bioremediation.<p>

CONTENTS: Fate of synthetic chemical contaminants in water, wastewater and waste treatment
and in remediation of contaminated environments.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Passed written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Additional reading to be announced at lectures.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>59318 Special Issues in Env. Biotechnology</b> <b> 	3,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Assoc. Prof.  Jaakko Puhakka<p>

Lectures 14 h.  Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

