LITERATURE: Lecture material and literature stated at lectures.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>59319 Instrumental Analysis</b><p>

<p>

Lecturer, N.N.<p>

Lectures 28 h.<p>

Excercises 14 h.<p>

Time will be announced in the beginning of semester.<p>

<p>

OBJECTIVE: To give theoretical background and practical skills to use modern instruments for
analysis of environmental contaminants.<p>

CONTENTS: Gas chromatography, liquid chromatography, mass spectrometry, atomic
adsorption, spectroscopy (UV, IR, visible light), nuclear magnetic resonance.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Laboratory excercises, passed written examination.<p>

PREREQUISITES: 35135 Organic Chemistry, 35140 Lab. excercises of Org. Chemistry<p>

LITERATURE: To be announced at lectures.<p>

