<p>

Lecturer, N.N.<p>

Lectures 28 h. Excercises 14 h.<p>

Time will be announced in the beginning of semester.<p>

<p>

OBJECTIVE: To understand environmental effects of industrial and municipal air, water and soil
pollution on ecosystems and humans.<p>

CONTENTS: Sources of contaminants, chemical nature of contaminants, local, regional and
global effects on ecosystem and humans.<p>

DEGREE REQUIREMENTS: Written examination.<p>

PREREQUISITES: 35130 Organic Chemistry, 59301 Biochemistry, 59302 Microbiology<p>

<p>

<b>59400 Waste Management 		3,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Senior Lec. Simo Isoaho<p>

Lectures 24 h. Exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

