<a name="transport">
<h2>Transportation Engineering</h2>


<p>

<b>
56101 Introduction to Transportation Engineering</b>	<b>4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Senior Ass. Harri Rauham&auml;ki<p>

Lectures 56 h.<p>

Takes place during fall and spring terms. <p>

<p>

GOAL: To provide understanding of the structures, functions and social significance of different
transportation systems.<p>

CONTENTS: Basic knowledge of passenger and goods transportation, different modes of
transport, traffic economy, traffic safety, and environmental impacts of traffic. Modal split and
special features of different transport modes in Finland.<p>

A brief overview on traffic network planning.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Two written examinations.<p>

LITERATURE: Rauham&auml;ki, H., Korpinen, S.: Liikennetekniikan perusteet. Tampere 1995.
M&auml;kel&auml;, T., M&auml;ntynen, J.: Logistiikka ja kuljetukset. Tampere 1995.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>56221 Transportation Systems Planning</b>    	<b>	4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate Prof. Jorma M&auml;ntynen, M.Sc. Risto Laaksonen<p>

Senior Ass. Harri Rauham&auml;ki<p>

Lectures 28 h. Case studies 10 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: To provide skills needed for urban transportation systems planning and traffic planning in
practice. <p>

CONTENTS:  Transportation systems planning, traffic and land use, capacity and service levels of
the network, traffic flow theory, traffic forecasts, traffic planning software, street layout,
pedestrian and bicycle traffic, parking, traffic control, traffic safety, and special issues in urban
traffic environment. <p>

REQUIREMENTS: Participation in case studies and a written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Will be announced in lectures.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>56401 Public Transportation Systems</b>    		<b>4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate Prof. Jorma M&auml;ntynen<p>

M.Sc. Matti Rainio, M.Sc. Hanna Kalenoja<p>

Lectures 28 h, exercises.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: To provide knowledge of the characteristics, planning, and special features of local,
regional and long-distance public transportation systems. <p>

CONTENTS:  Characteristics of long-distance and local public transportation systems: buses,
trams, subways, trains, air traffic, and ferries. The planning of the networks, operators, and
facilities. Public transportation surveys. Service level factors and consumer preferences. Public
transportation in rural areas. Fare collection and information systems. Transportation permits and
legislation. Economy of public transportation. Public transportation as a part of the traffic system.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and a written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Taajamien joukkoliikenteen suunnittelu. Paikallisliikenneliitto, 1994.<p>

 <p>

<b>

56402 Transport Economics</b>   <b> 			4,5 ECTS credits

</b><p>

Associate Prof. Jorma M&auml;ntynen<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises. <p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: To provide understanding of structure and influencing factors of the economics of
transportation system. <p>

CONTENTS:  The significance of transportation in national economy, demand, supply and
pricing of transportation, economics of transportation infrastructure, evaluation of the benefits
and drawbacks of different modes of transport. <p>

REQUIREMENTS: Exercises and a written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: M&auml;ntynen, J., Pelkonen, H.: Liikennetalous. TTKK 1994.<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>56411 Environmental Impacts of Transportation </b>  	<b>4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate professor Jorma M&auml;ntynen<p>

M.Sc. Hanna Kalenoja<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: To provide understanding of the energy use and environmental effects of traffic as well as
knowledge of the methods of measuring and evaluating them. <p>

CONTENTS:  Energy consumption in traffic, exhaust emissions, noise, measuring methods,
controlling of the environmental impacts, emission regulations, EIA-legislation and life
cycleanalysis in transportation.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and a written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: M&auml;ntynen, J., Kalenoja, H.: Liikenteen ymp&auml;rist&ouml;vaikutukset. TTKK, liikenne ja
kuljetustekniikka.<p>

<p>

<b>

