<a name="institutes">
<h2>Description of the Institutes and Laboratories and
Their  Activities in the Department of Civil Engineering</h2>

<b>Institute of Structural Engineering</b><p>

<p>

	<b>Laboratory of Structural Engineering</b><p>

	Structures, their physical function, analysis and design.<p>

	Building materials.<p>

<p>

	<b>Laboratory of Structural Mechanics</b><p>

	Analysis of stress, strain, stability and bearing capasity of structures and structural systems.<p>

<p>

	<b>Laboratory of Geodesy and Photogrammetry</b><p>

	Geodesy and photogrammetry in the field of building construction and civil engineering.<p>

	Data processing and CAD for Civil engineering.<p>

<p>

	<b>Laboratory of Geotechnics</b><p>

	Geotechnical laboratory research methods, soil mechanichs, and foundation structures.<p>

	Developement of pile types and measurement of their bearing capasity.<p>

	Earth pressure and excavations.<p>

<p>

	<b>Laboratory of Engineering Geology</b><p>

	Composition and structure of rocks and soils from the point of view of building construction and
environment<p>

	Properities of mineral building materials<p>

<p>

<b>Institute of Construction Economics<p>

<p>

</b>Economics of construction planning and production.<p>

Enterpreneural and community economics.<p>

Enviromental economics and decision-making systems.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>Institute of Transportation Engineering<p>

<p>

</b>Traffic and transport planning and logistics.<p>

Passenger traffic.<p>

Goods transportation.<p>

<p>

<a name="course">
<h2>Courses Available in the Department of Civil Engineering</h2>

Mainly all of the courses in the Department of Civil Engineering are
taught in Finnish. Foreign students are encouraged to study the
subject concerned, for instance from books written in
English. Examinations can also be arranged individually, preferably in
English.<p>

<p>

! All the credit units are given in ECTS credits.<p>

<p>

<p>

<a name="structu">
<h2>Structural Mechanics</h2>
<b><p>

52200 Theory of plasticity	</b>		<b>4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Markku Tuomala<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h. <p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Basic principles of plasticity theory. Elastoplastic material properties. Elastoplastic
bending of beams. Fundamental theorems of limit analysis. Upper bound loads for beams and
frames by the method of combined mechanisms. Deformations in limit state. Minimum weight
design. Plasic torsion. Yield surface and yield condition. Slip-line field theory. Introduction to
limit load analysis of plates.<p>

REEQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Lecture notes, Neal: The Plastic Methods of Structural Analysis, Horne: Plastic
Theory of Structures. Calladine: Engineering Plasticity.<p>

<p>

<b><p>

52221  Framed Structures</b>			<b>4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Special Lecturer Antero Miettinen<p>

Lectures 42 h. Exercises 28 h. Project work 30 h. <p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Analysis of statically indeterminate beams and frames. Basic principles of solution
methods. Force method, displacement method. Finite element method. Influence lines.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises, project work and written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Lecture notes, Loikkanen: Rakenteiden statiikka I and II.<p>

<p>

<b><p>

52300 Applied Elasticity Theory			4,5 ECTS credits<p>

</b><p>

Prof. Markku Tuomala<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h. <p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Elastic analysis of beams and plates. Basic principles of elastic theory. Bending and
torsion of thin-walled beams. Thin plate theory, solutions of rectangular plates and plate strips by
Fourier-series and -transforms.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Parland: Rakenteiden v&auml;&auml;nt&ouml;. Mikkola: Levyjen, laattojen ja kuorien teoriaa.
Kollbrunner &amp; Hajdin: D&uuml;nnwandige St&auml;be, Band I. Timoshenko &amp; Woinowsky-Kriger: Theory
of Plates and Shells.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>52310 Numerical Methods in Structural Mechanics</b>	<b>4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Markku Tuomala<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h. Project work 42 h.<p>

Takes place in spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Basic principles of finite element method. Interpolation fuctions, formulation of
two-dimensional elements, plate elements, and their properties. Generation of analysis model and
applications in structural engineering.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises, project work and written examination.<p>

Literature: Cook &amp; al.: Concepts and Applications of Finite Element Analysis.<p>

NOTE: Lectured every second year, lectured during terms 1996-97.<p>

<p>

<b><p>

52321 Applications in Structural Mechanics</b>	<b>	4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Markku Tuomala<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place in spring term.<p>

 <p>

CONTENTS: Stiffening systems of structures and buildings. Combined structures. Layered
beams. Plastic analysis of reinforced concrete plates. Application of mathematical programming
methods to plastic analysis of structures.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Parland: Rakenteiden v&auml;&auml;nt&ouml;. Nielsen M.D.: Limit Analysis and Concrete
Plasticity.<p>

NOTE: Lectured every second year, not lectured during terms 1996-97.<p>

<p>

<b><p>

52340  Stability Theory of Structures</b>	<b>	4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Markku Tuomala<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place in spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Basic principles of structural stability and general methods for determining critical
buckling loads of structures. Buckling of bars and frames, flexural-torsional buckling and lateral
buckling of bars. Buckling of plates and shells.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Lecture notes, Timoshenko and Gere: Theory of Elastic Stability.<p>

NOTE: Lectured every second year, lectured during terms 1996-97.<p>

<p>

<b><p>

52400 Plate and Shell Structures</b>		<b>	4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Markku Tuomala<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place in spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Application of elasticity theory to analysis of discs, plates and shells. Circular plate.
Energy method and approximative solutions for plates. Orthotropic plate. Membrane stresses and
displacements, approximative solutions for bending stresses in axisymmetric shells.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Mikkola: Levyjen, laattojen ja kuorien teoriaa. Timoshenko &amp; Woinowsky-Kriger: Theory of Plates and Shells.<p>

NOTE: Lectured every second year, not lectured during terms 1996-97.<p>

<p>

<b><p>

52422  Seminar of Structural Mechanics		3,0 ECTS credits</b> <p>

<p>

Prof. Markku Tuomala<p>

Seminar exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Actual and important subject of structural mechanics. Written and oral presentation
based on literature review.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved seminar lectures and participation in seminar sessions.<p>

LITERATURE: According to topic of seminar.<p>

<p>

<b><p>

52440  Special work I of Structural Mechanics</b>	<b>	3,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Markku Tuomala<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Project work dealing with special subject of structural mechanics.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved written document of project work.<p>

LITERATURE: Based on subject of work.<p>

NOTE: May also be undertaken as team work.<p>

<p>

<b>52450 Special work II of Structural Mechanics		4,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

<b>52460 Special work III of Structural Mechanics		6,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

 <p>

Prof. Markku Tuomala,  See Special Work I above.<p>

<p>

<b>52480  Applications to Shell Theory</b>	<b>		4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Docent Paavo Tupam&auml;ki<p>

Lectures 28h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Modern treatment of general shell theory and applications for shells made of
different materials. Solution method based on finite difference method.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Tupam&auml;ki: Kuoriteorian sovellutuksia.<p>

NOTE: Lectured every second year, not lectured during terms 1996-97.<p>

