<a name="geology">
<h2>Engineering Geology</h2>
<b><p>

54105  Principles of Engineering Geology</b>		<b>4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate Prof. Raimo Uusinoka<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 20 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Identification of Quaternary sediments, rock forming minerals and rocks.
Introduction to physical properties of soils, environmental and ground water geology and
engineering-geological investigation methohods.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Lectures and Geomekaniikka I, RIL 157, chapters 1 and 2. Taipale, K. &amp;
Saarnisto, M.: Tulivuorista j&auml;&auml;kausiin, WSOY 1991.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>54110  Environmental Geology</b>	 		<b>4,5 ECTS credits<p>

</b><p>

Associate Prof. Raimo Uusinoka<p>

Lectures 28 h. Field and laboratory exercises 28 h. Planning 12 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Interaction of man and his geological environment. Geology in land use planning.
Ground water and its protection. Acid rain.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Lectures and Niini, H.: Geologia, tekniikka ja yhteiskunta. TKK-IGE, B18.<p>

<p>

<b><p>

54141 Engineering Geology of Rocks and Soils 		3,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate Prof. Raimo Uusinoka<p>

Lectures 21 h. Laboratory exercises 18 h. Field exercieses 6 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Technical properties of rocks. Engineering-geological classification of bedrock and
soils. Physical properties of soils.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Lectures and Blyth and Freitas: A Geology for Engineers 7. ed. Arnold, London,
or Legget and Hatheway: Geology for Engineers 3 ed. McGraw-Hill, New York 1988. Korhonen,
K-H. &amp; Gardemeister, R.: Maalajien kaivuluokitus. VTT/Geo, tiedonanto 1, 1975, Korhonen, K-H. &amp; Gardemeister, R.: Rakennusalan kallioluokitus, VTT/Geo, tiedonanto 12, 1974.<p>

<p>

<b><p>

54161 Bedrock Engineering and Road Building materials</b> 	<b>4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate Prof. Raimo Uusinoka<p>

Lectures 21 h. Exercises 14 h. Filed exercises 7 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Rock drillability. Site investigations of rock stores. Bedrock strengthening.
Vibration effect in blasting. Rock aggregates.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Lectures and special papers (to be informed in the course).<p>

REMARKS: Preliminary knowledge of the courses 54105 and 54141.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>54171 Advanced Course in Engineering Geology of Soils</b>	<b>6,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate Prof. Raimo Uusinoka<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 25 h. Filed exercises 7 h. Planning 20 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

