<p>

<a name="geotecnics">
<h2>Geotechnics</h2>
<p>

<p>

<b>55102 Soil Mechanics 				4,5 ECTS credits<p>

<p>

</b>Ass. Mauri Koskinen<p>

Lectures 28 h. Calculation exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: To familiarize the student with the strength and deformation behaviour of the soil and
applications of elasticity and plasticity theory in order to provide the student basic knowledge of
geotechnical design calculations.<p>

CONTENT: Mechanical properites of the soil. Geostatic stresses and stress distribution in the
ground. Applications of the elasticity theory in soil mechanics; soil deformations and compression,
and foundation settlement. Applications of the plasticity theory in soil mechanics; stability, bearing
capacity and earth pressure.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Accepted calculation exercises. A written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: Lectures and Geomekaniikka I and II (RIL 157-1 and 2)<p>

<b><p>

<p>

55106 Site and Laboratory Investigations 		3.0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Senior Ass. Pauli Kolisoja<p>

Lectures 28 h. Field and laboratory exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: To familiarize the student with the most common field and laboratory investigation
methods, the basics of the geotechnical design, typical foundation engineering structures and the
most important foundation engineering methods.<p>

CONTENTS: Field and laboratory investigation methods and equipment. Physical properties of
the soil. Hydraulic properties of the soil and soil frost. Content of the foundation plan, guidance of
planning and occupational safety. Footings and pile foundations and retaining walls. Foundation
engineering methods.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Participation to the field and laboratory exerices and a written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: Rantam&auml;ki M.: Geotekniikka. Bowles: Physical and Geotechnical Properties of
Soils. Geomekaniikka I (RIL 157-1)<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>55121 Computer Aided Dimensioning 		4,5 ECTS credits<p>

	 of Foundation Structures</b>    <p>

<p>

Ass. Mauri Koskinen<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

	 <p>

GOAL: To familiarize the student with the design of the typical foundation engineering structures
using computer software.<p>

CONTENTS: Actions and safety of foundation engineering structures. Modelling of the structures and ground using the computer software applications. Essential geotechnical design tasks in
building and road construction and municipal engineering; stability of embankments and slopes,
total and differential settlement of foundations, road embankments and pipe lines, and design of
excavations.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Accepted exerices, their presentation and a written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: Lectures and Geomekaniikka I-II (RIL 157). Pohjarakennusohjeet (RIL 121).
Rakennuskaivanto-ohje (RIL 181). Putkikaivanto-ohje (RIL 194). Hansbo S.: Jordmekanik I. <p>

<p>

<p>

<b>55131 Municipality Geotechnics 			6,0 ECTS c</b>r<b>edits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Jorma Hartikainen<p>

Lectures 42 h. Planning exercises 80 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: To familiarize the student with the role of geotechnics in the design of land use, municipal
geotechnical tasks and geotechnical design of the municipal services.<p>

CONTENTS: Geotechnics in the land use design of various societies. Preloading and deep
stabilization. Recording and utilization of soil investigation data. Soil and rock embankments.
Earth dams. Excavations. Pipe line foundations. <p>

REQUIREMENTS: Accepted design exerices. A written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: Lectures. Pohjarakennusohjeet (RIL 121), Ly&ouml;ntipaalutusohjeet (LPO-87).<p>

<b><p>

<p>

<p>

55140 Foundation Engineering Structures 		6,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Jorma Hartikainen<p>

Lectures 42 h. Planning exercises 80 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: To familiarize the student with the geotechnical engineering, design and construction of
foundation engineering structures.<p>

CONTENTS: Content of foundation engineering. Shallow foundations, especially raft foundations, pile foundations, especially large diameter and special piles. Drainage and frost
protection. Deep excavations. Foundations for harbour structures. Basics of geodynamics.
Machine foundations.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Accepted design exerices and a written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: Lectures. Pohjarakenteet (RIL 166). Pohjarakennusohjeet (RIL 121). Suurpaaluohjeet (SPO-78).<p>

<b><p>

<p>

55151 Underpinning				4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Prof. Jorma Hartikainen<p>

Lectures 28 h. Planning exercises 40 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: To familiarize the student with the design and implementation of underpinning.<p>

CONTENTS: Old foundation methods. Reasons leading to foundation rupture and need for
underpinning. Investigation of the condition of foundations. Foundation reparation and reinforcement methods. Deepening of foundations and use of special piles. Ground improvement.
Preventing the ground water lowering. Construction, supervison and observation measurements in
underpinning works.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Accepted design exerices and awritten exam.<p>

LITERATURE: Lectures. Korjausrakentaminen: perustukset (RIL 174,5).<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>55161-55164 Special Research Work in Geotechnics 	3,0-7,5 ECTS credits<p>

<p>

</b>Prof. Jorma Hartikainen<p>

<p>

GOAL: To familiarize the student with geotechnical investigation and design methods and the use
of literature and writing of a technical report. <p>

CONTENTS:  Complying a report based on literature or experimental work.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Accepted research work.<p>

<p>

<b>55180 Seminar in Geotechnics 			3,75 ECTS credits<p>

</b><p>

Prof. Jorma Hartikainen<p>

Seminar exercises 24 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: To cover actual geotechnical topics, changing each year, in lectures, guest lectures and
seminar presentations and to provide a discussion forum between students, lectures and practical
engineers. Post graduate and supplementing education can be compined to the basic education.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Seminar paper and 80 % presence.<p>

<p>

<b><p>

55222 Environmental Geotechnics 			4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Senior Ass. Pauli Kolisoja<p>

Lectures 42 h. Planning exercises 80 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<b><p>

<p>

</b>GOAL: To explain the role and means of geotechnics in environmental engineering. To present
geotechnical methods available in connection of ground and ground water protection and to
familiarize the student with geotechnical design of exploitation of polluted areas, and design of
placing and construction of polluted functions and protection structures.<p>

CONTENTS: Typical ground and water pollutants, their sources, propagation and effects, and
limit values. Investigation methods in environmental geotechnics. Effect of permeability on
pollutant transportation in the ground and its modelling. Design of waste dams. Protection
structures. Landfill design, structures and construction. Soil remediation and landscaping.
Purification methods of polluted soil. Use of waste materials in geotechnics. <p>

REQUIREMENTS: Accepted design exerices and a written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: Zadroga B.: Design of Landfill. Lectures and material distributed in the course.<p>

<p>

<b><p>

<a name="transport">
</b><h2>Transportation Engineering</h2>
<b><p>

<p>

56101 Introduction to Transportation Engineering</b>	<b>4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Senior Ass. Harri Rauham&auml;ki<p>

Lectures 56 h.<p>

Takes place during fall and spring terms. <p>

<p>

GOAL: To provide understanding of the structures, functions and social significance of different
transportation systems.<p>

CONTENTS: Basic knowledge of passenger and goods transportation, different modes of
transport, traffic economy, traffic safety, and environmental impacts of traffic. Modal split and
special features of different transport modes in Finland.<p>

A brief overview on traffic network planning.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Two written examinations.<p>

LITERATURE: Rauham&auml;ki, H., Korpinen, S.: Liikennetekniikan perusteet. Tampere 1995.
M&auml;kel&auml;, T., M&auml;ntynen, J.: Logistiikka ja kuljetukset. Tampere 1995.<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>56221 Transportation Systems Planning</b>    	<b>	4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate Prof. Jorma M&auml;ntynen<p>

M.Sc. Risto Laaksonen<p>

Senior Ass. Harri Rauham&auml;ki<p>

Lectures 28 h. Case studies 10 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: To provide skills needed for urban transportation systems planning and traffic planning in
practice. <p>

CONTENTS:  Transportation systems planning, traffic and land use, capacity and service levels of
the network, traffic flow theory, traffic forecasts, traffic planning software, street layout,
pedestrian and bicycle traffic, parking, traffic control, traffic safety, and special issues in urban
traffic environment. <p>

REQUIREMENTS: Participation in case studies and a written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Will be announced in lectures.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>56401 Public Transportation Systems</b>    		<b>4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate Prof. Jorma M&auml;ntynen<p>

M.Sc. Matti Rainio, M.Sc. Hanna Kalenoja<p>

Lectures 28 h, exercises.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: To provide knowledge of the characteristics, planning, and special features of local,
regional and long-distance public transportation systems. <p>

CONTENTS:  Characteristics of long-distance and local public transportation systems: buses,
trams, subways, trains, air traffic, and ferries. The planning of the networks, operators, and
facilities. Public transportation surveys. Service level factors and consumer preferences. Public
transportation in rural areas. Fare collection and information systems. Transportation permits and
legislation. Economy of public transportation. Public transportation as a part of the traffic system.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Approved exercises and a written examination.<p>

LITERATURE: Taajamien joukkoliikenteen suunnittelu. Paikallisliikenneliitto, 1994.<p>

