<p>

GOAL: To familiarize the students with the employers' and designers' main tasks, choices,
decision support systems and information sources in a civil engineering project.<p>

CONTENTS: Cost, value and profitability analyses with applications. Property systems for civil
engineering. Cost, value and profitability databases. Employer's, designer's and contractor's
processes. Student groups schedule a civil engineering project as their case exercise.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Exam on the essential literature in the beginning of the course. Case
exercises and report. Paper on current topic in Project Management. Final exam. <p>

