<b><p>

57230 Business Management </b> 		<b>	5,0 ECTS credits</b> <p>

<p>

Prof. Raimo Salokangas<p>

Senior Ass. Mauno Siev&auml;nen <p>

Lectures 20 h. Case exercises 40 h, exercises.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: To introduce the students to the main activities of a firm in a construction industry.
During the course the student should gain the skills and information necessary to set up a firm and
organize its procurement, production and marketing activities in Finland.<p>

CONTENTS: The major activities of a firm in a construction industry. Alternative legal forms of
an enterprise. Strategic planning. Procurement, production and marketing activities. Personnel
and materials administration, accounting, corporate planning and decision making. Starting a firm,
accounting, book keeping, preparing the annual reports, taxation and finance.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Exam covering the essential literature in the beginning of the course. Case
exercises and report. Paper on current topic in Business Management. Final exam. <p>

LITERATURE: To be announced later.<p>

