<b>57422-57425 Independent Study</b>		<b>	3-7,5 ECTS credits</b> <p>

<p>

Prof. Raimo Salokangas or other faculty members<p>

Takes place during fall or spring term. <p>

<p>

GOAL: To deepen the student's understanding and knowledge on special topics of construction
economics and management, and to provide experience and capabilities to an independent scientific work and the presentation of results. <p>

CONTENTS: Independent studies are often designed to serve current research projects at the
Institute of Construction Economics and Management. They can also be outlined to meet the special needs of an advanced student. Independent studies can  either emphasize empirical work and
practical problem solving, or they can focus on theoretical issues. The content and objectives of
an independent study should be outlined together with the guiding faculty member.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Individually accepted literature package and approved report/paper.<p>

