57840 Labour Law</b> 			 	<b>1,5 ECTS credits</b> <p>

<p>

Lecturer Tapio Kurkela<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

GOAL: To introduce the areas of labor law needed in the industrial management positions.<p>

CONTENTS: Acts on labor relations and issues. Contract of employment and employment.
Collective Agreements Act, the system of collective bargaining and duties to obey labor market
peace. Working Hours Act and Annual Leave Act. Occupational safety regulations. Acts on
industrial democracy and codetermination.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Active participation in lectures and final exam.Literature: Kairinen, Martti.
1991. Ty&ouml;oikeuden perusteet. Laajennettu ja uudistettu painos. Turku.<p>

