<b><p>

57995 Environmental Economics</b>			<b>3,0 ECTS credits</b> <p>

<p>

Prof. Raimo Salokangas<p>

M.Sc. (Eng) Juha Kaivonen<p>

Visiting lecturers <p>

Takes place during spring term. <p>

	<p>

GOAL: The objective of the course is to familiarize the students with the most central theoretical
topics in environmental economics and management.<p>

CONTENTS: Macromodels focusing on economy and environment, microeconomic theory
explaining pollution and exhaustion of natural resources, instruments of environmental policy and
their economic analysis, economic valuation of environmental goods, principles of benefit cost
analysis and environmental impact assessment, and environmental business management.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Exam covering the essential literature in the beginning of the course.
Personal or group paper. Final exam covering lectures and literature. <p>

Literature: 1) Pearce, David and R. Kerry Turner. 1990. Economics of Natural Resources and the
Environment. New York and London: Harvester Wheatsheaf. Chapters 1-13. 2) Pedersen, Bo
(ed.). 1993. Planning a Life Cycle Assessment. Helsinki: UETP-EEE and the Finnish Associate of
Graduate Engineers TEK. 3) Coursepack containing 250-300 pp. articles on various themes of
environmental economics and management.<p>

<p>

<a name="geodesy">
<h2>Geodesy and Photogrammetry</h2>
<p>

<b>58100 Fundamentals of Surveying</b>			<b>4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate Prof: Hannu Salmenper&auml;<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 42 h.<p>

Takes place during fall and spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Basic geodetic instruments and survey methods. Principles of photogrammetry.
Principles of error theory and survey computations. Review of mapping activities, map production
and cadastral systems in Finland.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: An intermediate exam, laboratory and field exercises, survey computations
and their reporting, and a final written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: H. Salmenper&auml;: Rakennusmittausten perusteet.<p>

NOTES: Passed intermediate exam after the first lecture session is pre-requisite for the laboratory
and field exercises.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>58111 General Course in Surveying and</b>	<b>	3,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<b>Photogrammetry<p>

</b><p>

Associate Prof: Hannu Salmenper&auml;<p>

Lectures 28 h, exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Geodetic and photogrammetric methods used in the inventory and planning of
community and civil engineering projects. Special emphasize is on photogrammetry. Review of
environmental information systems and databases.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Laboratory and field exercises, survey computations and their reporting, and
a written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: H. Salmenper&auml;: Fotogrammetria. T.J.M. Kennie and G. Petrie: Engineering
Surveying Technology (chapters 1, 6, 7, and 11). <p>

<p>

<b><p>

58121 Surveying in Highway and Water Engineering	3,0 ECTS credits</b> <p>

<p>

Associate Prof: Hannu Salmenper&auml;<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Geodetic and photogrammetric control surveys. Satellite surveying. Digital
elevation model. Geometric design of roads. Site surveys and setting out. Areas and volumes.
Underground surveying. Hydrographic surveying.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Laboratory and field exercises, survey computations and their reporting, and
a written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: H. Salmenper&auml;: Maa-, vesi- ja kalliorakentamisen mittaukset. T.J.M. Kennie and
G. Petrie: Engineering Surveying Technology (chapters 2, 3, 4, and 10). TKK, Geodesian
laboratorio 20/1991: Numeerisen kartoituksen maastomittausohjeet.<p>

NOTES: The course 58111 General Course in Surveying and Photogrammetry is pre-requisite for
58121.<p>

<p>

<b><p>

58131 Construction Surveying</b>		<b>	3,0 ECTS credits<p>

<p>

</b>Associate Prof: Hannu Salmenper&auml;<p>

Lectures 28 h, exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Survey instruments and methods for building construction. Principles of building
tolerances. Survey standards. Planning for site surveys. Control surveys. Duties and surveys by
local authority. Geometry of plans and drawings. Setting out. Areas and volumes. Surveys for the
renovation of buildings.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Laboratory and field exercises, survey computations and their reporting, and
a written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: H. Salmenper&auml;: Talonrakennuksen mittaukset. M. Martikainen ja J. Santala:
Rakennusmittaus. J. van den Berg and &Aring;. Lindberg: Measuring Practice on the Building Site.
SFS-ISO Standards 3443-3, 4463-1, 7976-1, and 7976-2.<p>

<p>

<b><p>

58141 Deformation Measurements</b>	<b>		3,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate Prof. Hannu Salmenper&auml;<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Survey instruments and methods for deformation measurements. Error theory.
Analysis and adjustment of survey measurements. Planning for deformation measurements.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Laboratory and field exercises, survey computations and their reporting, and
a written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: H. Salmenper&auml;: Valvonta- ja muodonmuutosmittaukset. P. Laurila: Satunnaisvirheiden kasautuminen ja tasoituslaskenta.<p>

NOTES: The course is offered every other year, offered in 1996-97.<p>

<b><p>

<p>

58161 Surveying, Special Assignments</b>		<b>3,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

<b>58170 Surveying, Special Assignments</b>	<b>	7,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate Prof: Hannu Salmenper&auml;<p>

Exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during fall and spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Topics on geodesy, photogrammetry, and engineering surveying based on
literature, laboratory works, or field surveys.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Written report.<p>

LITERATURE: Depends on the topic.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>58181 Surveying, Seminar</b>		 	<b>3,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate Prof: Hannu Salmenper&auml;<p>

Exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during fall and spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Seminar topics on geodesy, photogrammetry, and engineering surveying based on
literature, special assignments, and final projects.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Written report, oral presentation, and attendance of seminar sessions.<p>

LITERATURE: Depends on the topic.<p>

<p>

<b><p>

58200 Remote Sensing and GIS</b>		<b>	3,0 ECTS credits<p>

<p>

</b>Associate Prof: Hannu Salmenper&auml;<p>

Lectures 14 h. Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Principles of remote sensing techniques and image interpretation. Earth resources
satellites. Photogrammetric methods. Applications for the inventory of earth resources and
environmental monitoring. Geographical and environmental information systems and databases.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Laboratory exercises and their reporting, and awritten exam.<p>

LITERATURE: Lillesand and Kiefer: Remote Sensing and Image Interpretation.<p>

NOTES: The course is intended to the students of environmental engineering. <p>

<p>

<b><p>

58210 GIS in Transportation</b>		<b>	3,0 ECTS credits<p>

<p>

</b>Associate Prof: Hannu Salmenper&auml;<p>

Lectures 14 h. Exercises 14 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Principles of positioning systems and geographical information systems. Satellite
navigation. Inertial navigation. Geographical information systems and databases. Management of
databases. Applications for transportation and construction.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: A written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: Lecture notes and a collection of articles.<p>

NOTES: The course is intended to the students of transportation engineering.<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>58220 Measurement of Large Structures</b>		<b>4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate Prof: Hannu Salmenper&auml;<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 42 h.<p>

Takes place during fall and spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Survey instruments and methods for large structures in the dimension of 1...100 m.
Coordinate systems. Measurement of angles, distances, and height differences. Coordinate based
measurements. Control surveys. As built surveys. Principles of error theory and survey
computations.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: An intermediate exam, laboratory and field exercises, survey computations
and their reporting, and a final written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: H. Salmenper&auml;: Rakennusmittausten perusteet (partly), lecture notes and
collection of articles.<p>

NOTES: Passed intermediate exam after the first lecture session is pre-requisite for the laboratory
and field exercises. The first lecture session will be arranged together with the course 58100
Fundamentals of Surveying. The course is intented to the students of mechanical engineering.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>58501 Application Programs</b>	 	<b>	3,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate Prof: Hannu Salmenper&auml; (contact person)<p>

Exercises 28 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: User education for various application programs, as Excel, Hardvard Graphics, and
2d-CAD (AutoCAD for Windows).<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Attendance of exercise sessions.<p>

NOTES: The course is arranged by Tampereen teknillinen ammattikorkeakoulu. The place for the
exercises depends on the number of students. <p>

<p>

<p>

<b>58511 Computer Aided Design</b> 		<b>	4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate Prof: Hannu Salmenper&auml; (contact person)<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 35 h.<p>

Takes place during fall term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Theory of product data model and its applications for building construction.<p>

Relational databases. Application and exercise environment is based on Ingres relational database
program, AES CAD system, and UNIX work stations.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Exercises and a written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: M. Laiho: Relaatiotietokannat. Bj&ouml;rk, Penttil&auml; ja Karstila: Rakenuksen
tuotemallin teoria ja sen sovellukset. AES Manuals.<p>

NOTES: The course 58501 Application Programmes is recommended as pre-requisite for 58511.<p>

<p>

<b>58521 CAD-Applications and Programming</b> 	<b>	4,5 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate Prof: Hannu Salmenper&auml; (contact person)<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 35 h.<p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Fundamentals of programming and computer graphics as applied to civil
engineering. Methods of software engineering. CAD systems. AutoCAD. Programming in C.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Programming exercises and a written exam.<p>

LITERATURE: Silpi&ouml;: C-kieli. ADS Programmers Reference Manual.<p>

NOTES: The course 58511 Computer Aided Design or 58501 Application Programs is pre-requisite for 58521.<p>

<p>

<p>

<b>58531 Special project in CAD </b>		<b>	3,0 ECTS credits</b><p>

<p>

Associate Prof: Hannu Salmenper&auml; (contact person)<p>

Lectures 28 h. Exercises 28 h. <p>

Takes place during spring term.<p>

<p>

CONTENTS: Programming of CAD- and database systems. User interfaces. Programming in C in
AutoCAD-environment.<p>

REQUIREMENTS: Large programming work.<p>

LITERATURE: B. Kerninghan. The C Programming Language. AutoCAD-R12 Manuals: ADS
Programmers Reference Manual, SQL Extension Reference Manual, and AutoCAD Mukautusk&auml;sikirja.<p>

NOTES: The course 58521 CAD-Applications and Programming is pre-requisite for 58531.<p>
<IMG WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=14 SRC="images/BlueLine.gif" ALT="- - -"><BR>
