<HTML>
 <HEAD>
 <TITLE>Departements of TUT - Materials science</TITLE>
 </HEAD>
 <BODY
  BACKGROUND=""
  BGCOLOR="#ffffff"
  TEXT="#000000"
  LINK="#F00000"
  VLINK="#F00000"
 >
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 VALIGN=TOP>
<A HREF="default.htm">
<IMG WIDTH=321 HEIGHT=44 SRC="images/InternationalOfficeSmall.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="International Office">
</A><BR><BR>
<TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=170>
<A HREF="default.htm"><IMG WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BtnMainPageNorm.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="Main page"></A><BR>
<A HREF="info.htm"><IMG WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BtnInformationNorm.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="Information"></A><BR>
<A HREF="studies.htm"><IMG WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BtnStudiesSel.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="Studies at TUT"></A><BR>
<A HREF="courseguide.htm"><IMG WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BtnCourseGuideNorm.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="Course guide"></A><BR>
<A HREF="contact.htm"><IMG WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BtnContactNorm.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="Contact information"></A><BR>
<IMG WIDTH=136 HEIGHT=10 SRC="images/BlueLineShort.gif" ALT=""><BR>
<A HREF="international.htm"><IMG WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BtnUlkomailleNorm.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="Ulkomaille"></A><BR>
<IMG WIDTH=136 HEIGHT=10 SRC="images/BlueLineShort.gif" ALT=""><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.tut.fi/cgi-bin/cgiwrap/~kvweb/aglimpse"><IMG WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BtnSearch.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="Search"></A><BR>
</TD>
<TD VALIGN=TOP>
<DL>
<P><DT>
<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica">
<H2>
<A HREF ="http://www.tut.fi/~materwww/">MATERIALS SCIENCE</A>
</H2>
</FONT>
The program of  Materials Science gives a detailed view into structure and properties of
materials, including metals, ceramics and  polymers and their composites and provides a
solid basis for studies in materials  science.  <P>

Facilities and equipment are available for  structural characterization and for  studies of
properties and applications  of materials.<P>

Research at the Institute of  Materials  Science focuses on the development of materials
and materials combinations for a variety of different applications ranging from human
implants to advanced materials    for power engineering. It includes  fundamental as well
as applied research carried out mainly as combinations of these works for different
academic degrees, but partially also as discrete work by itself. International collaboration
covers most of the industrialized countries.<P>

<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica">
<H3>
Individual studies and research in fiber, textile and clothing science:
</H3>
</FONT>

The Institute of Fiber, Textile and Clothing Science (IFTCS) is under the Department of
Material Technology, which also includes general materials technology, plastics technology,
chemistry and electron microscopy. The IFTCS educates, trains and conducts research. The
research and service areas in brief: fiber research, mechanical production of textiles, chemical
treatment of textile materials, textile recycling and reuse, biotechnology in textile processes,
standard tests on fibers, yarns and fabrics, CAD, technical and economic aspects of the textile
and clothing industry, manufacture of trial lots. The training for the M.Sc (Eng) takes 5 to 7
years and the course consists of general studies, textile specialist studies and a Master's thesis. It
is possible to continue with postgraduate academic studies leading to the Licentiate and the
Doctorate in Technology. The prerequisite for a student applying as a visiting student is a
minimum of three year's academic studies or a Bachelor's degree in the field.
<P>
<UL type=disc>
<li><a href="http://www.tut.fi/units/ms/biom/">Institute of Biomaterials</a>
<li><a href="http://www.tut.fi/units/ms/elm/cem.html">Electron Microscopy</a>
<li><A HREF="http://www.tut.fi/units/ms/mol/">Materials Science</A>
<li><a href="http://www.tut.fi/units/ms/foundry/">Foundry Institute</a>
<li><A HREF="http://www.tut.fi/units/ms/teva/">Fiber, Textile and Clothing Science</A>
<li><a href="http://www.tut.fi/units/ms/muo/index_en.html">Plastics Technology</a>
<li><a href="http://www.tut.fi/units/ymp/kem/index_en.html">Materials Chemistry</a>
</UL>
<P>
</DL>
<IMG WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=14 SRC="images/BlueLine.gif" ALT="- - -"><P>
<A HREF="osasto1.htm">
<IMG WIDTH=95 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BackButton.gif" ALT="<- Back" BORDER=0>
</A>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
