<TD VALIGN=TOP>
<DL>
<P><DT>
<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica">
<H2>
<A HREF ="http://www.tut.fi/ttkk.koti/units.html">ENVIRONMENTAL ENGINEERING</A>
</H2>
</FONT>
The program in Environmental Engineering is aimed at senior undergraduate and first-year
graduate students in Environmental Engineering or related studies. The program offers
courses in water supply,    wastewater treatment, environmental biotechnology, waste
management, safety engineering, energy technology and  management and applied process
technology.  The students can specialize flexibly by selecting  studies from other available
training  programs.
<P>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.tut.fi/units/me/ener/">Energy and Process Engineering</A>
<li><a href="http://www.tut.fi/units/ymp/kem/index_en.html">Materials Chemistry</a>
<LI><A HREF="http://turva.me.tut.fi/">Occupational Safety Engineering</A>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.tut.fi/units/ymp/pap/index.htm">Paper Converting Technology</A>
<li><A HREF="http://www.tut.fi/units/ymp/ves/index_en.html">Water and Environmental Engineering</A>
<P>
</DL>
<IMG WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=14 SRC="images/BlueLine.gif" ALT="- - -"><P>
<A HREF="osasto1.htm">
<IMG WIDTH=95 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BackButton.gif" ALT="<- Back" BORDER=0>
</A>
