<HEAD>
<TITLE>Requirements</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<!--
maaritellaan sivun parametrit:
        ei taustakuvaa
        valkoinen tausta
        musta teksti
        punaiset linkit
-->
<BODY
 BACKGROUND=""
 BGCOLOR="#ffffff"
 TEXT="#000000"
 LINK="#F00000"
 VLINK="#F00000"
>

<!-- Using a table makes it easier to construct -->

<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 VALIGN=TOP>
<A HREF="default.htm"><IMG WIDTH=321 HEIGHT=44 SRC="images/InternationalOfficeSmall.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="International Office"></A><BR><BR>

<!-- Taulukon ensimmainen, ja ainoa rivi -->
<TR>
<!-- eka sarake, leveys fiksattu kuvien mukaiseksi -->
<TD VALIGN=TOP WIDTH=170>
<!--
linkkinapit. kuvan nimi loppuu Norm, jos se on linkki ja Sel jos se on "selected", eli ollaan juurikin
silla sivulla
-->
<A HREF="default.htm"><IMG WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BtnMainPageNorm.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="Main page"></A><BR>
<A HREF="info.htm"><IMG WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BtnInformationNorm.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="Information"></A><BR>
<A HREF="studies.htm"><IMG WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BtnStudiesSel.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="Studies at TUT"></A><BR>
<A HREF="courseguide.htm"><IMG WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BtnCourseGuideNorm.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="Course guide"></A><BR>
<A HREF="contact.htm"><IMG WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BtnContactNorm.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="Contact information"></A><BR>
<IMG WIDTH=136 HEIGHT=10 SRC="images/BlueLineShort.gif" ALT=""><BR>
<A HREF="international.htm"><IMG WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BtnUlkomailleNorm.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="Ulkomaille"></A><BR>
<IMG WIDTH=136 HEIGHT=10 SRC="images/BlueLineShort.gif" ALT=""><BR>
<A HREF="http://www.tut.fi/cgi-bin/cgiwrap/~kvweb/aglimpse"><IMG WIDTH=150 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BtnSearch.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="Search"></A><BR>

</TD>
<!-- toinen sarake, johon tulee varsinainen leipateksti, leveytta ei ole asetettu -->
<TD VALIGN=TOP>
<!-- sisennysta varten tarvitaan DefinitionList -->
<DL>
<!-- uusi kappale aloitetaan P-DT yhdistelmalla -->
<P><DT>
<!-- Otsikoiden fontiksi arial/helvetica, koska se nayttaa paremmalta -->
<!-- Huomaa myos englanninkielelle tyypillinen otsikoiden capitalisointi -->
<FONT FACE="Arial, Helvetica">
<H1>
Admission Requirements For M.Sc.-level Studies
</H1>
</FONT>
<!-- sisennys tapahtuu DD-tagilla -->
<DD>
I.Please note that Tampere University of Technology selects foreign students
mainly for the International University Programs in which the language of instruction
is English. The courses are Digital Signal Processing, Materials Science and Biomedical
Engineering.<P>

A foreign student wishing to study at TUT is recommended to apply for these International
University Programs. After one year's successful studies at TUT as an international
non-degree student, the student can apply for a degree program.<P>

<DL><DT>
To be considered for admis-sion (M.Sc-level) they must meet the following re-quirements:
<dd>
<LI>3 - 4 years of university-level studies or the degree of B.Sc.
<LI>a certificate of proficiency in English language (=TOEFL)
<LI>to be financially self-supporting (the University will not grant scho-larships).<P>
</DL>
More information about these International University Programs and requirements you can
find in a special information leaflet.<P>

The deadline of the applications for International University Programs is March 31st for
Fall term and September 30th for Spring term.<P>

<ul type=disk>
<li><A HREF="iup.ps">Application for International University Programs</a><br>
<li><A HREF="ugs.ps">Application for foreign students Undergraduate studies for M. Sc. degree</a>
</ul>
<br>You can also order application from IO.
<p>

Applications should be sent to:<P>
<DL><DT>
<DD>International Office
<DD>Tampere University of Technology
<DD>P.O.Box 527, 33101 Tampere
<DD>FINLAND</DL>
<P>

II.In very few special cases foreign students can apply for Tampere University of
Technology without passing the entrance examinations.<P>

To be considered for admission (M.Sc-level) they must meet the following re-quirements:<P>
<DL><DT>
<dd><LI>3 - 4 years of university-level studies or the degree of B.Sc.
<dd><LI>a working knowledge of Finnish language and a certificate of proficiency in English language (=TOEFL)
<dd><LI>to be financially self-supporting (the University will not grant scho-larships).<p>
</DL>
Therefore foreign students must send the following documents to the International Office
of TUT:<P>
<DL><DT>
<dd><LI>an application form (the student will get this form from the International Office of TUT on request)
<dd><LI>a transcript of credits taken at another university (or equivalent institution) and a copy of the B.Sc. degree and their English translation
<dd><LI>a certificate of proficiency in English language (=TOEFL). Please note TUT does not have a TOEFL Code number of its own!
<dd><LI>letters of recommendation
<dd><LI>an official proof of financial support signed by the parent, the guardian, the employer or by the organisation by which a scholarship has been granted.<P>
</DL>

III. Foreign students wishing to study for a M.Sc. degree at Tampere University of
Technology (not having a B.Sc. degree or equivalent) must have a good knowledge of Finnish
language and they are required to pass the entrance examinations before admittance to the
University.<P>

To pass the entrance examinations and to be considered for admission (M.Sc-level) foreign
students must meet the following requirements:<P>
<DL><DT>
<DD><LI>they must have finished their upper secondary school education with good grades and taken a final examination (Bacca-laureat, Abitur, GCE, A-level or equivalent)
<DD><LI>a good knowledge of Finnish language and a certificate of proficiency in English language (=TOEFL)
<DD><LI>to be financially self-supporting (The University will not grant scho-larships).<P>
</DL>
To apply for addmission foreign students must send the following documents to the
International Office of TUT:<P>
<DL><DT>
<DD><LI>an application form [a special pink one with information about the entrance examinations] (the student will receive this form from the International Office of TUT on request)
<DD><LI>a copy of grades of school education and/or other education (and their English translations)
<DD><LI>a copy of grades of the final examination (Baccalaureat, Abitur, GCE, A-level or equivalent) and their English translations
<DD><LI>a certificate of Finnish language (The courses at TUT are given only in Finnish with very few exeptions and therefore a good knowledge of Finnish language is required when studying for the primary academic degree (M.Sc.)
<DD><LI>a certificate of proficiency in English language (=TOEFL)
<DD><LI>letters of recommendation
<DD><LI>an official proof of financial support signed by the parent, the guardian, the employer or by organisation by which a shcolarship has been granted.
</DL>
<P>
The deadline for all undergraduate applications for all degree programs is January 31st.

<DL><DT>
<p>
<ul type=disk>
<li><A HREF="exstud.ps">International Exchange Student Application Form</a>
</ul>
<br>You can also order application from IO.
<p>
Applications should be sent to:<P>
<DD>International Office
<DD>Tampere University of Technology
<DD>P.O.Box 527, FIN-33101 Tampere,
<DD>FINLAND<P>
</DL>

Applications will not be processed at all if all the required documents are not
received by 31st January. Documents can be submitted in Finnish, Swedish or English.
All copies and translations must be officially certified, and, please, all documents
should be sent together and in the same envelope.<P>
</DL>
<!-- sopivaan valiin voi iskea sinisen viivan erottamaan asioita toisistaan -->
<IMG WIDTH=400 HEIGHT=14 SRC="images/BlueLine.gif" ALT="- - -"><P>
<A HREF="regu.htm">
<IMG WIDTH=95 HEIGHT=35 SRC="images/BackButton.gif" ALT="<- Back" BORDER=0>
</A>
