<HTML>
<HEAD>
	<TITLE>
		Ron Arad - Artical
	</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="/Images/head-know.gif" >
</CENTER>
<PRE>
                        (C) The Jerusalem Post 1992
                        Wednesday, January 5, 1994



Source: BATSHEVA TSUR


        FAMILIES OF MIAS DISAPPOINTED AFTER MEETING WITH HURD


FAMILIES of the IDF soldiers missing in action in Lebanon came
out of a meeting yesterday with British Foreign Secretary Douglas Hurd
"disappointed," according to the father of one of the boys.

"We have to try everything," said Yona Baumel, father of Zacharya
Baumel, missing since the battle of Sultan Ya'acoub, "so we requested
[Secretary Douglas] Hurd's good offices.  But we had the feeling that
both sides were merely going through the motions.

"There was no real interest on the part of the secretary," Baumel
said, adding that Hurd had "failed to follow up on commitments to
British Jewry [on this subject] on previous occasions."

The meeting with Hurd, held at the Foreign Ministry, was also
attended by the parents of Yossi Fink, Rahamim Alsheik and Zvi
Feldman.

Hurd then met separately with the mother and brother of missing
Air Force navigator Ron Arad.

For his part, the secretary twice referred to the plight of the
Israeli MiAs yesterday at news conferences with the media.

In reply to a question before his meeting with the families, Hurd
said: "I have raised the issue from time to time, in confidence, with
people whom I thought might be of help." He added that he had noted
Prime Minister's Rabin's statement that there was nothing to say about
the subject "unless it was definite."

Speaking later in the day, Hurd added that he had met with many
human tragedies in the Middle East.  "Only today I spoke with the
families of the MiAs.  One can imagine what they have gone through ...
I shall continue to speak of them whenever possible and sensible."



</PRE>
<CENTER>
<P><A HREF="http://www.macom.co.il"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/Images/macom.gif" ></A>
</CENTER>
