<HTML>
<HEAD>
	<TITLE>
		Ron Arad - Artical
	</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="/Images/head-know.gif" >
</CENTER>
<PRE>
                        (C) The Jerusalem Post 1992
                        Tuesday, April 26, 1994



Source: DAVID MAKOVSKY, MOSCOW


        RABIN: ARAD BEING HELD BY IRAN OR ITS SURROGATES


DOWNED IAF navigator Ron Arad is being held either by Iran or by
its supporters in Lebanon, Prime Minister Yitzhak Rabin said yesterday
at a meeting with Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin.

Rabin also told the Russian premier that PLO Chairman Yasser
Arafat had promised him more information about Israeli MiAs, but has
not been forthcoming, apparently fearing it would complicate his
relations with Syria, said Rabin advisers who attended the meeting.

Yesterday's remarks by Rabin contradict a statement by Foreign
Minister Shimon Peres last week that Arafat had done everything
possible to obtain information on Israel's missing soldiers.  Several
months ago, Arafat handed Israeli officials half a dog-tag belonging
to Zacharia Baumel, who went missing in Lebanon during the 1982 battle
at Sultan Yakoub.

Rabin's statements about Arad come just days after Iranian
Foreign Minister Ali Akbar Velayati told an Army Radio correspondent
in Bucharest that Arad is not being held on Iranian soil.

According to an adviser to Rabin, the premier told Chernomyrdin
that "Arad is being held by Iran or Iranian elements in Lebanon." He
refused to reveal whether Rabin had referred to the Iranian
Revolutionary Guards still deployed in the Bekaa valley, or the
Hizbullah in southern Lebanon.

When asked to use his influence with Iran and Syria, Chernomyrdin
issued a personal pledge of support, participants said.



</PRE>
<CENTER>
<P><A HREF="http://www.macom.co.il"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/Images/macom.gif" ></A>
