</CENTER>
<PRE>
                        (C) The Jerusalem Post 1992
                        Thursday, September 19, 1991



Source: ALON PINKAS

          Arens.  Israel.  IDF.

        ARENS: NO NEW DATA ON MIAS


The negotiations on the five Israeli MiA's still missing are
stalled, Defense Minister Moshe Arens told Israel Television last
night.

Arens said in a Mabat interview that chief negotiator Uri
Lubrani's meetings with UN Secretary-General Javier Perez de Cuellar
did not produce new information on the whereabouts of IAF navigator
Ron Arad, believed to be alive and held by a pro-Iranian group in
Lebanon.

Israel is also seeking information on the three missing Armor
Corps soldiers - Zacharia Baumel, Yehuda Katz and Zvi Feldman - who
disappeared in the battle of Sultan Yacoub in June 1982.

Arens reiterated Israel's position on Sheik Abdel Karim Obeid,
the Shi'ite cleric from Lebanon, saying he is the strongest bargaining
chip Israel now has vis-a-vis the Shi'ite groups.



</PRE>
