<PRE>
                        (C) The Jerusalem Post 1992
                        Monday, May 6, 1991



Source: Jerusalem Post Staff

          Fink.  Rahamim Levi Alshech.  Hizbullah.

        ISRAEL SET TO AID HOSTAGES' RELEASE IF POWS INCLUDED


The government is prepared to contribute to the release of
Western hostages in Lebanon if IDF PoWs are among those released, the
Defense Ministry announced last night.

Responding to media pressure on Israel to take some action to aid
the Western hostages' release, Defense Ministry spokesman Danny Naveh
said that the government has in the past expressed its willingness to
help with their release and has even made gestures towards that end on
the condition that Israeli PoWs and MIAs be included among the
released.

Israel has seven PoWs and MIAs in Lebanon, including Ron Arad who
is in Iranian hands and Yosef Fink and Rahamim Levi Alshech who are
being held by the Iranian-sponsored Hizbullah.

"The Israelis' captors refuse to act according to elementary
rules of human behavior and the international conventions requiring
that information about them and proof that they are alive be provided
and that the captors give the Red Cross access to them," Naveh said.
"Israel repeats its call to all those elements holding its prisoners
and Western hostages to allow the Red Cross access to them and to
enter negotiations to bring about their immediate release.  In this
framework, Israel will be ready to negotiate the release of Lebanese
detainees being held in Israel."



</PRE>
