</CENTER>
<PRE>
                        (C) The Jerusalem Post 1992
                        Friday, April 12, 1991



Source: Jerusalem Post Staff and New Agencies

          Palestinian.  Prison.  Abdel Karim Obeid.

        ISRAEL SHOULD FREE ARABS FOR HOSTAGES, SAYS HIZBULLAH


A Lebanese fundamentalist leader has said that Western hostages
would be freed if Israel released all Arabs it has captured in
Lebanon.

"What is required is a general pardon on all Lebanese and
Palestinian prisoners captured by Israel on Lebanese soil," Hussein
Musawi, a leader of Hizbullah, said in a speech late on Wednesday in
the eastern town of Mashgara.

The South Lebanese Army - together with Israel, according to some
reports - is said to be holding hundreds of Lebanese and Palestinians
from Lebanon prisoner.  In July 1989, Israeli snatched Hizbullah
leader Shekh Abdel Karim Obeid from his base in South Lebanon and
transported him to an Israeli prison.  Obeid has featured prominently
in reports of possible tradeoffs involving the Hizbullah and Israel.

Israel has reportedly indicated willingness to trade prisoners
for captives, but wants at least three missing Israel servicemen
included in any deal: Nahal soldiers Yossi Fink and Rahmin Alsheikh as
well as IAF navigator Ron Arad, who have been held since 1986.  Arad
is reportedly in the hands of Amal, a rival Shi'ite group.  At least
four other Israeli servicemen have been mentioned in reports as being
held in Lebanon.



</PRE>
