<PRE>
                        (C) The Jerusalem Post 1992
                        Sunday, September 24, 1989



Source: By DAVID HOROVITZ, Jerusalem Post Reporter


        IRAN SAID READY FOR HOSTAGE DEAL


LONDON - Iran is reported to be prepared this week to propose a
hostage-exchange deal, offering the release of all Western hostages in
Lebanon and captured Israeli navigator Ron Arad in return for Sheik
Abdul Karim Obeid and 500 Israeli-held prisoners, according to a press
report today.

The Sunday Times claims that Iranian president Ali Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani will pass details of the proposals to the Bush
administration this week.  Apart from Obeid and the 500 Lebanese and
Palestinian detainees, he is also reportedly seeking the unfreezing of
$6 billion in Iranian assets held in the U.S.

Rafsanjani is said to have decided on a policy of "opening up to
the West" - but today's report claims Islamic extremists are doing
their utmost to undermine him.



</PRE>
<CENTER>
<P><A HREF="http://www.macom.co.il"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/Images/macom.gif"></A>
