<PRE>
                        (C) The Jerusalem Post 1992
                        Sunday, August 20, 1989



Source: By DAVID HOROVITZ, Jerusalem Post Correspondent


        PAPER SAYS ISRAEL NEGOTIATING FOR REMAINS OF TWO SOLDIERS


LONDON - Acting on the belief that missing soldiers Joseph Fink
and Rahamim Alshech are dead, Israel has entered into negotiations
intended to secure the return of their bodies, "The Sunday Times"
claimed today.

The British newspaper, which last week published the hotly-denied
report that Israel had "concluded" that the two died within hours of
their ambush in south Lebanon in February 1986, said that "a secret
channel of communications has been reactivated for the negotiations."

The Israelis, it added, were also demanding the release of air
force navigator Ron Arad, shot down over Sidon in October 1986.



</PRE>
