<PRE>
                        (C) The Jerusalem Post 1992
                        Monday, June 6, 1994



Source: YIGAL KOTZER

          Mustafa Dirani.  Perception.

        RABIN: RON ARAD STILL CONSIDERED PRISONER


PRIME Minister Yitzhak Rabin said yesterday that IAF navigator
Ron Arad is still considered to be missing in action and a prisoner.

"I cannot say with certainty that Ron Arad is not alive, and thus
his position is that of a prisoner who is missing in action.  And as
long as it is not proved otherwise, for me he is still alive," Rabin
said at Haifa University, where he received an honorary doctorate.

Rabin said abducted Shi'ite leader Mustafa Dirani is talking to
interrogators, but gave no details.  "There is now additional
information about Ron Arad's past and I hope that perhaps there will
be some about the future.  At this stage, one must be cautious and not
say too much," Rabin said.



</PRE>
