<PRE>
                        (C) The Jerusalem Post 1992
                        Thursday, June 30, 1994



Source: AP


        TEHERAN DENIES HOLDING RON ARAD


NICOSIA - Teheran has denied IAF navigator Ron Arad is being held
in Iran, but made no mention of Israeli claims he may be in south
Lebanon.

The Iranian Foreign Ministry on Tuesday said "allegations made by
the Zionist regime on the presence of an Israeli pilot in Iran" are a
"sheer lie," according to an Islamic Republic News Agency dispatch
issued yesterday and monitored in Cyprus.

Oded Ben-Ami, spokesman for Prime Minister Yitzhak Rabin, told
The Associated Press yesterday that "Israel holds Iran, or Iranian
officials in Lebanon, responsible for Ron Arad." However, he declined
to discuss Arad's precise whereabouts.



