<PRE>
                        (C) The Jerusalem Post 1992
                        Thursday, July 14, 1994



Source: Itim

Lebanon.

        HIZBULLAH ACTIVISTS CRITICIZE THE HOLDING OF RON ARAD



VETERAN Hizbullah activists yesterday criticized the continued holding of
downed navigator Ron Arad, saying it had led to the  IAF bombing of their base
in Baalbek in Lebanon.

In an open letter published in the Lebanese newspaper Al-Shara, the "Young
Believers" said Hizbullah activities were not  being conducted in consultation
with Islamic spiritual leaders, and cited several attacks, demanding to know
which Islamic leader  had authorized them.

One of the incidents cited was "the kidnapping of the cursed Jew  ...  When
the pilot (sic) was not returned, Ain Kuchab in  Baalbek was bombed.  How do
they justify keeping the pilot, when believers are killed because of it?



</PRE>
