<PRE>
                        (C) The Jerusalem Post 1992
                        Friday, July 15, 1994

Memo: NEWS IN BRIEF

Source: Itim


        AIR SHOW TO HONOR RON ARAD



One hundred pilots will land on a special runway near Ron Arad's Hod Hasharon
home this morning as a part of an air show to  draw attention to the fate of
the missing air force navigator.

"It will be the largest and most impressive air show which will express the
feeling of the entire nation that Ron Arad must  not be forgotten," a pilot
participating in the event said yesterday.

The pilot who flew with Arad to Lebanon when their plane was shot down will
land the first plane at 8:30, with Knesset  Speaker Shevah Weiss as his
passenger.  A ceremony will be held at 10:30.



</PRE>
<CENTER>
<P><A HREF="http://www.macom.co.il"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/Images/macom.gif"></A>
</CENTER>
